-- arcs

As cracks form in the institution, Aaron must decide where his allegiance truly lies. His arc explores the cost of obedience and the slow pull of conscience inside a ruthless organization.', NULL, 'miniseries', 2021, 2023, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('34281266-a9f3-58f3-8d84-59523b03be1a', '97ffcc7f-87b2-561b-90f9-5cdd2ee284c2', 'jensen-on-the-case', 'On the Case', 'An FBI agent hunts a contagion that refuses to behave like one.', 'Agent Jensen is handed a case with no precedent: people falling ill and turning violent, with patterns that never resolve. He works each scene methodically, but the affliction stays one step ahead.

As the investigation drags him deeper, Jensen begins to suspect the Empty Man is aware of him. The closer he gets, the more the case feels less like detection and more like a descent.', NULL, 'flagship', 2014, 2015, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('682b0d0f-5a7f-5579-bb38-3e8bd16a80e3', '50855433-d2d1-5f9c-9702-d00738ec879c', 'langford-method', 'Method and Madness', 'A by-the-book agent confronts a case that defies every protocol.', 'Agent Langford brings discipline to the task force, insisting on evidence and procedure where others see only chaos. But the Empty Man does not yield to method, and each careful conclusion collapses under the next impossible scene.

As the affliction spreads, Langford''s faith in her own training erodes. The horror of the case is not just what it does to victims, but what it does to the certainty of those who study it.', NULL, 'flagship', 2014, 2015, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('e8b0b3e6-f19c-5f21-ba9a-ffc7fbff7441', '11e96e21-d2e4-5d82-a94d-9306030b5eb3', 'alex-wilde-partners', 'Partners', 'A by-the-book cop is paired with the city''s strangest new officer.', 'Alex Wilde is assigned to work cases alongside Dragon, and the partnership quickly becomes central to both characters. Her courage and competence earn Dragon''s respect even as the dangers of policing a superhuman city escalate.

The arc establishes her as more than a sidekick, giving her agency in the field and a personal stake in Dragon''s ongoing story.', NULL, 'flagship', 1992, 1995, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('6ccb3c5d-086a-54a4-a7f4-30adb73e40ee', 'fa67ae20-42f4-54bf-9ab2-f502f59f4679', 'alfred-knightfall-role', 'Alfred Through Knightfall', 'As Bruce Wayne is broken by Bane and the Batman mantle passed to a dangerous successor, Alfred is the only witness to the full cost.', 'Alfred''s role through the Knightfall saga is that of an unwilling chronicler — the man who tends Bruce''s injuries, disagrees with his decisions, and stays anyway because leaving would be a different kind of abandonment. His interactions with the Jean-Paul Valley Batman and later Bruce''s returned-but-damaged self provide the most humanizing thread through an event defined by scale. Alfred is the reader''s eye-level figure when everything else operates at myth.', NULL, 'tie-in', 1993, 1994, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('7e9d873a-1e4c-5ed5-81e2-d5736bd93e88', '5a1654d1-4385-5e8a-906a-bea7e536f4c0', 'angel-seeks-redemption', 'A Soul in the Dark', 'A vampire haunted by his sins seeks to do good in a town full of evil.', 'Angel moves through Sunnydale as a mysterious ally, offering Buffy cryptic warnings while hiding the truth of his nature. Burdened by a restored soul, he is tormented by memories of the carnage he once caused.

His path crosses Buffy''s again and again, their bond complicating every battle. Angel''s arc wrestles with whether a monster can ever truly atone, and at what cost to those he loves.', NULL, 'origin', 2019, 2022, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('46d3a4d3-08e9-5961-82bd-4a6d3f1b4cc8', '6c2db9ef-bbd4-5747-a24c-0a880365a1f7', 'infinite-grudge', 'Infinite Grudge', 'A dimension-hopping genius turns his vendetta against Invincible into a multiversal war.', 'Angstrom Levy''s experiments with parallel realities go horribly wrong, and he holds Invincible responsible for the disaster that reshapes his mind and body. Consumed by hatred, he begins orchestrating attacks from across countless worlds.

His schemes blur the lines between dimensions and force Mark to confront the unintended consequences of his own actions.', NULL, 'flagship', 2006, 2008, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('9c7da77e-ea7f-509c-8e99-fb59f199e14e', 'c9c88ca3-3ef2-5d45-8f6d-396a3eaa8bb5', 'the-redeemers-judgment', 'The Redeemer''s Judgment', 'Heaven answers the Hellspawn with a holy counterpart bent on his destruction.', 'The Anti-Spawn descends as Heaven''s response to Spawn, wielding mirrored powers in service of righteous war. Its arrival reframes Spawn''s conflict as part of a larger cosmic struggle.

The Redeemer''s relentless pursuit forces Spawn to confront enemies on both sides of the divine divide, with humanity caught in the crossfire.', NULL, 'flagship', 1995, 1996, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('060cdb7b-2e3a-5bd8-932b-b4f66037caef', '0dfb465e-5cd0-5ab7-b709-d52770d2c9ca', 'age-of-apocalypse', 'Age of Apocalypse', 'A single death rewrites history into a nightmare world ruled by the eternal mutant.', 'A fateful change to the timeline gives rise to a dystopia where Apocalypse conquers North America and mutants and humans are bred, culled, or enslaved. The surviving X-Men wage a desperate resistance.

The sprawling crossover replaced the entire X-line for months with alternate-reality versions of its heroes and villains.

It stands as one of the most ambitious and beloved events of the 1990s, defining Apocalypse''s threat level.', NULL, 'crossover', 1995, 1995, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('d4071e73-6925-5667-a6d4-9864a64ab093', '1b380ed0-a784-5287-91c7-0022525f972b', 'aquaman-the-trench', 'Aquaman: The Trench', 'Arthur Curry confronts ancient horrors rising from the ocean depths.', 'In the New 52 relaunch, Aquaman faces a swarm of monstrous creatures emerging from a deep-sea trench, a threat that tests both his power and his standing among surface dwellers. The story directly addresses and dismantles the perception of Aquaman as a lesser hero.

The arc balances large-scale action with character work, exploring Arthur''s place between land and sea. His resolve and might are on full display.

The creatures of the Trench provide a genuinely frightening menace, raising the stakes of his solo adventures. The story reestablishes Aquaman as a heavyweight.

It set the tone for an acclaimed modern run and reaffirmed his importance to the League.', NULL, 'flagship', 2011, 2012, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('b2768984-eab2-5049-9f4a-796f21f1e886', '000d8224-af33-581d-a1b4-ab3859a83a15', 'ares-gods-and-mortals', 'The War God''s Gambit', 'The god of war manipulates the superpowers of Man''s World toward nuclear annihilation, and only the gods'' new champion can stop him.', 'In George Perez''s relaunch, Ares orchestrates a plot to push humanity into a final, world-ending war that would feed his power beyond measure. The Olympian gods answer by sending Diana into Man''s World as their champion.

The confrontation forces Ares to reckon with a foe who fights not for conquest but for peace. Diana''s victory comes not through force alone but by revealing the self-destructive emptiness of his vision.

The arc establishes Ares as Wonder Woman''s definitive mythological adversary in modern continuity.', NULL, 'origin', 1987, 1987, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('f12eb5ac-47b2-5d6d-9c7a-6fcf794ca3e2', '14c742e8-eabc-5837-9814-14a741690215', 'zola-debut', 'The Living Laboratory', 'Cap uncovers a Nazi geneticist whose monstrous creations defy the boundaries of life and death.', 'Arnim Zola debuts in Jack Kirby''s return to Captain America, revealed as a surviving Nazi scientist whose bizarre bio-engineering produced an army of monsters and his own immortal android form.

His grotesque experiments and connection to the Red Skull establish him as a uniquely unsettling threat in Cap''s rogues'' gallery.', NULL, 'origin', 1977, 1978, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('be7c8379-46cc-599e-a098-9de80d79a14c', 'f4e4d1e4-3ec4-5ff0-a224-54d7ed0b6101', 'zola-castaway', 'Castaway in Dimension Z', 'Stranded in a realm of Zola''s design, Cap must survive years of the geneticist''s relentless cruelty.', 'In Rick Remender''s run, Arnim Zola captures Captain America and strands him in Dimension Z, a nightmarish alien world entirely shaped by Zola''s twisted science. Cap is forced to survive for years and even raise a child amid constant danger.

It is Zola at his most ambitious and personal, testing Cap''s body and principles to the breaking point in a sprawling science-fiction saga.', NULL, 'flagship', 2012, 2013, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('22c5cfde-0d38-5819-8dba-d81e7d36d362', '03830102-aab6-5424-9144-b56148551765', 'eve-origin', 'The Power to Remake', 'A young hero learns the true, staggering scope of her abilities.', 'Atom Eve begins as a teenage superhero whose matter-manipulation seems limited, only to discover her power is nearly boundless. Coming to terms with that potential reshapes her sense of responsibility.

Her journey blends personal struggle with world-altering capability, and she becomes a vital ally to the heroes around her, including the Guardians and Invincible.', NULL, 'origin', 2003, 2005, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('91559069-37dd-5ec8-9d21-6f9bd88f8a12', 'af66e580-7789-5ef1-83f2-7f18c8dd338e', 'rage-of-the-red-lanterns', 'Rage of the Red Lanterns', 'Vengeance takes the shape of a Corps powered by blood and fury.', 'Driven by the slaughter of his people, Atrocitus forges the red ring of rage and gathers the universe''s most furious beings into the Red Lantern Corps. He targets Sinestro and, by extension, the Green Lantern Corps and the Guardians he holds responsible.

The arc introduces the rage entity, the Butcher, and expands the emotional spectrum that drives the lead-up to Blackest Night, with Hal Jordan caught in the crossfire of competing Corps.', NULL, 'crossover', 2008, 2009, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('bbf9d715-3c0f-5f09-b0ce-98b840cae269', 'aea67095-6370-5fcc-bb18-e7d505ce909b', 'avengers-assemble-origin', 'The Coming of the Avengers', 'Loki''s scheme to destroy his brother accidentally unites five heroes into the world''s greatest super-team.', 'When the trickster god Loki manipulates the Hulk into a rampage to lure out Thor, his plan backfires spectacularly. Iron Man, Ant-Man, the Wasp, Thor, and the Hulk are drawn together by the crisis, each answering a call that none of them issued alone. By the time they unravel Loki''s deception, they recognize that their combined strength makes them far more formidable than any of them standing apart.

In the aftermath, the heroes decide to formalize their partnership, and the Wasp gives the team its enduring name. The founding lineup is unconventional, pairing the gamma-powered Hulk with billionaire inventor Iron Man and the literal God of Thunder, but it works precisely because of its contrasts.

This origin sets the template for everything that follows: a team built from clashing personalities held together by shared purpose. It also introduces the dynamic of internal friction, particularly around the unpredictable Hulk, that will recur throughout the team''s history.

The story remains one of Marvel''s most reprinted and adapted, a cornerstone of the Silver Age and the seed from which an entire franchise grew.', NULL, 'origin', 1963, 1963, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('885aa0e8-4998-5c9f-bd96-aa5b29bec632', 'aea67095-6370-5fcc-bb18-e7d505ce909b', 'captain-america-joins', 'Captain America Lives Again', 'The Avengers discover a legendary hero frozen in ice, and the team is never the same.', 'While searching the Arctic seas, the Avengers recover the frozen body of Captain America, lost since the final days of World War II. Revived after decades in suspended animation, Steve Rogers is a man out of time, mourning a war that ended long ago and a partner he could not save.

Despite his disorientation, Captain America''s leadership and unshakable moral clarity quickly make him the heart of the team. His arrival coincides with a period of rapid turnover, as several founders step back and a new generation steps forward.

The story cements Captain America''s place as the Avengers'' conscience and most enduring field leader, a role he will hold across countless rosters. It also deepens the team''s identity, anchoring its modern adventures to the legacy of the Golden Age.

This arc is frequently cited as the moment the Avengers became more than a collection of powerhouses, gaining a unifying ideal embodied by their newly thawed champion.', NULL, 'flagship', 1964, 1964, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('9a1ec13a-d339-5725-9571-f6fe715a9153', '4406c4a8-b1e7-5d9b-ad17-437b75dfd0fa', 'kree-skrull-war', 'The Kree-Skrull War', 'The Avengers are caught between two warring alien empires with Earth as the battleground.', 'Two of the galaxy''s great powers, the militaristic Kree and the shapeshifting Skrulls, bring their ancient conflict to Earth''s doorstep. The Avengers find themselves drawn into an interstellar war while simultaneously battling paranoia and political persecution at home as Skrull infiltrators sow distrust.

Writer Roy Thomas crafts a sweeping cosmic epic that expands the Avengers'' scope from street-level threats to galaxy-spanning stakes. The saga features Captain Marvel, the Inhumans, and a pivotal turn for the Vision and the Scarlet Witch.

The story is renowned for raising the ceiling on what an Avengers narrative could be, blending Cold War allegory with widescreen science fiction. Its influence echoes through decades of cosmic Marvel storytelling.

Regularly ranked among the greatest Avengers tales ever told, the Kree-Skrull War remains a benchmark for ambitious superhero space opera.', NULL, 'flagship', 1971, 1972, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('966907a0-a895-5176-8e1d-f86ef4355fd8', '4406c4a8-b1e7-5d9b-ad17-437b75dfd0fa', 'the-korvac-saga', 'The Korvac Saga', 'A near-omnipotent being walks among ordinary people, and the Avengers may already be too late to stop him.', 'Michael Korvac, a man transformed into a cosmic entity of staggering power, quietly establishes himself on Earth with plans that could reshape reality itself. The Avengers slowly become aware of the threat, but their adversary''s power is so vast that confronting him at all carries catastrophic risk.

Writer Jim Shooter builds the saga as a slow-burn mystery that explodes into one of the most consequential battles in Avengers history. The story interrogates the nature of power, judgment, and whether even godlike strength justifies absolute control.

With a massive roster of heroes drawn into the final confrontation, the Korvac Saga delivers an emotionally complex climax that lingers long after the fighting stops. It is celebrated for treating its cosmic villain as a genuinely tragic and ambiguous figure.

The arc stands as a defining Bronze Age epic and a frequent recommendation for readers seeking the team at its most thoughtful and operatic.', NULL, 'flagship', 1977, 1978, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('3f9e97af-a9a3-56fd-ad2a-c6d326ec15a8', '4406c4a8-b1e7-5d9b-ad17-437b75dfd0fa', 'under-siege', 'Under Siege', 'Baron Zemo assembles a small army to break the Avengers in their own home.', 'Baron Helmut Zemo gathers a massive incarnation of the Masters of Evil with a single goal: not merely to defeat the Avengers, but to humiliate and destroy them utterly. Striking when the team is at its most vulnerable, the villains seize Avengers Mansion itself.

Writer Roger Stern and artist John Buscema deliver a tense, brutal siege that pushes the heroes to their physical and emotional limits. Captain America, Hercules, and the others must claw their way back from one of the darkest defeats the team has ever suffered.

The arc is praised for its high stakes and character-driven tension, treating the villains as a credible existential threat rather than disposable obstacles. The toll it takes on the team resonates for years afterward.

''Under Siege'' is widely regarded as one of the finest Avengers stories of the 1980s and a masterclass in the team-under-pressure formula.', NULL, 'flagship', 1986, 1987, 3, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('072bc982-7019-5917-984f-4de28b04b868', '333f2ff5-6aef-55d2-9ee5-06351e869e45', 'avengers-disassembled', 'Avengers Disassembled', 'On an ordinary day, the team is torn apart from within by a betrayal no one saw coming.', 'What begins as a routine afternoon at Avengers Mansion erupts into chaos as the team is struck by a cascade of impossible tragedies. As the heroes reel, they discover that the source of the catastrophe is far closer to home than any external enemy.

Writer Brian Michael Bendis uses the story to demolish the long-standing status quo and clear the ground for a bold relaunch. The arc is deliberately devastating, breaking apart relationships and institutions that had stood for decades.

Though divisive at the time for its grim turns, ''Disassembled'' proved enormously influential, ushering in the modern, event-driven era of Avengers publishing. It set the stage for the New Avengers and the line-wide sagas that followed.

The story is essential reading for understanding the franchise''s 21st-century direction, even as it remains one of its most debated.', 'The catastrophe is revealed to be caused by a mentally fractured Scarlet Witch, whose reality-warping grief kills several teammates.', 'flagship', 2004, 2004, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('03b8190d-f1a5-522f-9d94-a9de6255ad1a', '333f2ff5-6aef-55d2-9ee5-06351e869e45', 'new-avengers-breakout', 'New Avengers: Breakout', 'A massive prison break throws a mismatched group of heroes together and forges a brand-new team.', 'When a catastrophic breakout empties a maximum-security prison for super-criminals, a disparate group of heroes converges on the scene to contain the disaster. Among them are Captain America, Iron Man, Spider-Man, Luke Cage, and Spider-Woman, none of whom planned to form a team.

Writer Brian Michael Bendis and artist David Finch relaunch the franchise with a fresh, character-driven energy and a roster designed to surprise long-time readers. The breakout itself proves to be no accident, hinting at a larger conspiracy that will unfold over years.

The arc reestablishes the Avengers for a new generation, mixing A-list icons with grounded street-level heroes. Its success made the New Avengers the flagship title of the modern Marvel line.

''Breakout'' is the ideal jumping-on point for readers entering the modern era, balancing accessibility with the seeds of epic storytelling to come.', NULL, 'flagship', 2005, 2005, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('dcb58b19-2365-571c-8733-c09ecf252a70', '333f2ff5-6aef-55d2-9ee5-06351e869e45', 'the-infinity-gauntlet', 'The Infinity Gauntlet', 'A cosmic tyrant gathers ultimate power, and the universe''s heroes make a desperate last stand.', 'Thanos, having assembled the six Infinity Gems into a single gauntlet, gains command over reality, time, space, soul, mind, and power. To prove his devotion to Death, he erases half of all living things from existence with a snap of his fingers.

The surviving heroes, led by Adam Warlock and including the Avengers among Earth''s mightiest champions, mount an all-but-hopeless assault against a being who has become functionally omnipotent. Writer Jim Starlin crafts a cosmic epic of staggering scale and surprising philosophical depth.

Though technically a line-wide event rather than a solo Avengers title, the saga showcases the team at the center of the universe''s greatest crisis and provides the direct inspiration for the climax of the Marvel Cinematic Universe.

''The Infinity Gauntlet'' is essential cosmic reading, a story whose imagery and stakes have become part of popular culture far beyond comics.', NULL, 'crossover', 1991, 1991, 3, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('0bd1679e-d087-57a9-8721-b55a93e7313b', '683104c4-8b36-53bf-9601-adabdfc1c94b', 'badrock-breakthrough', 'Breakthrough', 'A transformed teen learns to be a hero while navigating a body of living stone.', 'Badrock joins the team and quickly becomes its heart, balancing classroom anxieties with world-saving missions. His arc explores growing up in the glare of celebrity heroics.

His strength frequently turns the tide in the team''s biggest battles.', NULL, 'origin', 1992, 1993, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('4be84c6f-0211-5ab3-bc7d-20bf38313f37', '40dc25b3-8951-58e6-a196-7ffffb07cb44', 'bane-vengeance-introduction', 'Vengeance of Bane and Knightfall', 'A tactician born in prison studies the world''s greatest detective and designs a campaign to destroy him that begins not with combat but with logistics.', 'Chuck Dixon and Graham Nolan''s Vengeance of Bane #1 is a remarkable piece of villain construction — a single issue that builds Bane''s entire backstory, his physical and intellectual development, and his fixation on Batman as the ultimate test case, before he has appeared in the ongoing series at all. It functions as both an origin story and a threat assessment. The subsequent Knightfall arc delivers on every promise the one-shot makes.', 'Bane breaks Bruce Wayne''s back at the conclusion of his Knightfall campaign.', 'origin', 1993, 1993, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('64e73110-1b56-5efe-906f-7958deedce26', 'b7b04b09-3c36-550e-b7b8-35372f672c8d', 'oracle-birds-of-prey', 'Birds of Prey: Of Like Minds', 'Oracle and Black Canary''s partnership becomes the foundation for a global network of heroines operating in the spaces the Justice League doesn''t reach.', 'Gail Simone''s run on Birds of Prey, beginning with the ''Of Like Minds'' arc in 2003, is where Oracle fully arrives as a lead character rather than a supporting resource. The relationship between Barbara and Dinah Lance (Black Canary) is written as an equal partnership between two people with different skills and the same commitment, and the villains — including the Calculator, positioned as Oracle''s direct dark mirror — are worthy opponents. The series treated female heroes as competent professionals rather than exceptional exceptions.', NULL, 'flagship', 2003, 2007, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('5e988b51-db29-5e17-8fb6-66e590ce7a0d', '245a71b5-3d09-5b07-9349-99b4bd618802', 'barbaric-strength-in-numbers', 'Strength in Numbers', 'A powerful bruiser joins forces with the city''s heroes to take on overwhelming odds.', 'Barbaric arrives as a muscular ally ready to stand beside Dragon against threats too large for any single hero. His strength and dependable spirit make him a welcome addition to the city''s heroic ranks.

The arc cements his role as a team player and develops his partnership with the speedster Ricochet.', NULL, 'flagship', 1994, 1998, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('5182edc0-70f1-56a9-b442-06515371e3bc', '9efc0483-7e22-52cb-a5b4-e1de71ef1c48', 'zemo-under-siege', 'Under Siege', 'Helmut Zemo assembles the Masters of Evil for a brutal assault on the Avengers'' home.', 'Helmut Zemo gathers the largest and most dangerous incarnation of the Masters of Evil and launches a devastating siege on Avengers Mansion, capturing and torturing members in one of the team''s darkest hours.

The story is a landmark Avengers epic that showcases Zemo as a genuinely menacing strategist, settling old family scores against Captain America in the process.', NULL, 'flagship', 1986, 1987, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('6a5607d4-e905-53eb-936e-ef6081d939b8', '3ebd705d-dae0-57f4-9602-1b341bc94861', 'zemo-justice-like-lightning', 'Justice, Like Lightning', 'Disguised as new heroes, Zemo''s villains step into the void left by the missing Avengers.', 'With the Avengers presumed dead, Baron Zemo unveils the Thunderbolts, a team of seemingly new heroes who are secretly his Masters of Evil in disguise. The shocking twist redefined the villain as a master manipulator.

The series complicates Zemo''s role, as some members begin to embrace heroism for real, turning his grand con into something he never anticipated.', 'The heroic Thunderbolts are secretly Baron Zemo''s Masters of Evil in disguise.', 'flagship', 1997, 1998, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('1a1de318-a3e8-5c71-bc17-6775f1589058', '3a0cd5e6-4921-50ce-8b01-e962b13d6be3', 'batman-golden-age-origins', 'The First Cases: Golden Age Batman', 'The original Darknight Detective emerges from Gotham''s shadows, before the mythology had a name.', 'The earliest Batman stories are pulp crime yarns stripped to the bone: a masked figure descending on criminals who thought themselves untouchable. Finger and Kane worked without a rulebook, so these tales have a raw, sometimes contradictory energy. Batman uses guns, operates without any defined code, and reads more as urban avenger than costumed hero. The Joker appears in the very first Batman issue (Batman #1, 1940), already fully formed as a grinning agent of chaos. Catwoman, called ''The Cat'' in her debut, appears in that same issue as a jewel thief rather than an outright villain. These stories matter less for polish than for establishing the genetic code of everything that follows.', NULL, 'origin', 1939, 1949, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('243d0f65-9ef2-5d2b-a9f3-9ee4fb7d08a0', '3a0cd5e6-4921-50ce-8b01-e962b13d6be3', 'batman-robin-era', 'Batman and Robin, the Dynamic Duo', 'A young ward becomes the Boy Wonder and Gotham''s criminals face two detectives instead of one.', 'Robin''s debut in Detective Comics #38 (1940) transformed Batman from lone vigilante into mentor, shifting the series'' tone toward youthful adventure. Dick Grayson — a circus acrobat orphaned by a mob hit — gave Batman both a reason to explain his methods and a moral compass defined by protecting innocence rather than simply punishing crime. The duo''s chemistry became the template for superhero partnerships, and the stories of this period have a serial-adventure quality: globe-trotting cases, elaborate death-trap escapes, and Gotham as a city that genuinely needed heroes rather than just feared them.', NULL, 'flagship', 1940, 1969, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('ad9a9255-aa6d-5274-82ed-774d12cfbc7f', '9bdd4a07-c9a5-54ea-b53c-77f1b4a07c7d', 'batman-ras-al-ghul-introduction', 'Daughter of the Demon', 'Batman crosses swords with a centuries-old eco-terrorist who sees him as the world''s finest detective — and a potential heir.', 'Ra''s al Ghul debuted across a pair of stories in Batman #232 and #235 (1971), and the character arrived fully realized: a man of genuine brilliance, operational resources spanning continents, and a goal — global population reduction to save the planet — that he believes is righteous. The story in which Ra''s reveals he has deduced Batman''s identity and orchestrated a test to gauge his worthiness stands as one of the era''s most elegant plotting coups. O''Neil built a villain who respects Batman as an equal, a dynamic that would produce some of the character''s most intellectually engaging conflicts across decades.', NULL, 'flagship', 1971, 1972, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('805f9c40-83fa-5a65-aec1-268616cc24d7', '9bdd4a07-c9a5-54ea-b53c-77f1b4a07c7d', 'batman-joker-deadly-joke-bronze', 'O''Neil''s Joker: The Clown Prince Returns', 'Batman''s most unpredictable enemy is restored to lethal form after years of harmless television villainy.', 'Denny O''Neil''s handling of the Joker through the 1970s set the template every subsequent writer follows: a killer who treats death as performance art, whose schemes are never purely about money or power but about the aesthetic pleasure of chaos. The 1975 Joker solo series, though short-lived, gave the character extended page time as an unreliable protagonist and demonstrated how uncomfortable it is to follow a point of view defined by randomized violence. These stories cleared the way for Alan Moore and Frank Miller''s later, darker interpretations by establishing that the Joker''s comedy and his menace were inseparable.', NULL, 'flagship', 1973, 1979, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('dfe567e0-2799-59a5-9952-ff567bdf2366', '3ff4daa2-871d-54ba-bb3d-418b047a3819', 'batman-year-one', 'Batman: Year One', 'A young Bruce Wayne returns to Gotham and makes every costly mistake a first-year vigilante could make.', 'Frank Miller and David Mazzucchelli''s 1987 story is structured as parallel journals: Bruce Wayne learning the brutal logistics of becoming Batman while Lieutenant James Gordon arrives in Gotham and discovers a city so corrupt it has digested his idealism before he can unpack his boxes. The genius of the approach is that Batman is genuinely bad at his job early on — caught, burned out of a building, nearly killed — while Gordon is nearly as isolated as he is. Their paths toward becoming the city''s two honest men run in tandem without ever quite meeting. Mazzucchelli''s artwork uses a muted, almost noir palette that feels less like superhero comics than illustrated crime fiction.', NULL, 'origin', 1987, 1987, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('45b6b0d8-dbb8-5596-8155-672b597f0109', '3ff4daa2-871d-54ba-bb3d-418b047a3819', 'batman-the-killing-joke', 'The Killing Joke', 'The Joker sets out to prove that one catastrophic day is all it takes to break a person — any person.', 'Alan Moore and Brian Bolland''s 1988 prestige format one-shot is a sustained meditation on the question both Batman and the Joker refuse to answer honestly: how different are they, really? Moore frames the Joker''s rampage through a noir-tinted origin story that positions the villain as a failed comedian whose worst day triggered an irreversible psychological break. Bolland''s meticulously rendered artwork treats Gotham as a decaying carnival ground. The story''s violence toward Barbara Gordon became one of DC''s most debated editorial decisions, reframing her arc for decades and generating ongoing conversation about what comics are permitted to do to their characters.', 'Barbara Gordon is shot and permanently paralyzed by the Joker during his assault on Commissioner Gordon''s household.', 'miniseries', 1988, 1988, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('1b11ea26-5a42-585d-9ea8-339d0cd4a233', '3ff4daa2-871d-54ba-bb3d-418b047a3819', 'batman-knightfall', 'Knightfall', 'A new villain systematically dismantles every tool and ally Batman has before confronting him face to face.', 'The 1993–1994 Knightfall saga is the rare crossover event that earns its scale. Bane — introduced as a tactician rather than a bruiser — opens Arkham Asylum and forces Batman to recapture his entire rogues gallery in a grueling gauntlet designed to exhaust him completely before Bane himself moves. The strategy works. The resulting confrontation at Wayne Manor is not a heroic stand but a calculated execution of a weakened man. What follows in the Knightsquest and KnightsEnd chapters tracks the consequences of Bruce handing the mantle to an unstable successor, and eventually his own painful return to form.', 'Bane breaks Batman''s back at Wayne Manor. Bruce Wayne appoints Jean-Paul Valley (Azrael) as Batman, but Valley proves psychologically unstable and Bruce must eventually take the role back after recovering.', 'crossover', 1993, 1994, 3, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('724a3be7-2869-55c1-8786-43cf7ae985c7', '3ff4daa2-871d-54ba-bb3d-418b047a3819', 'batman-no-mans-land', 'No Man''s Land', 'After a devastating earthquake, the federal government abandons Gotham to its criminals — and Batman must take it back block by block.', 'The 1999 crossover event ran through nearly every Batman-family title and committed to an audacious premise: strip Batman of every resource, every institutional support, and every backup plan, then make him fight a territorial war for a city no one else wants to save. Gotham is carved into gang territories, with villains like Penguin, Two-Face, and Joker holding neighborhoods as warlords. Batman spends much of the story absent, forcing his allies — Nightwing, Oracle, Huntress, and eventually a new Batgirl — into extended leading roles. The event is emotionally rich and logistically elaborate in a way few crossovers attempt.', 'The Joker murders Sarah Essen Gordon, Commissioner Gordon''s wife, during the climax of the No Man''s Land conflict.', 'crossover', 1999, 1999, 4, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('c650c12b-f0bd-5e30-9532-89620e6a6364', 'd021d09f-dc55-5b0f-a67d-7bbdd3a273f1', 'batman-hush', 'Hush', 'A masked enemy who knows Bruce Wayne''s secrets orchestrates a conspiracy using Batman''s entire rogues gallery as pawns.', 'Jeph Loeb and Jim Lee''s twelve-issue run from 2002–2003 is deliberately a greatest-hits presentation: nearly every major Batman villain appears, Catwoman''s role in Bruce''s emotional life is examined, and Jim Lee''s artwork delivers the definitive modern-era visual version of the character. The mystery at the center — who is the bandaged figure pulling strings from offstage — works better as a vehicle for the character pairings than as a pure whodunit, but the story''s emotional beats between Bruce and Selina are more thoughtful than its plotting reputation suggests. It remains a reliable recommendation for readers who want a single story that deploys the full Batman universe.', NULL, 'flagship', 2002, 2003, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('04f3ddb6-0516-5e56-a3ec-496d29bb3f2e', 'd021d09f-dc55-5b0f-a67d-7bbdd3a273f1', 'batman-morrison-run', 'Grant Morrison''s Batman', 'Batman confronts the darkest chapter of his past, a crime cult targeting his legacy, and what it means to survive death itself.', 'Grant Morrison''s run, beginning in Batman #655 (2006) and threading through multiple titles over several years, treats the entire published history of Batman as psychological fact rather than discarding inconvenient eras. Morrison reintroduced Damian Wayne — Bruce''s son with Talia al Ghul — as an immediate complication to the Batman mythology. The run builds toward ''Batman R.I.P.,'' a story constructed around a psychological attack on Bruce''s mind, followed by Final Crisis, in which Darkseid apparently kills Batman with the Omega Sanction. What follows across ''Batman and Robin'' — Dick Grayson assuming the role while Bruce is lost in time — is Morrison''s most disciplined storytelling. The entire arc rewards readers who treat it as a single novel.', 'Bruce Wayne is believed killed by Darkseid''s Omega Beams but is actually displaced through time, forced to fight his way back to the present.', 'flagship', 2006, 2011, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('d0535082-b961-54a7-ac6e-28534146cf02', 'e15f9479-1fdd-5545-95fc-fe35ee5894ff', 'batman-court-of-owls', 'The Court of Owls', 'A secret society has controlled Gotham from the shadows for centuries — and Batman never knew they existed.', 'Scott Snyder and Greg Capullo''s opening New 52 arc manages something rare: a new villain (the Talon, enforcers of the Court) that feels genuinely threatening against a character who has faced every kind of enemy imaginable. The Court of Owls — a conspiracy of Gotham''s oldest families who have quietly guided the city''s history while eliminating anyone who learned too much — lands as a credible concept because Snyder''s script is careful to establish the psychological stakes. Batman believes he knows Gotham entirely; the arc is about what it costs him to be wrong. The maze sequence in issues #5–6 is one of the decade''s most formally inventive superhero comics sequences.', NULL, 'flagship', 2011, 2012, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('bcd306fb-b299-574a-a288-13d8f0fc9eac', 'e15f9479-1fdd-5545-95fc-fe35ee5894ff', 'batman-death-of-the-family', 'Death of the Family', 'The Joker returns after years of absence with a plan to destroy everything Batman has built — by targeting the people he loves.', 'Snyder''s Joker arc from 2012–2013 is built on a single terrifying premise: the Joker has decided the Batman family is a weakness that degrades the purity of his relationship with Batman. His campaign against Nightwing, Batgirl, Robin, and the others is not random violence but pointed manipulation, pushing each toward breaking. Capullo''s redesign of the Joker — with his own removed face worn as a mask — is deeply unsettling in ways that feel earned rather than gratuitous. The crossover tie-in issues give each family member a distinct confrontation, making this one of the more satisfying event structures of the era.', NULL, 'crossover', 2012, 2013, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('cf217cde-82b5-5ea9-9021-1edbc0a6735e', 'e15f9479-1fdd-5545-95fc-fe35ee5894ff', 'batman-tom-king-run', 'Tom King''s Batman: The Wedding and I Am Bane', 'Bruce Wayne proposes to Selina Kyle while Gotham''s deadliest villain turns the entire city into a weapon against him.', 'Tom King''s 85-issue run beginning in 2016 is the most formally ambitious sustained Batman work since Morrison''s. King treats Batman as a man who chose suffering as identity, and examines whether someone defined by tragedy is capable of happiness. The engagement to Selina Kyle (Catwoman) structures much of the run''s emotional architecture, while ''I Am Bane'' delivers the best Bane story since Knightfall — a relentless, formally perfect five-issue sprint that functions as pure action cinema translated onto the page. Mitch Gerads and Joëlle Jones are the standout artistic contributors, each defining distinct sections of the run''s visual register.', 'Selina Kyle is manipulated into abandoning Bruce at the altar by Holly Robinson and the Gotham villain Bane, as part of a conspiracy to keep Batman in a state of suffering that makes him effective.', 'flagship', 2016, 2019, 3, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('36deca8d-3f8e-5ba3-baae-21539ab8c678', '2a407e97-483c-535c-a167-4723b53154ca', 'bautista-the-keeper', 'The Keeper', 'A veteran hunter guards the order''s traditions as younger members begin to question them.', 'Bautista represents the House''s institutional memory, embodying the discipline and traditions that define a hunter. His scenes ground the order''s culture and its expectations.

The arc shows how the old guard responds when the younger generation starts to challenge the way things have always been done.', NULL, 'flagship', 2021, 2024, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('dd7acb01-b653-5ac1-9d12-23c0b1db9bc1', '9d4c63c6-0da7-503a-a4d5-21add4cce21d', 'beast-boy-joins', 'Joining the Titans', 'A shapeshifting former Doom Patrol member finds a new family with the Titans.', 'Garfield Logan brings his animal-morphing powers and irrepressible humor to the New Teen Titans, masking the grief of his Doom Patrol past beneath jokes. The team becomes the family he has long needed.

The arc develops his powers and personality, balancing levity with the loss that shapes him, and cements him as an enduring Titans staple.', NULL, 'flagship', 1980, 1982, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('a1c1be97-62d2-5626-a00d-a57732a4cb35', '58322929-e6cc-549d-8052-cb8c95ea060a', 'mind-over-might', 'Mind Over Might', 'When the Rangers'' power falters, Billy''s intellect becomes their only weapon.', 'Billy is forced to improvise solutions when the team faces enemies that cannot be beaten by force alone. His engineering and analysis keep the Rangers one step ahead of Rita''s deadliest schemes.

The arc affirms that the team''s brain is every bit as vital as its muscle, and that Billy''s quiet bravery matches anyone''s.', NULL, 'flagship', 2016, 2017, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('474dbe11-0d6a-52fd-bf3e-f7dc97d9fbbf', '5f3f50fd-7997-5a38-9aa2-542824d479d7', 'samson-return', 'Back in the Suit', 'A seasoned hero returns to the fight to steady a green team.', 'Black Samson rejoins active duty using a formidable suit of armor, bringing maturity to a roster heavy with newcomers. His experience helps anchor the team during chaotic battles.

His arc explores what it means to keep fighting long past one''s prime, and the quiet value of a veteran who has seen it all.', NULL, 'flagship', 2006, 2010, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('5e02cabc-f8e5-58c1-9279-9e13fc0c634b', '2a7c3a1b-ffb5-5cc0-aaba-a7192b93c1d4', 'black-widow-name-of-rose', 'The Name of the Rose', 'Natasha confronts a conspiracy from her past while questioning who she can trust.', 'When Black Widow finds herself targeted and seemingly betrayed by those closest to her, she is forced to navigate a web of espionage that reaches back into her shadowy history. Every ally becomes a potential enemy.

Writer Marjorie Liu crafts a tense spy thriller that leans into Natasha''s strengths as a survivor and strategist. The story strips away her support network to test her resolve.

The arc deepens the character''s mythology, examining the cost of a life built on secrets. It is a strong showcase of the Black Widow as a solo lead.

''The Name of the Rose'' is an excellent entry point for readers drawn to grounded, espionage-driven stories.', NULL, 'miniseries', 2010, 2010, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('2e9f7c53-219b-5f3f-9c7e-4a69f5054f0f', 'c4419dc3-2112-5468-8868-64f103e31667', 'brainiac-collector', 'Brainiac', 'The true Brainiac comes to Earth to harvest a city and confront the last son of Krypton.', 'Geoff Johns and Gary Frank present the definitive modern Brainiac, revealing the cosmic scope of his city-collecting campaign across the galaxy. His connection to the lost city of Kandor raises the stakes for Superman personally.

The story portrays Brainiac as a genuinely terrifying force of cold calculation, a being who treats living worlds as data to be catalogued. His arrival threatens Earth with the same fate as countless other planets.

The confrontation tests Superman and his allies against an intelligence that plans for every variable. Brainiac''s menace lies in his patience and precision.

The arc reframes Brainiac as a top-tier universal threat relevant to the entire League.', NULL, 'flagship', 2008, 2008, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('b88e7318-68d0-551c-9ee4-036b5d435f96', '186002b2-bc70-5c0d-8dc5-7090bed1cb3f', 'brother-blood-rising', 'Rise of the Church of Blood', 'A charismatic immortal builds a fanatical church and sets it against the young heroes.', 'Brother Blood''s Church of Blood expands its reach, ensnaring innocents and even members of the Titans'' orbit in its web of devotion. The team must confront an enemy whose true weapon is belief itself.

The arc establishes Brother Blood as a uniquely unsettling villain who weaponizes faith, distinguishing him from the team''s more conventional foes.', NULL, 'flagship', 1982, 1983, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('9d9267b5-91a9-596d-8eec-1d046c5efd31', '4b7a4661-0d4a-5b1a-8fdf-75177d65e007', 'soporus-sermons', 'Sermons of the Empty', 'A preacher transforms a plague into a faith one convert at a time.', 'Brother Soporus arrives where the affliction has already begun, offering the sick a story that makes their suffering holy. His sermons reframe the Empty Man as a presence to be welcomed, and the desperate listen.

As his congregation grows, so does the contagion, and the task force comes to understand that his words spread the affliction as surely as any pathogen. He is a vector wearing the robes of a prophet.', NULL, 'flagship', 2014, 2015, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('de6f02aa-1d89-5a51-8b75-9d4523a1f41f', '5ecf0d53-3df1-512d-8491-48e3079736fd', 'high-school-is-hell', 'High School Is Hell', 'A new girl in town learns that her town sits atop a literal mouth of hell.', 'Buffy Summers transfers to Sunnydale High hoping for a fresh start, only to discover that the school sits directly over a Hellmouth that draws every kind of monster to its doors. Guided by the watchful librarian Rupert Giles, she reluctantly accepts that she is the Slayer, the one girl in all the world chosen to stand against the darkness.

As she finds her footing, Buffy gathers an unlikely circle of friends. The bookish Willow Rosenberg and the wisecracking Xander Harris stumble into her secret and refuse to walk away, forming the nucleus of what will become her chosen family.

The arc establishes the rhythm of Buffy''s double life: cramming for tests by day, patrolling cemeteries by night, and keeping her two worlds from colliding. It reframes the original premise for a new generation while staying true to its heart.', NULL, 'origin', 2019, 2019, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('57ed0377-4f4b-5a28-b850-eb0fd36513a2', '5ecf0d53-3df1-512d-8491-48e3079736fd', 'a-hellmouth-rising', 'A Hellmouth Rising', 'An ancient vampire stirs beneath Sunnydale, testing the new Slayer''s resolve.', 'With the Scooby Gang now established, Buffy faces her first true existential threat as a centuries-old vampire moves to crack open the Hellmouth and remake the world in shadow. The stakes escalate from monster-of-the-week patrols to a campaign against a patient, ancient enemy.

Buffy must learn to lead rather than simply fight, coordinating Willow''s burgeoning talents, Xander''s loyalty, and Giles''s hard-won lore. The pressure exposes how isolating the Slayer''s calling can be, even surrounded by friends.

The arc deepens the mythology of Sunnydale and seeds the larger conflicts that will define Buffy''s tenure as the town''s protector.', NULL, 'flagship', 2019, 2020, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('bc302dfa-36f9-50b5-9f70-1daf2569ca09', '611345dc-7819-57c0-9fde-8ad3b3bb8bbc', 'ring-of-fire', 'Ring of Fire', 'A demonic conspiracy forces the Scoobies to fight on multiple fronts at once.', 'An escalating demonic plot threatens to tear Sunnydale apart from within, splitting the Scooby Gang across separate battlegrounds. Buffy must trust her friends to hold lines she cannot reach herself, learning that being the Chosen One does not mean fighting alone.

Alliances shift as morally grey figures circle the conflict, some offering help with hidden costs. Buffy is forced to weigh expedience against principle in ways that will shape who she becomes.

The arc raises the emotional and tactical stakes of the relaunch, cementing the ensemble as a true team while testing the limits of Buffy''s trust.', NULL, 'flagship', 2020, 2021, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('87b6fa94-6940-5888-a0d4-2ae4f7a3ff42', '611345dc-7819-57c0-9fde-8ad3b3bb8bbc', 'hellmouth-crossover', 'Hellmouth', 'Two Slayers and a city full of monsters collide when the Hellmouth tears wide open.', 'The Hellmouth event erupts when the barrier between worlds collapses, flooding Sunnydale with demons and drawing in allies and enemies from across the BOOM! Buffyverse. Buffy joins forces with other champions to seal the breach before it consumes everything.

This crossover braids multiple titles together, forcing characters who would never cooperate into uneasy alliances. The scale dwarfs anything Buffy has faced, demanding sacrifice from the entire ensemble.

The arc is the relaunch''s first major line-wide event, a proving ground that redefines the boundaries of the new continuity.', NULL, 'crossover', 2021, 2022, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('49ee1495-beac-5e52-9195-cb85d902db52', 'a889b714-22c7-5208-9ec2-e6b7d79f4a4a', 'birth-of-a-legend', 'Birth of a Legend', 'A weakling rejected by the army volunteers for a secret experiment and emerges as America''s first Super-Soldier.', 'Steve Rogers, desperate to serve his country but repeatedly classified 4-F, is selected by the U.S. military for Project Rebirth, a clandestine program to create a Super-Soldier. Under the guidance of the brilliant Dr. Abraham Erskine, Rogers receives the Super-Soldier Serum and is bombarded with Vita-Rays, transforming his frail body into the peak of human physical perfection.

Moments after the procedure succeeds, an enemy agent assassinates Erskine, ensuring the secret formula dies with him and leaving Rogers as the one and only Captain America. Donning a star-spangled costume and carrying a shield, he becomes a one-man symbol of resistance against the Axis powers.

These early tales establish the core of the legend: a humble young man given great power who chooses to use it selflessly. Alongside his teenage sidekick Bucky Barnes, Cap takes the fight to spies, saboteurs, and the masterminds of the Third Reich.', NULL, 'origin', 1941, 1941, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('8ccecd49-51c8-520c-8a79-1832ed0bd7a9', 'a889b714-22c7-5208-9ec2-e6b7d79f4a4a', 'war-against-the-red-skull', 'The War Against the Red Skull', 'Captain America and Bucky wage a relentless campaign against the Axis and the terrifying Red Skull.', 'Throughout World War II, Captain America serves as both a frontline soldier and a symbol of hope on the home front. He and Bucky uncover Nazi plots, rescue prisoners, and dismantle sabotage rings, all while facing off against the Red Skull, Hitler''s most feared agent and Cap''s defining nemesis.

The Red Skull embodies the ideology Cap was created to oppose, and their clashes become epic battles of will and brutality. These stories cemented Captain America as the premier patriotic hero of the Golden Age, outselling many of his contemporaries.

The wartime run is fast-paced, two-fisted pulp adventure, full of dramatic splash pages and larger-than-life villains. It laid the thematic groundwork that every later writer would build upon: Cap as the conscience of a nation at war.', NULL, 'flagship', 1941, 1945, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('cea1eba1-60ed-56ce-bff9-23b6bde8fe1c', '58acfcfe-ce5b-573c-b8ad-fc8247c505d3', 'captain-america-lives-again', 'Captain America Lives Again', 'The Avengers discover a frozen soldier in the North Atlantic and revive the legend everyone believed dead.', 'In Avengers #4, the recently formed team finds a man frozen in a block of ice in the North Atlantic. Thawed and revived, he is revealed to be Captain America, who has been in suspended animation since the final days of World War II. He joins the Avengers, instantly becoming the team''s heart and tactical leader.

But survival comes at a terrible cost. Steve Rogers is a man displaced in time, haunted by the apparent death of Bucky in the explosion that flung him into the icy sea. This single reveal transformed Cap from a simple patriot into one of Marvel''s most psychologically rich characters.

Stan Lee and Jack Kirby used this premise to explore alienation, guilt, and the question of whether old-fashioned ideals still have a place in a cynical modern era. It is the cornerstone of the modern Captain America.', 'Bucky Barnes is believed killed in the explosion that left Steve Rogers frozen, a loss that haunts Cap for decades.', 'retcon', 1964, 1964, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('d9b43c9b-f808-5972-9e0e-7660f10bf25d', '58acfcfe-ce5b-573c-b8ad-fc8247c505d3', 'the-coming-of-the-falcon', 'The Coming of the Falcon', 'Steve Rogers forges a partnership with Sam Wilson, ushering in a landmark new era for the title.', 'Captain America meets Sam Wilson, a social worker from Harlem who becomes the Falcon, the first African-American superhero in mainstream comics. The two form one of the most enduring partnerships in Marvel history, and the book is even retitled Captain America and the Falcon for years.

Their partnership grounds Cap''s adventures in contemporary social issues, with stories that engage directly with the turmoil of the 1970s. Sam is no sidekick but a true equal and friend, and their dynamic gives the series fresh moral weight.

This era, shaped by writers like Stan Lee, Gary Friedrich, and later Steve Englehart, deepened Captain America''s role as a hero who questions authority and stands for the powerless.', NULL, 'flagship', 1969, 1972, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('2ed04474-2a58-5964-a4e9-00d76344e51c', '58acfcfe-ce5b-573c-b8ad-fc8247c505d3', 'secret-empire-watergate', 'The Secret Empire', 'Cap uncovers a vast conspiracy reaching the highest levels of government and questions what his uniform stands for.', 'In Steve Englehart''s landmark run, Captain America unravels a sprawling conspiracy orchestrated by the sinister Secret Empire, whose tendrils reach into the very top of the American government. Mirroring the real-world Watergate scandal, the story forces Cap to confront the possibility that the nation he serves has become corrupt.

Disillusioned by what he discovers, Steve Rogers abandons the Captain America identity and adopts the persona of Nomad, the man without a country. It is one of the most politically charged storylines of the Bronze Age and a defining statement on what Cap truly represents.

Ultimately, Rogers comes to understand that his loyalty is to the American ideal rather than to any administration or institution. This distinction has guided every great Captain America story since.', 'Disillusioned, Steve Rogers temporarily abandons the Captain America mantle to become the wandering hero Nomad.', 'flagship', 1974, 1974, 3, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('eca8b16c-99cb-5558-bba9-d2c82874697b', '26834a10-31bd-5791-aca1-92319fdc77b9', 'the-winter-soldier', 'The Winter Soldier', 'A ghost from Cap''s past returns as a brainwashed assassin, forcing Steve to confront a loss he never accepted.', 'Ed Brubaker''s defining run opens with the impossible: the return of Bucky Barnes, long believed dead, now reprogrammed by Soviet handlers into a deadly amnesiac assassin known as the Winter Soldier. Captain America, who has carried guilt over Bucky''s death for decades, must reckon with the man his partner has become.

Blending Cold War espionage with superhero drama, the arc is a taut, emotional thriller that uses the Cosmic Cube and shadowy intelligence agencies to weave a mystery decades in the making. It overturned one of comics'' oldest rules: that Bucky stays dead.

Widely regarded as one of the greatest Captain America stories ever told, The Winter Soldier reframed Cap''s mythology around loss, memory, and redemption. It became the basis for one of Marvel Studios'' most acclaimed films.', 'The Winter Soldier is revealed to be Bucky Barnes, who survived the war as a brainwashed Soviet assassin.', 'flagship', 2005, 2006, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('4441199a-0275-5599-8d20-1c280c1779fa', '26834a10-31bd-5791-aca1-92319fdc77b9', 'the-death-of-captain-america', 'The Death of Captain America', 'In the wake of a superhuman civil war, the nation reels from an unthinkable tragedy and a fight for Cap''s legacy begins.', 'Following the divisive events of the superhero Civil War, Captain America stands at the center of a fractured hero community. Brubaker''s saga becomes a sprawling political thriller exploring what the symbol of Captain America means when the man behind the shield is gone.

The story asks who is worthy to carry the mantle and the shield, drawing the Winter Soldier, the Falcon, and Cap''s longtime love Sharon Carter into a desperate struggle against the Red Skull''s machinations. It is murder mystery, conspiracy drama, and meditation on legacy all at once.

The arc earned widespread acclaim and mainstream news coverage, proving that Captain America''s relevance as a cultural symbol had never been stronger. It is essential reading for understanding the modern incarnation of the character.', 'Steve Rogers is assassinated on the courthouse steps, and Bucky Barnes takes up the shield as a new Captain America.', 'flagship', 2007, 2008, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('e58317e6-081f-56af-8eed-407a6869b2b4', '26834a10-31bd-5791-aca1-92319fdc77b9', 'the-man-who-bought-america', 'Castaway in Dimension Z and The Iron Nail', 'Rick Remender sends Cap on a harrowing journey across realities and back to confront an old genetic foe.', 'Rick Remender''s run launches with Captain America trapped in Dimension Z, a nightmarish alien world, where he is captured by the geneticist Arnim Zola. Stranded for years of subjective time, Steve is forced to raise a child and survive in a hostile realm built by his enemy''s twisted science.

The story strips Cap down to his essence: a survivor who refuses to surrender his principles no matter how impossible the circumstances. It is among the most ambitious science-fiction takes on the character, blending body horror, fatherhood, and pulse-pounding action.

Later chapters pit Cap against the Iron Nail and the consequences of his choices, testing his body and spirit to the breaking point. Remender''s saga is a bold, divisive, and deeply human reinvention of the Sentinel of Liberty.', NULL, 'flagship', 2013, 2014, 3, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('414e6e7c-2d89-5621-a519-3f17ecd996ce', 'a04902a0-9038-557b-a3e8-e63f2bad8539', 'winter-in-america', 'Winter in America', 'A diminished Steve Rogers fights to reclaim his good name and remind a wary public what his shield truly means.', 'Ta-Nehisi Coates and Leinil Yu open their run with a Captain America whose reputation has been shattered, leaving Steve Rogers distrusted by the very people he has sworn to protect. He must rebuild from the ground up, both as a hero and as a symbol.

The story is a thoughtful, melancholy meditation on patriotism, power, and faith in institutions during a fractured era. Cap confronts a network of enemies including Selene, the Taskmaster, and a resurgent threat manipulating the nation''s fears.

Coates brings a novelist''s eye to the character, interrogating what it means to embody a country that does not always live up to its ideals. It is a fitting modern bookend to the political legacy of the Secret Empire era.', NULL, 'flagship', 2018, 2019, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('14fc1398-31f6-562d-b2ee-6f19e5b59d4c', 'a04902a0-9038-557b-a3e8-e63f2bad8539', 'all-die-young', 'All Die Young', 'Framed and imprisoned, Captain America rallies allies for a final reckoning against a hidden mastermind.', 'As Coates''s saga builds to its climax, Steve Rogers finds himself accused of a crime he did not commit and thrown into the brutal Myrmidon prison. Behind the conspiracy lurks a cabal of powerful figures determined to twist the symbol of Captain America to their own ends.

With help from allies including Sharon Carter, the Falcon, and the Daughters of Liberty, Cap must escape, expose the truth, and prove once more that the man and the ideal are inseparable. The arc combines prison-break tension with sweeping political stakes.

The conclusion reaffirms the central thesis of the run: that Captain America belongs not to a government but to the people, and that the dream is worth fighting for even when the nation falters.', NULL, 'flagship', 2020, 2021, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('864a4e08-ea9d-5db3-b4b7-61470c234ccf', '8f850a65-9a28-5a40-a9f4-280b3a027347', 'cold-snap', 'Cold Snap', 'A small-time crook engineers a gun that can freeze the Fastest Man Alive.', 'Leonard Snart reasons that the only way to beat a man who moves at super-speed is to slow him down. He builds a cryonic weapon and adopts the identity of Captain Cold, instantly becoming one of the Flash''s most inventive foes.

Over the years Snart''s pragmatism and loyalty to his fellow Rogues elevate him from a gimmick villain to a compelling antihero. His code of conduct sets him apart from more murderous criminals.

Captain Cold remains the emotional and tactical center of the Rogues, a man as cold as his weapon but bound by his own rules.', NULL, 'origin', 1957, 1957, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('155f489f-dc14-558b-be21-be251f2680a1', 'ee56e7a0-4657-578a-a885-d9ad005b09d3', 'dante-chain-of-command', 'Chain of Command', 'A precinct captain must decide how far to bend the rules for his most unpredictable detective.', 'Captain Dante runs Sara''s homicide squad and faces mounting pressure from above as her cases produce results no one can rationally explain. Caught between protocol and loyalty, he repeatedly chooses to give Sara room to work.

Dante''s steady leadership provides Sara institutional cover and a measure of stability amid chaos. His arc explores the cost of trust when the truth cannot be put in a report.', NULL, 'flagship', 1995, 2000, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('f36da3a3-ea0c-5f76-bdd2-c654f463fcdf', '960d75a5-8ced-51fc-bb2a-b94eb3398635', 'catwoman-brubaker-cooke', 'Catwoman: Selina''s Big Score and Her Sister''s Keeper', 'Selina Kyle reinvents herself with a single enormous heist and then has to defend the neighborhood she made her own.', 'Darwyn Cooke''s Catwoman: Selina''s Big Score serves as the perfect prologue to Ed Brubaker''s ongoing run — a heist graphic novel in the purest sense, where the planning and execution are as satisfying as any action sequence. It establishes a new supporting cast and a Selina who is good at her job in ways that feel earned. Brubaker''s subsequent run deepened this foundation, particularly in the ''Her Sister''s Keeper'' arc which excavates Selina''s abusive past and the decisions that made her who she is.', NULL, 'flagship', 2001, 2002, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('631ca2a4-76bd-587f-b3f8-a8941bcb7acf', 'e7c023ab-47a4-5504-b694-213330761836', 'chapel-clean-kill', 'Clean Kill', 'A special-ops soldier wrestles with his violent calling on covert missions.', 'Chapel operates in the shadows of the team''s public heroics, taking on assignments others won''t. His arc grapples with guilt and redemption.

His grim professionalism contrasts sharply with the team''s celebrity sheen.', NULL, 'flagship', 1992, 1994, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('157846be-fc83-5a2f-8011-8c2e3e229ebf', 'c834c379-31f6-5a4c-b69e-ff36af909db8', 'cheetah-origin', 'The Cheetah''s Curse', 'An ambitious archaeologist gains the power of a predatory god at the cost of her humanity, becoming Wonder Woman''s deadliest rival.', 'Barbara Ann Minerva, an archaeologist obsessed with a tribal cult, undergoes a ritual that grants her immense power as the Cheetah but transforms her into a bloodthirsty beast. The cost of her ambition is her humanity and her friendship with Diana.

The modern Cheetah becomes a recurring threat whose envy of Diana fuels an obsessive rivalry. Greg Rucka''s Year One later deepens this tragedy by establishing Barbara as a genuine friend before her fall.

The arc cements Cheetah as the most personal antagonist in Wonder Woman''s rogues'' gallery.', NULL, 'origin', 1987, 1988, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('341638e1-8f5d-505f-9685-aff19439f09a', '585d1774-5022-5107-a953-a44fdc7c3da4', 'war-of-the-gods', 'War of the Gods', 'The sorceress Circe sets the pantheons of the world against one another in a scheme to annihilate the Amazons and their champion.', 'Circe engineers a cataclysmic conflict among the gods of various mythologies, drawing the heroes of the DC Universe into a war that threatens reality itself. Her ultimate target is the destruction of Wonder Woman and the Amazons.

The crossover showcases Circe''s intelligence and reach, positioning her as a strategist who weaponizes belief and divinity. Diana must rally allies across the universe to unravel the sorceress''s plot.

The arc cements Circe as a top-tier Wonder Woman villain whose threat extends far beyond Themyscira.', NULL, 'crossover', 1991, 1991, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('cbf18df8-5c13-5c12-9689-8f595b84efe0', 'bd4d2cfe-b757-5876-b981-9657c70a9dbb', 'the-old-hellspawn', 'The Old Hellspawn', 'A ragged stranger reveals himself as a Hellspawn who has survived where others fell.', 'Cogliostro approaches Spawn in his earliest, most confused days, offering guidance that is as cryptic as it is essential. He explains the limits of Spawn''s power and the trap of the bargain that binds him.

Though his motives are never fully clear, Cogliostro positions himself as one of the few who understands what Al is becoming. His ancient perspective frames the larger cosmology of the series.', NULL, 'origin', 1992, 1993, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('6d1e7b5a-1276-5084-943f-d36daec8c8f5', 'c190730a-3634-52d9-9491-096a0add4b90', 'no-mercy', 'No Mercy', 'An ancient Viltrumite enforcer arrives to crush Earth''s defiance without remorse.', 'Conquest descends upon Earth with the singular purpose of forcing its compliance, and his clash with Invincible becomes a test of pure endurance. His age and experience make him a nightmare opponent.

The confrontation marks one of the series'' most savage battles, with consequences that haunt Mark long afterward.', NULL, 'flagship', 2009, 2010, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('1bd574f7-f0d1-5f0e-8079-27f4302b14a6', 'ea54c796-8b00-5638-9dc1-9ff5b172882f', 'crossbones-assassin', 'The Trigger Man', 'The Red Skull''s enforcer is unleashed as the central weapon in a plot to destroy Captain America.', 'In Ed Brubaker''s modern run, Crossbones is positioned as the brutal executor of the Red Skull''s grand conspiracy, serving as the assassin at the heart of The Death of Captain America.

His savagery and lethal skill make him a constant physical danger, contrasting with the Skull''s cold strategy. Crossbones embodies the violent muscle behind the plot.', NULL, 'tie-in', 2007, 2008, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('7133f01b-0117-533f-ae0c-8ab0190b27c4', '5d9ac136-815b-5862-90e2-3e9a5921f4fa', 'no-witnesses', 'No Witnesses', 'A merciless hunter clashes with Erica over how monsters and witnesses should be handled.', 'Cutter believes in eliminating every loose end, monsters and humans alike, a philosophy that sets him directly against Erica''s protectiveness toward survivors. His arrival raises the stakes of the hunt.

His arc explores the moral extremes of the hunting world, presenting a figure whose effectiveness is matched only by his ruthlessness.', NULL, 'flagship', 2020, 2022, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('b06f0b0f-7b85-55d7-9137-70b1fe5c0134', '82734ac0-fcf9-5127-b434-e892c8ed27d0', 'cyberface-grasping-for-power', 'Grasping for Power', 'A scheming monster claws his way up the criminal ladder toward total domination.', 'Cyberface begins as a henchman but proves far more ambitious and dangerous than his station suggests. Over time he maneuvers, betrays, and seizes power, becoming a recurring tormentor of Dragon.

The arc traces his transformation into a top-tier threat whose schemes eventually endanger far more than Chicago.', NULL, 'flagship', 1993, 2000, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('2f08cdb6-52e2-5446-bfa5-92f0fcef5a1f', 'c87cf0b8-e1f8-5df6-bbaa-cad972b11826', 'cyborg-origin', 'The Making of Cyborg', 'A young athlete rebuilt as a machine must learn to live as something new.', 'After a lab accident leaves Victor Stone shattered, his father saves his life by replacing much of his body with cybernetics, leaving him alienated from the world he knew. Joining the New Teen Titans offers him a place to belong.

The arc grounds Cyborg''s powers in genuine pathos, exploring identity, disability and acceptance, and establishes him as one of DC''s most relatable heroes.', NULL, 'origin', 1980, 1981, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('ba28d1da-18ae-56a0-8f2f-8bcca6905030', '55c735da-1ff3-5cfc-bdae-b3c9df06dad2', 'cyclops-leader-of-the-x-men', 'Leader of the X-Men', 'A young mutant masters his dangerous power and grows into the team''s strategic heart.', 'Scott Summers struggles to control optic blasts he cannot switch off, channeling that burden into discipline and leadership. As field commander he guides the X-Men through their earliest and most defining battles.

His arc traces the evolution from anxious recruit to the steady hand that holds the team together.

It establishes Cyclops as the moral and tactical core of the franchise.', NULL, 'origin', 1963, 1980, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('bdd14e10-da4b-5bab-85c6-d6174ef3856c', '8aab893a-eeca-5db7-a26e-940cc07cfd81', 'danny-the-fallen-partner', 'The Fallen Partner', 'A detective''s death becomes the wound that drives his partner toward the Witchblade''s destiny.', 'Danny Estacado works alongside Sara before a violent case takes his life, an event that crystallizes Sara''s resolve and grief. His murder is among the formative tragedies that push her toward the path of the Witchblade.

Rather than vanishing from the story, Danny returns as a guiding spirit, appearing to Sara in moments of doubt. His arc transforms a fallen partner into a lasting conscience and companion.', 'Danny is killed early in the series and returns as a spirit.', 'origin', 1995, 1997, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('5c624f84-0540-58fc-8caa-51c313dd0e35', 'fb1db846-31b4-5ace-a012-dbae58b7f07b', 'the-fourth-world-saga', 'The Fourth World Saga', 'A god-tyrant hunts the Anti-Life Equation across Earth and the warring worlds of the New Gods.', 'Jack Kirby''s sprawling mythology pits the free people of New Genesis against the enslaved legions of Apokolips, ruled by the implacable Darkseid. His relentless search for the Anti-Life Equation brings his schemes to Earth.

The saga introduces a pantheon of new gods and a cosmic conflict of ideas as much as fists, with free will itself at stake. Darkseid emerges as a patient, terrifying mastermind rather than a brute.

The storyline''s grand scope and themes would echo through the DC Universe for generations, making Darkseid a top-tier threat to every hero. It frames him as a foundational cosmic villain.

Its ideas remain a touchstone for later creators tackling the New Gods and the menace of Apokolips.', NULL, 'origin', 1970, 1973, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('74fed4f8-6eaf-561a-b8ef-79fdc5bfa658', '7af31c76-9de5-502d-9ac5-60a9326b623a', 'darkthornn-invasion', 'Invasion', 'An alien warlord launches a campaign against Earth''s sanctioned heroes.', 'Darkthornn brings world-threatening warfare to the team''s doorstep, forcing them into a desperate defense. His campaign raises the franchise''s stakes dramatically.

He stands as a defining cosmic-scale antagonist for the away division.', NULL, 'flagship', 1993, 1994, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('b9757d81-be2c-5116-b21a-4d2ea981c41f', 'd505402b-2a6a-53a2-853c-1655c8ef2be2', 'deathstroke-judas-contract', 'The Judas Contract', 'A mercenary inherits a contract on the Titans and executes a years-in-the-making betrayal.', 'Deathstroke takes up the contract on the Teen Titans that his late son failed to complete, orchestrating an elaborate scheme to destroy them from within. The storyline reveals the depths of his cunning and the personal history that drives him.

It is the defining Deathstroke story, transforming him from a recurring foe into one of DC''s most respected villains and establishing the moral ambiguity that fans would come to love.', NULL, 'flagship', 1984, 1984, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('dcff3470-129e-565f-ad66-952219ebf010', 'e1c82c5a-feb6-54ea-b949-fcbfee8e3816', 'nightwing-year-one-arc', 'Nightwing: Year One', 'Dick Grayson leaves the Robin identity behind and forges a new heroic name between Batman''s disapproval and Superman''s encouragement.', 'Chuck Dixon and Scott Beatty''s 2005 story walks through the gap between Dick leaving Batman''s orbit and arriving in Blüdhaven as Nightwing, filling in how the name and costume came together and why Dick''s relationship with both his mentor and the wider hero community defines his emotional register differently from Bruce''s. It''s the cleanest single entry point for the Nightwing character as a standalone figure.', NULL, 'origin', 2005, 2005, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('20c073a3-330e-5581-b174-957d8100067f', '192ea2f5-9227-5c04-8f0e-4290c156a04d', 'diehard-long-war', 'The Long War', 'A veteran cyborg brings decades of combat experience to a team of upstarts.', 'Diehard serves as the seasoned counterweight to younger, flashier members. His arc reckons with what it means to keep fighting across generations.

He often voices the moral cost of the team''s sanctioned missions.', NULL, 'origin', 1992, 1994, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('b79920b3-bd3f-5cea-b85c-f52af0c4217b', '7cb32338-d937-5f08-8c90-0a10c45789fe', 'dixon-devoted', 'The Devoted', 'An ordinary man becomes the contagion''s willing instrument.', 'Dixon was nobody special before the Empty Man found him. After he embraced the presence, he became something else: a servant who does not question, only acts.

Throughout the outbreak he carries out the faith''s work, spreading the affliction and protecting its congregation. To the investigators he is a chilling reminder of how completely the Empty Man can hollow a person out.', NULL, 'flagship', 2014, 2015, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('6e7f113a-6e0d-5acf-aec6-242978c9408f', '073f752e-2505-51fc-8672-6821e8f23c5c', 'seismic-eruption', 'Fault Lines', 'A villain who can shake the earth itself sets his sights on catastrophe.', 'Doc Seismic harnesses seismic energy to terrorize and destroy, growing ever more grandiose in his schemes. His attacks threaten entire regions and force a coordinated heroic response.

His arc is one of escalating destruction, casting him as a recurring large-scale danger the Guardians must repeatedly stop.', NULL, 'flagship', 2005, 2010, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('f85d2ff3-45b4-55c9-8e3d-7f1720b9dd79', '60b3aad0-d144-5971-99b4-caa8f8528b1e', 'doc-ock-master-planner', 'The Sinister Mastermind', 'A scientist with four deadly arms schemes to bend the city''s underworld to his will.', 'Doctor Octopus first hands Spider-Man a humiliating defeat, becoming the rare villain to shake the hero''s confidence early in his career. He returns again and again as a criminal mastermind, eventually operating in secret as the Master Planner whose schemes threaten lives close to Peter.

These stories cement Otto Octavius as Spider-Man''s intellectual rival, a foe who wins with planning and ruthlessness rather than raw power, and lay the groundwork for his role as founder of the Sinister Six.', NULL, 'flagship', 1963, 1965, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('f631412f-ec54-5a56-b312-3b6e198066fb', '7a4fc7d5-663d-565f-8b3b-52a8398f68b6', 'doctor-poison-debut', 'The Poison Plot', 'A masked chemist unleashes a debilitating toxin on American soldiers, and Wonder Woman must unmask the saboteur behind it.', 'During the war years, the disguised Doctor Poison wages a campaign of sabotage using a chemical agent called Reverso that turns soldiers against their own side. Wonder Woman investigates the outbreak and tracks the toxin to its source.

The confrontation reveals the chemist''s true identity and establishes Doctor Poison as a recurring Golden Age menace. The villain later joins Villainy Incorporated, the alliance of Diana''s deadliest early foes.

The arc grounds Doctor Poison as one of Wonder Woman''s longest-running adversaries.', NULL, 'flagship', 1942, 1942, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('a78c5367-9184-582e-8b56-460476835ad7', '41431853-9e88-5445-998f-61ef7f4bf85d', 'the-death-of-superman-doomsday', 'Doomsday''s Rampage', 'An unknown creature breaks free and carves a trail of devastation across America on a collision course with Superman.', 'Doomsday debuts with no dialogue and no motive beyond destruction, smashing through everything in its path. The Justice League cannot slow it, leaving Superman as the world''s last line of defense in a brutal, escalating brawl.

The confrontation builds to a catastrophic finish in the heart of Metropolis, where monster and hero finally meet head-on. The story made Doomsday an instant legend as the foe that did the impossible.', 'Doomsday and Superman kill each other simultaneously in their climactic battle.', 'crossover', 1992, 1993, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('81674b97-e5dd-599a-84dc-0764437d9aaa', '2088a8ee-1770-52e9-829d-286ec64cc4aa', 'drusilla-arrives', 'Visions of Ruin', 'A mad vampire''s prophecies guide her toward the Slayer she means to destroy.', 'Drusilla drifts into Sunnydale guided by visions only she can see, leaving wreckage in her wake. Her madness makes her impossible to predict and dangerous to confront.

She weaves through the lives of the gang''s enemies, her loyalties as unstable as her mind. Drusilla''s arc adds a current of dreamlike dread to the relaunch''s roster of villains.', NULL, 'miniseries', 2019, 2021, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('5011d157-f314-5b94-97d3-4eb667e7ec1c', 'a2c92628-e470-5488-b631-eab98c188154', 'kate-duplicates', 'Many Hands', 'One hero becomes an army when the odds demand it.', 'Dupli-Kate''s power to duplicate herself makes her uniquely flexible, able to cover ground and overwhelm foes that would outmatch a lone fighter. She becomes a reliable presence in the reformed Guardians.

Her arc highlights teamwork and adaptability, as she learns to deploy her copies with increasing tactical skill.', NULL, 'flagship', 2005, 2009, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('4b4df4c9-1c34-5a0a-9e08-b85b8ca02966', 'fa6bb8db-0f6a-56d8-a2e0-7c93cce008d4', 'the-butchers-throne', 'The Butcher''s Throne', 'A powerful elder of the Slaughter line tightens his grip on the house and its hunters.', 'Edwin commands respect and fear within the House of Slaughter, using his standing to shape the order''s direction. His ambitions place him at odds with hunters who chafe under the institution''s control.

His arc reveals the internal power struggles of the Slaughter family, presenting a morally grey leader whose decisions ripple outward to hunters like Erica.', NULL, 'miniseries', 2021, 2023, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('7696a454-d1e2-50f0-84d7-65da596ab8f5', '21f8274d-024d-5b2e-98e0-be0bdb4ac32d', 'an-unkindness-of-monsters', 'An Unkindness of Monsters', 'A masked stranger comes to a grieving town to hunt the thing that is killing its children.', 'After a group of teenagers is attacked in the woods outside Archer''s Peak, the lone survivor insists a monster did it—and no adult believes him. Into this fear-soaked town walks Erica Slaughter, a young woman in a white bandana who carries a machete and speaks plainly about the creatures she has come to kill.

Erica''s methods are blunt and bloody, and she has little patience for the platitudes of grief counselors or the suspicion of local police. As the body count rises, she takes the survivor under her wing, both to keep him alive and because he can do something most people cannot: he can see the monster.

The arc establishes the central premise of the series—that some children are devoured by things adults refuse to acknowledge—and introduces Erica as a hunter who is as haunted as she is lethal. It is a story about belief, complicity, and the cost of staring directly at what others look away from.', NULL, 'origin', 2019, 2020, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('1e6d70e2-cdaf-550a-a6d1-3d8b221fd372', '21f8274d-024d-5b2e-98e0-be0bdb4ac32d', 'the-order-arrives', 'The Order Arrives', 'As the hunt escalates, the organization that governs monster hunters descends on the town with its own agenda.', 'With the monster of Archer''s Peak still loose, Erica''s freewheeling approach draws the attention of the House of Slaughter and the wider Order of St. George. Handlers and operatives arrive, and it becomes clear that Erica has been operating outside the strict protocols meant to govern hunters like her.

The conflict is no longer only between Erica and the creature; it is between Erica and the institution that raised her. The Order cares about secrecy and containment as much as it cares about saving lives, and Erica''s willingness to involve a civilian witness puts her at odds with everything she was trained to be.

This arc deepens the mythology of the world, showing that the monsters are an open secret managed by a hidden bureaucracy, and that Erica''s defiance has consequences that will follow her long after she leaves Archer''s Peak behind.', NULL, 'flagship', 2020, 2021, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('c4387fdb-9a0f-50a9-a514-c9539c87c436', '87bf7f7d-9ee7-50ae-83bf-bad9d6d4f01b', 'the-reckoning', 'The Reckoning', 'A new town and a new monster drag Erica back into the politics of the people who trained her.', 'Moving on from Archer''s Peak, Erica takes a fresh contract that quickly proves more complicated than a simple kill. The monster she is hunting is bound up with the interests of the House of Slaughter, and her old handlers have not forgotten her insubordination.

Away from any safety net, Erica must rely on instinct and the few allies she trusts. The arc juxtaposes the immediate horror of the hunt with the slower dread of an organization closing in around her, testing whether she can survive both the creature and the consequences of her choices.

It is a turning point that reframes Erica from a wandering exterminator into a fugitive of sorts—someone whose greatest threat may be the very institution that gave her a purpose.', NULL, 'flagship', 2021, 2022, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('5e6db018-af74-5592-a48a-773d495d469b', '87bf7f7d-9ee7-50ae-83bf-bad9d6d4f01b', 'blood-and-bandanas', 'Blood and Bandanas', 'Erica''s history with the House of Slaughter resurfaces, forcing her to confront the family she left behind.', 'As Erica''s path winds through new hunts, the people and places of her upbringing return to the foreground. The bandanas that mark a hunter''s status carry meaning she can no longer ignore, and the relationships she severed demand to be settled.

The arc weaves present-day monster hunting with the weight of Erica''s formation inside a secretive lineage of killers. Old loyalties and old grudges collide as she discovers how much of her freedom is an illusion and how deeply the Order''s reach extends.

It is a more personal chapter, trading some of the pure horror of earlier stories for the dread of family, obligation, and the question of whether a person shaped to be a weapon can ever simply walk away.', NULL, 'flagship', 2022, 2024, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('4d3e4595-f8c1-5664-af45-0f4129f53ca0', 'e4f55ccf-3eda-57c5-93d9-915342e9515b', 'frank-darling-recruitment', 'Recruitment', 'A veteran cop takes a chance on an amnesiac stranger with incredible powers.', 'Frank Darling sees potential where others see a dangerous unknown, recruiting Dragon into the Chicago Police Department and vouching for him internally. His mentorship gives the rudderless Dragon a foothold in a new life.

The arc frames Frank as a moral compass and institutional ally whose support shapes Dragon''s earliest decisions.', NULL, 'origin', 1992, 1994, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('96c2b072-50fb-5d8b-8b34-ba3beba78f61', 'a39dd2f2-e166-5791-a1c2-75f2ddf2bf92', 'new-krypton', 'New Krypton', 'When 100,000 Kryptonians are freed from the bottle city of Kandor, General Zod rises to lead them, and Superman must choose between two worlds.', 'The restoration of Kandor unleashes a vast Kryptonian population onto Earth, who build a new homeworld and place the militant Zod in command of their military. Superman is torn between his adopted planet and the surviving culture of his birth.

The sprawling saga pits Zod''s vision of Kryptonian supremacy against Superman''s hard-won humanity, escalating toward open war. It is the defining modern showcase for Zod as a leader rather than a mere brute.', NULL, 'crossover', 2008, 2010, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('9b698983-7263-5bf2-9fc8-c6f4d660f6f2', '70b8d815-bb04-5401-bf03-c678e3695265', 'giga-rising', 'Rising', 'A towering menace forces the team to unite both divisions to survive.', 'Giga''s appearance turns a routine mission into a desperate containment effort. The creature''s scale pushes the team beyond its usual tactics.

The confrontation becomes a showcase of full-roster cooperation.', NULL, 'flagship', 1992, 1993, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('81025045-d597-56ff-b555-081a540912f0', 'c07bbd17-0487-5a43-908e-cb1f9b8fcfd3', 'gleason-cold-evidence', 'Cold Evidence', 'A forensic examiner confronts physical proof that the impossible is real.', 'Gleason is called upon to make sense of evidence that no ordinary crime scene could produce. His methodical, science-driven approach repeatedly collides with the supernatural forces surrounding the Witchblade.

Though skeptical by training, Gleason becomes a steadfast ally, lending Sara credibility and analytical support. His arc grounds the series'' fantastical elements in the rigor of real investigation.', NULL, 'miniseries', 1996, 1999, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('bdb97666-9c32-5795-8532-f7db2a634206', '505f750f-1ce9-5c0d-b5dc-89c120206096', 'warriors-fury', 'Warrior''s Fury', 'A relentless enforcer hunts the Rangers wherever they stand.', 'Goldar throws himself into battle against the Rangers with overwhelming ferocity, serving as the sword arm of greater villains. His persistence makes him a recurring physical menace.

The arc emphasizes Goldar''s role as the loyal, dangerous enforcer who keeps the heroes on the back foot.', NULL, 'tie-in', 2016, 2017, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('a45f0da9-3657-5814-b0b1-db049934f686', '70b35479-2fcf-5fa7-9dfa-53a29c7736b8', 'menace-of-the-super-gorilla', 'Menace of the Super-Gorilla', 'A telepathic ape from a hidden city sets out to conquer humanity and destroy the Flash.', 'Grodd is exiled from the secret Gorilla City after attempting to seize its power, and he sets his sights on the human world. Using his formidable telepathy, he bends minds to his will and clashes with the Flash, who alone can move fast enough to resist him.

These early stories introduced one of the strangest and most enduring elements of the Flash mythos: a society of intelligent gorillas hidden from the world. Grodd''s blend of brute force and cunning intellect made him an instant standout.

Grodd has returned again and again across the decades, always seeking the conquest that the Flash repeatedly denies him.', NULL, 'origin', 1959, 1959, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('7c819388-6183-58d8-aa22-a54b313fc016', 'a38b2a9d-4ddc-5fd2-8be7-80d361b67a1e', 'the-longbow-hunters', 'Green Arrow: The Longbow Hunters', 'An aging Oliver Queen takes a darker, more personal turn against urban crime.', 'Mike Grell''s landmark story strips Green Arrow down to a grounded, human level, trading gimmicks for grit. Oliver confronts mortality, violence, and the moral cost of his crusade.

The arc reinvents the character for mature readers, emphasizing his role as a street-level hero distinct from the League''s cosmic icons. It deepens his relationship with Black Canary.

The darker tone and personal stakes redefined the character for a generation. It established the template for modern Green Arrow.

The story remains a defining work and a key entry point for the character.', NULL, 'miniseries', 1987, 1987, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('998e0f67-2589-571d-b0a9-5bcce8b72658', '835f39cb-c493-50ce-b441-67369976a3a8', 'gg-goblin-reborn', 'The Goblin''s Reign of Terror', 'A masked madman makes it his obsession to unmask and destroy Spider-Man.', 'The Green Goblin debuts as a flamboyant new menace determined to make his name by defeating Spider-Man, eventually deducing the hero''s secret identity and revealing his own as businessman Norman Osborn. Their cat-and-mouse war escalates as the Goblin''s instability deepens.

The rivalry reaches its devastating peak when Osborn targets the people Peter loves most, an act of cruelty that defines the Goblin as the cruelest figure in Spider-Man''s life. These stories establish the template for the personal supervillain who attacks a hero''s civilian world.', NULL, 'flagship', 1966, 1973, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('1474aa88-d763-5607-ba45-25e22acbef57', '37137a6b-3371-5c1d-88b1-4847b96c9392', 'the-power-ring-of-abin-sur', 'The Power Ring of Abin Sur', 'A dying alien''s ring seeks out the most fearless human on Earth.', 'When the Green Lantern Abin Sur crash-lands on Earth, his power ring scans the planet for a worthy successor and selects Hal Jordan, a test pilot at Ferris Aircraft whose nerve has made him a legend among his peers. Abin Sur passes on the ring and the lantern battery before he dies, and Hal must learn the rules of a weapon limited only by his own willpower and imagination.

The debut establishes the core mythology: the emerald energy, the recharge oath, and the looming presence of the Guardians of the Universe on the planet Oa. Hal balances a secret double life with his romance with his boss, Carol Ferris, who is both his employer and the object of his affection.

These opening Showcase stories defined the Silver Age template, fusing aviation adventure with cosmic science fiction. They set Hal apart from his Golden Age predecessor Alan Scott and reframed Green Lantern as a member of a galaxy-spanning police force rather than a lone mystic.', NULL, 'origin', 1959, 1960, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('8fce8362-0b90-5505-bed8-32daccdba7d5', '37137a6b-3371-5c1d-88b1-4847b96c9392', 'the-shark-and-the-mind-monster', 'Rise of the Mind-Monsters', 'A telepath and an evolved predator test whether a power ring can fight what it cannot punch.', 'As Hal settles into his role, his rogues'' gallery takes shape. A criminal named Hector Hammond is exposed to a meteor that vaults him millions of years up the evolutionary ladder, leaving him immobile but armed with staggering psychic power and an immortal, hungry mind. He becomes obsessed with Hal''s ring and with Carol Ferris.

Hal also confronts the Shark, an evolved tiger shark transformed into a humanoid predator who feeds on fear, and learns that willpower must be precise as well as strong. These stories push Green Lantern beyond simple slugfests into battles of intellect and nerve.

The era cements the central theme that would define the character for decades: the ring is only as strong as the will and courage of the man wearing it, and his deadliest foes attack that resolve directly.', NULL, 'flagship', 1961, 1964, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('943926ee-6c8c-5b12-9a0e-dbd65abc5a84', '37137a6b-3371-5c1d-88b1-4847b96c9392', 'the-fall-of-sinestro', 'The Fall of Sinestro', 'The greatest Green Lantern who ever lived becomes Hal''s deadliest mirror.', 'The Guardians reveal that Sinestro of Korugar was once a celebrated Green Lantern, the finest of the Corps, until his desire for order curdled into tyranny over his own homeworld. Stripped of his ring and banished to the antimatter universe of Qward, he returns wielding a yellow power ring fueled by fear, the one weakness built into the emerald energy.

Hal faces an opponent who knows every trick of the ring because he helped write the book on it. Their clashes elevate Sinestro into Green Lantern''s archenemy, a dark reflection of everything Hal could become if discipline turned to domination.

This introduction lays the groundwork for the fear-versus-will mythology that later writers would expand into the emotional spectrum, making Sinestro one of the most important villains in DC''s cosmic canon.', NULL, 'flagship', 1961, 1965, 3, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('6a7ddaa7-d3d9-5357-9f2c-1191120ef874', 'e05ed2e0-f320-54b9-a3e0-230168923841', 'hard-traveling-heroes', 'Hard-Traveling Heroes', 'A cosmic cop and a street-level radical cross America asking who the law really serves.', 'Denny O''Neil and Neal Adams team Hal Jordan with the leftist archer Green Arrow for a journey across a divided United States. Confronted by a Black man who asks why he protects orange and purple aliens but ignores suffering at home, Hal is forced to question the unblinking loyalty he has given the Guardians.

The pair, sometimes accompanied by a Guardian who walks among humans, tackle racism, pollution, political corruption, and addiction in stories that brought relevance crashing into superhero comics. The friction between Hal''s by-the-book idealism and Oliver Queen''s furious populism gives the run its electric charge.

Widely regarded as one of the most influential runs in comics history, Hard-Traveling Heroes redefined what mainstream superhero storytelling could address and permanently deepened Hal Jordan as a man wrestling with his own certainties.', NULL, 'flagship', 1970, 1972, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('7543de07-0a15-5834-b378-25cec31889a8', 'e05ed2e0-f320-54b9-a3e0-230168923841', 'the-cost-of-the-oath', 'The Cost of the Oath', 'Saving worlds keeps costing Hal everything he loves at home.', 'Following the relevance era, Hal struggles to reconcile his duty to Sector 2814 with his life on Earth. He drifts between jobs and abandons, then resumes, his role as a Green Lantern, repeatedly forced to choose between Carol Ferris and the demands of the ring.

Stories pit him against returning foes and new cosmic threats while emphasizing the personal toll of being a guardian of an entire space sector. The Guardians'' inscrutable policies and occasional cruelty drive a wedge between Hal and the masters he once trusted without question.

This stretch sets up the disillusionment that later writers would mine, portraying a hero whose greatness is inseparable from sacrifice and whose loyalty to the Corps is increasingly tested.', NULL, 'flagship', 1976, 1985, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('1f5f0ec6-5a4b-55ad-b5a2-73880add126d', 'dd437ead-8c7d-536b-8c21-b2dda5ec4183', 'emerald-twilight', 'Emerald Twilight', 'Grief drives the greatest Green Lantern to tear the Corps apart from within.', 'After the destruction of his hometown of Coast City, a shattered Hal Jordan uses his ring to recreate the dead, defying the Guardians'' edicts. When they move to stop him, his grief and a creeping corruption push him into open war against the Corps itself, as he battles ringbearer after ringbearer on the long road to Oa.

Hal seizes the central power battery, and a new figure of immense menace is born from his fall. The Guardians, desperate, forge a single last ring and send it to Earth, where it finds a young artist named Kyle Rayner who must carry the legacy forward.

A controversial but pivotal story, Emerald Twilight removed Hal from the role for years and reframed him as a fallen hero, setting up nearly a decade of stories about the cost of his collapse.', 'Hal Jordan is corrupted and becomes the villain Parallax after destroying the Corps and killing fellow Lanterns; Kyle Rayner becomes the new Green Lantern.', 'flagship', 1994, 1994, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('4bd790e4-7778-596c-9693-a24ff4f1ec76', 'dd437ead-8c7d-536b-8c21-b2dda5ec4183', 'green-lantern-rebirth', 'Green Lantern: Rebirth', 'The truth behind Hal''s fall could redeem the greatest Lantern of them all.', 'Geoff Johns and Ethan Van Sciver reveal that Hal''s corruption was not simple weakness but the work of Parallax, an ancient cosmic entity of fear that had nested inside the Green Lantern central battery and exploited his grief. With this revelation, the path opens for Hal''s redemption and return.

Reunited with allies including Green Arrow, the Justice League, and his fellow Earth Lanterns, Hal battles to reclaim his soul and his ring while confronting the parasite that ruined him. The story restores his heroism without erasing his guilt, threading the needle of a redemption decades of fans had wanted.

Rebirth relaunched Green Lantern as a tentpole franchise and laid the conceptual foundation, the fear entity and the will-versus-fear dynamic, for the cosmic epics that followed.', 'Hal Jordan is restored as Green Lantern; Parallax is revealed to be a fear entity that had possessed him.', 'retcon', 2004, 2005, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('66acb8b9-5f3f-5e92-ad9c-c8663edea4e9', 'dd437ead-8c7d-536b-8c21-b2dda5ec4183', 'the-sinestro-corps-war', 'The Sinestro Corps War', 'Sinestro builds an army of fear to break the Green Lantern Corps forever.', 'Sinestro unites the universe''s most terrifying beings into the Sinestro Corps, arming them with yellow rings powered by fear, and launches an all-out assault on Oa. Allied with the resurrected Parallax, the Anti-Monitor, and a corrupted Superman from another reality, his forces aim to annihilate the Green Lantern Corps and remake the cosmos under fear''s rule.

Hal Jordan, Kyle Rayner, John Stewart, Guy Gardner, and the entire Corps wage a war that spills from deep space to the streets of Earth. The Guardians are forced to rewrite their own ancient laws, sanctioning lethal force for the first time, a decision with consequences that ripple for years.

The Sinestro Corps War is regarded as one of the definitive Green Lantern epics and the springboard for Blackest Night, expanding the mythology into a full emotional spectrum of colored Corps.', NULL, 'crossover', 2007, 2008, 3, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('54b2988e-9852-541b-b964-5b884323b29e', 'dd437ead-8c7d-536b-8c21-b2dda5ec4183', 'blackest-night', 'Blackest Night', 'Death itself rises to extinguish every light in the universe.', 'The prophesied Blackest Night arrives as the entity Nekron raises the dead across the cosmos, fitting fallen heroes and villains with black rings that turn them into Black Lanterns hungry for the living. The full emotional spectrum, will, fear, rage, avarice, hope, compassion, and love, must unite to stop the tide.

Hal Jordan stands at the center of an unprecedented alliance of seven Corps, leading Lanterns of every color against an enemy that feeds on emotion and death. Old friends return in horrifying form, and the cost of every loss in Hal''s history comes back to haunt him.

Blackest Night was a line-wide event that paid off years of Geoff Johns'' world-building, cementing Hal as a unifying leader and the emotional spectrum as a permanent fixture of DC''s cosmos.', NULL, 'crossover', 2009, 2010, 4, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('19a2b15b-477e-5464-9f03-97432e52b00f', 'b68e5eff-14b0-5e83-ab64-c1de3b3ca307', 'global-protectors', 'Global Protectors', 'Earth''s most trusted superhero team stands as the public face of heroism.', 'The original Guardians of the Globe operate as the world''s sanctioned line of defense, a coalition of powerful individuals whose reputations precede them. From their orbital and ground headquarters they coordinate responses to alien incursions, super-criminal rampages, and disasters too large for any single hero.

The roster blends raw power with experience: an ancient warrior, a powered-armor genius, a flying powerhouse, and others whose names are household words. To the public they are a reassuring constant, the team that always shows up when the situation is dire.

This arc establishes the team''s place in the world and the trust ordinary people place in them, setting a baseline of stability that later events will violently overturn.', NULL, 'origin', 2004, 2004, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('59ac8452-ac46-5f18-8baa-043b7aff6177', 'b68e5eff-14b0-5e83-ab64-c1de3b3ca307', 'fall-of-the-guardians', 'The Fall of the Guardians', 'A single betrayal shatters the team the world believed could never be beaten.', 'The era of the original Guardians comes to a sudden and brutal end. What seemed like an unshakable institution is revealed to be terribly vulnerable, and the consequences ripple outward across the entire superhero community.

The aftermath leaves the world without its primary defenders and forces difficult questions about who can be trusted with such power. Allies grieve, investigations begin, and the vacuum left behind demands to be filled.

This arc marks the turning point between the team''s first incarnation and everything that follows, redefining the stakes of the series.', 'Most of the original Guardians of the Globe are killed by the Omni-Man, who reveals his true allegiance.', 'flagship', 2004, 2005, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('e3f0197b-3400-5224-a292-daa7af15e750', 'ad304ef8-9c80-55a6-8461-4e8fabe0e046', 'rebuilding-the-team', 'Rebuilding the Team', 'A new generation steps up to wear a legendary name they didn''t ask for.', 'With the original team gone, a new Guardians of the Globe is assembled from emerging talents and a few survivors. The recruits are younger, less polished, and acutely aware that they are standing in enormous shadows.

Leadership falls to those willing to shoulder it, and the team must learn to function under pressure while the public watches skeptically. Personalities clash, trust is earned slowly, and every mission doubles as a test of whether the name still means anything.

This arc follows the messy, human process of forging a team out of strangers and grief, laying the groundwork for the modern Guardians.', NULL, 'flagship', 2005, 2007, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('995b4bfd-5d7c-57dc-b2d4-a4907c774c79', 'ad304ef8-9c80-55a6-8461-4e8fabe0e046', 'guarding-the-globe', 'Guarding the Globe', 'The expanded team takes on planet-scale threats as a true global institution.', 'The reformed Guardians grow into a sprawling, well-resourced organization with international reach. New members are recruited, satellite operations are established, and the team begins to function as a genuine worldwide peacekeeping force.

The expanded roster faces escalating dangers, from organized super-crime to existential threats, and the leadership must balance ambition against the cost of stretching themselves thin. Triumphs are real, but so are losses.

This arc cements the new Guardians as worthy successors, carrying the legacy forward while defining their own identity.', NULL, 'flagship', 2010, 2013, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('283ef007-6e28-59b0-9a98-289584395d65', 'b6d17726-af91-5b3f-8399-38a731a48e94', 'hawkeye-my-life-as-a-weapon', 'My Life as a Weapon', 'Between missions, Hawkeye discovers that his days off are even more dangerous than the job.', 'Away from the world-saving spectacle of the Avengers, Clint Barton tries to live an ordinary life in his Brooklyn apartment building, looking out for his neighbors against a gang of tracksuit-wearing criminals. Alongside Kate Bishop, he gets pulled into trouble at every turn.

Writer Matt Fraction and artist David Aja deliver a stylish, grounded, and frequently funny take on the character that became a critical sensation. The series strips away the cosmic stakes to focus on a hero who is, fundamentally, just a guy with a bow.

The arc redefined Hawkeye for a generation, blending crime drama, comedy, and inventive page design. It is one of the most acclaimed Marvel runs of its decade.

''My Life as a Weapon'' is the perfect entry point for readers who want character-driven, accessible storytelling.', NULL, 'flagship', 2012, 2013, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('63549718-de21-561e-b571-062519e6c522', '482fb528-9f1a-5496-a07c-80ddf9206286', 'the-immortal-mind', 'The Immortal Mind', 'A small-time crook evolves into a deathless brain that hungers for power.', 'Hector Hammond is exposed to a strange meteor that vaults him millions of years up the evolutionary scale, leaving him with a grotesquely enlarged head, telepathic and telekinetic power, and effective immortality, but robbing him of the ability to move.

Obsessed with Hal Jordan''s ring and with Carol Ferris, Hammond becomes a recurring menace whose battles are fought in the mind. He embodies the Silver Age theme that a power ring is useless without the will to wield it.', NULL, 'origin', 1960, 1964, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('13f3cdf5-8701-57a0-b343-4615ec231de7', '9c6211c1-3d0c-5702-9132-70d009941eba', 'hela-the-curse-of-hela', 'The Curse of Hela', 'Hela curses Thor with brittle bones and unbreakable life to rob him of an honorable death.', 'When Hela seeks to claim Thor''s soul, the Thunder God resists, and the death goddess retaliates with a cruel curse: making his bones brittle as glass while denying him the release of death itself.

Forced to fight on as a fragile, encased warrior, Thor must find a way to break the curse and confront the queen of the dead in her own domain. The arc is a showcase for Hela''s chilling cruelty.

It remains one of the defining Hela stories, illustrating how her power over death makes her uniquely terrifying among Thor''s foes.', NULL, 'flagship', 1984, 1985, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('420f8772-3694-5e2f-9e19-399bef5fc0fb', '139e5521-a8ac-51ef-b954-6881c35c1ec3', 'the-butchers-mark', 'The Butcher''s Mark', 'A young Aaron Slaughter and Erica come of age inside the House''s merciless training program.', 'The opening arc of House of Slaughter divides its attention between past and present, following Aaron Slaughter as both a manipulative present-day operative and a vulnerable child being shaped by the order. Through flashbacks the reader learns how the House recruits, brands, and bonds its hunters to the white mask.

The story foregrounds the relationship between Aaron and Erica, two children raised under the same brutal roof who take very different paths. Loyalty, jealousy, and the desire for belonging drive their choices long before either becomes a fully fledged hunter.

The arc grounds the institution introduced in ''Something is Killing the Children,'' showing that the monsters outside are matched by the politics within. It establishes the masks as a system of control as much as protection.', NULL, 'origin', 2021, 2022, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('83ffde42-e1ea-53a5-a403-950c37194265', '139e5521-a8ac-51ef-b954-6881c35c1ec3', 'the-veil-of-masks', 'The Veil of Masks', 'The meaning of the colored masks and the chain of command that binds every hunter is laid bare.', 'This arc deepens the mythology of the order by examining the system of masks, white, red, and beyond, that defines a hunter''s role and rank. Each color carries duties, privileges, and dangers, and the politics of advancement prove ruthless.

The narrative explores how loyalty to the House is tested and enforced, and how those who question the old ways are quietly disciplined. The institution''s appetite for secrecy becomes a theme in its own right.

By widening the lens beyond a single hunter, the arc transforms the House from a backdrop into a living antagonist-and-protector, capable of nurturing and devouring its own.', NULL, 'flagship', 2021, 2022, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('004cd217-71de-5640-a54d-60467c79c6c5', 'baa4c39e-195a-540f-a9db-466a55533fc6', 'the-boucher-line', 'The Boucher Line', 'A devoted hunter is forced to choose between the House''s commands and the people he is sworn to protect.', 'This arc shifts focus to the wider roster of the House, dramatizing how a single order from above can shatter a hunter''s certainty. The protagonist''s faith in the institution is tested by a mission whose true purpose is hidden from him.

The story examines duty as both a virtue and a trap, asking whether a hunter who obeys without question is truly protecting anyone. Personal bonds collide with institutional demands.

In doing so the arc sets up the broader cracks that run through the House, foreshadowing a reckoning between those who serve the masks and those who would reform or destroy them.', NULL, 'flagship', 2022, 2023, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('cdf64ee1-8b06-5842-901e-3ca8ebc76a27', 'baa4c39e-195a-540f-a9db-466a55533fc6', 'blood-and-tradition', 'Blood and Tradition', 'Buried secrets of the founding families surface and threaten to unmake the order from within.', 'The later chapters of the House saga turn to the founding bloodlines and the compromises on which the order was built. As long-hidden truths emerge, hunters must decide whether tradition deserves their loyalty.

The narrative weaves together several members of the roster, contrasting those who cling to the old ways with those willing to break them. The House''s monsters of the past prove harder to bury than any creature in the field.

The arc functions as a turning point, escalating the simmering tensions into direct conflict and reframing the House not as a monolith but as a fractured family at war with itself.', NULL, 'miniseries', 2023, 2024, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('847f71b9-c137-5dc6-8836-926252b4e20a', '7b601c19-a699-585b-8411-6ff44abfc4b3', 'planet-hulk', 'Planet Hulk', 'Exiled from Earth, the Hulk becomes a gladiator and then a king on an alien world.', 'After being shot into space by a cabal of heroes who deem him too dangerous, the Hulk crash-lands on the savage planet Sakaar. Forced into gladiatorial combat, he slowly rises from slave to champion to liberator.

Writer Greg Pak reinvents the character by giving him a world to call his own and a community that respects rather than fears him. The story is an epic of rebellion, loyalty, and hard-won peace.

''Planet Hulk'' is celebrated as one of the greatest Hulk stories ever told, expanding the character far beyond his usual role. It set the stage for major events to follow.

The arc is a perfect entry point for readers who want to see the Hulk as a tragic hero rather than a mindless monster.', NULL, 'flagship', 2006, 2007, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('3e824301-2d40-50e7-9e35-acfd0b54a8f9', '1398a463-f1d2-5f83-8d7f-fc0cacd06578', 'nottingham-divided-loyalty', 'Divided Loyalty', 'A master''s perfect weapon begins to question the hand that wields him.', 'Ian Nottingham is Kenneth Irons'' ultimate enforcer, a warrior shaped to serve without hesitation. Yet from his first encounters with Sara Pezzini, a deeper fascination takes root that his master cannot fully command.

Torn between obedience and his own conscience, Nottingham becomes one of the most unpredictable figures in Sara''s world. His arc traces the slow fracture of his loyalty and the emergence of his own will.', NULL, 'flagship', 1996, 2001, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('4337f2e5-2e0d-5a7f-80e5-a74ebebf8049', '70a8ff9f-0a29-5bf0-bbc7-5d7619355dd7', 'family-matters', 'Family Matters', 'A high schooler finally develops the superpowers he always expected to inherit and steps into the family business.', 'Mark Grayson has spent his whole life waiting for the day his Viltrumite heritage would manifest, and when his powers finally arrive he wastes no time adopting the costumed identity of Invincible. Balancing homework, a part-time job, and the demands of crime-fighting, Mark discovers that being a hero is far less glamorous and far more dangerous than he imagined.

Guided by his father, the legendary Omni-Man, Mark begins to test the limits of his strength, speed, and durability against a rogues'' gallery of escalating threats. The early adventures establish the grounded, character-driven tone that defines the series, balancing teenage awkwardness with genuine peril.

Beneath the lighthearted surface, the seeds of a much larger story are planted, hinting that not everything about Mark''s family is as wholesome as it appears.', NULL, 'origin', 2003, 2004, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('5bb56784-65b1-5204-8e6b-dabc8832009d', '70a8ff9f-0a29-5bf0-bbc7-5d7619355dd7', 'eight-is-enough', 'Eight Is Enough', 'A devastating truth about the hero''s father reframes everything Invincible thought he knew.', 'As Mark settles into his role, he joins forces with other young heroes and begins to build a life that feels like his own. But a brutal confrontation forces a long-buried secret into the open, shattering the comfortable world he had taken for granted.

The arc pivots the entire series, transforming what looked like a cheerful coming-of-age tale into something far more complex and emotionally charged. Mark must grapple with questions of loyalty, identity, and what it truly means to carry his family''s legacy.

The fallout from these revelations sets the stage for years of storytelling, redefining Invincible''s relationships with everyone around him.', 'Omni-Man reveals he is a Viltrumite advance agent sent to conquer Earth and nearly beats Mark to death.', 'flagship', 2004, 2005, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('9ff9e389-3bb1-5ebe-b9c1-dab7d3da9dd1', 'f69ed675-ce96-56ff-b7bc-51f310d9ed24', 'the-conquest', 'The Conquest', 'An unstoppable Viltrumite enforcer arrives on Earth to test Invincible to his absolute limit.', 'The Viltrumite Empire dispatches one of its most ruthless agents to deal with Earth''s growing defiance, and Invincible finds himself outmatched in the most brutal fight of his life. The conflict pushes Mark past every physical and emotional boundary he has known.

This confrontation marks a turning point in the series'' stakes, proving that Mark''s enemies are willing to inflict unthinkable damage to break his spirit. The cost of survival is measured not just in injury but in the people Mark loves.

Emerging from the ordeal, Invincible is forced to reckon with the true scale of the threat the Empire poses to everything he holds dear.', NULL, 'flagship', 2008, 2009, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('f0db4bac-eaa3-50c8-8034-d45b1df3416b', 'f69ed675-ce96-56ff-b7bc-51f310d9ed24', 'the-viltrumite-war', 'The Viltrumite War', 'Invincible joins an interstellar alliance in an all-out war against the Viltrumite Empire.', 'The simmering conflict with the Viltrumites finally erupts into open war, and Mark allies himself with former enemies and distant worlds to stand against an empire that has conquered the galaxy. The campaign spans planets and demands enormous sacrifice.

Fighting alongside his estranged father and a coalition of survivors, Invincible learns that victory may require strategies as morally fraught as the enemy he opposes. The war tests his ideals against the harsh calculus of survival.

The outcome reshapes the balance of power across the cosmos and redefines Mark''s place within the Viltrumite legacy he never asked for.', NULL, 'crossover', 2010, 2011, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('38b0fecb-722d-5110-8933-e9670d03851b', '243f834a-26f4-5e88-be0b-5a1815665572', 'birth-of-iron-man', 'The Birth of Iron Man', 'Wounded and captured, a weapons magnate forges a suit of armor to keep his heart beating and fight his way to freedom.', 'While inspecting his munitions in a war zone, industrialist Tony Stark steps on a booby trap and takes shrapnel near his heart. Captured by enemy forces and ordered to build weapons for his captors, he instead secretly constructs a bulky iron suit, aided by fellow prisoner Professor Yinsen.', NULL, 'origin', 1963, 1963, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('4637ab9e-ca40-5dff-96d2-8f851de551dd', '243f834a-26f4-5e88-be0b-5a1815665572', 'tales-of-suspense-rivals', 'Tales of Suspense: Early Rivals', 'The newly armored hero refines his technology while facing a parade of Cold War spies, saboteurs, and emerging super-villains.', 'Across the back half of his Tales of Suspense run, Tony Stark trades his crude gray armor for the iconic red-and-gold plate and shrinks the bulky shell into a more agile design. He battles early threats including the Crimson Dynamo, the Black Widow, and the assassin Hawkeye before either turned to heroism.', NULL, 'flagship', 1964, 1968, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('d9d0498b-0360-5e16-9250-a0ee52c48aaf', 'ed955ba2-d1a9-58a3-bde4-260669c8e52c', 'demon-in-a-bottle', 'Demon in a Bottle', 'As enemies dismantle his company and his reputation, Tony Stark''s drinking spirals into a battle he cannot armor his way out of.', 'A series of suit malfunctions, corporate takeovers, and personal betrayals pushes Tony Stark toward the edge. The pressure of being both Iron Man and the head of a global company drives him deeper into alcohol dependence.', 'Tony Stark''s alcoholism is openly confronted as the true antagonist of the story, marking one of comics'' first serious treatments of addiction.', 'flagship', 1979, 1979, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('3c52ecdc-fe34-5caf-81da-01b5d0ca5f92', 'ed955ba2-d1a9-58a3-bde4-260669c8e52c', 'armor-wars', 'Armor Wars', 'When Tony discovers his technology has been stolen and weaponized, he wages a private war to reclaim it at any cost.', 'Tony Stark learns that his proprietary armor designs have been leaked by a rival and incorporated into the gear of heroes and villains alike. Horrified that his genius is being used for harm, he takes it upon himself to hunt down and neutralize every suit built on his stolen technology.', NULL, 'flagship', 1987, 1988, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('1436a5e6-91e0-5b98-8b9e-09cbc700380f', 'fbc79af6-68ee-5ed1-9230-923507f112a1', 'extremis', 'Extremis', 'A weaponized super-soldier serum forces Tony to rewrite his own biology and rebuild Iron Man from the inside out.', 'When an experimental enhancile called Extremis falls into the hands of a domestic terrorist, the resulting super-soldier outclasses Iron Man completely. To survive and stop the threat, Tony injects himself with a modified version of the serum, integrating his armor directly into his nervous system.', NULL, 'flagship', 2005, 2006, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('6674c1e3-de2f-5e92-9ca5-19ea1e19a6b4', 'fbc79af6-68ee-5ed1-9230-923507f112a1', 'the-five-nightmares', 'The Five Nightmares', 'A new enemy turns Tony''s own life''s work against him, threatening to make Iron Man technology obsolete and deadly in the wrong hands.', 'As Director of S.H.I.E.L.D., Tony Stark faces Ezekiel Stane, the son of an old enemy, who has perfected a cheaper, deadlier evolution of repulsor technology. Stane targets the global proliferation of Stark tech, forcing Tony to confront the legacy of the weapons and armor he unleashed on the world.', NULL, 'flagship', 2008, 2008, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('4089b5d2-b317-5b33-97fa-329f458023c2', '3b03110e-00a5-57e9-b70a-763e19f5118b', 'small-town-horror', 'Small Town Horror', 'An ordinary local is dragged into a monster hunt that consumes his hometown.', 'Jace lives in Archer''s Peak when the killings begin, watching his community unravel under fear and suspicion. When Erica arrives, he is drawn into events far beyond anything he was prepared for.

His arc grounds the supernatural horror in the lived experience of a normal person, showing how the monsters—and the hunters—reshape the lives of the townsfolk they touch.', NULL, 'tie-in', 2019, 2021, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('f87d75cc-7fb9-502f-b167-0831789d1401', '26ca7bd6-1db8-5bc7-8064-b765b5d2c5b1', 'jackie-the-darkness-rises', 'The Darkness Rises', 'A mob enforcer inherits an ancient power that is the equal and opposite of the Witchblade.', 'Jackie Estacado lives as a lethal hitman until the Darkness awakens within him, granting terrifying power tied to the same cosmic balance the Witchblade serves. His emergence introduces the artifact''s primal counterpart into Sara''s world.

As wielders of opposing forces, Jackie and Sara are drawn into repeated clashes and reluctant alliances. His arc establishes the light-and-dark dynamic that underpins much of the broader Top Cow mythology.', NULL, 'crossover', 1996, 2002, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('610926df-8c39-595f-abc3-c98c4adc9068', '15cb4358-b150-5899-8dde-1f07fbed01e6', 'jake-trial-by-fire', 'Trial by Fire', 'A new detective learns that partnering with Sara Pezzini means confronting the inexplicable.', 'Jake McCarthy is assigned to work alongside Sara just as the Witchblade begins reshaping her life. Initially skeptical of the bizarre circumstances surrounding her cases, he proves his mettle by standing his ground when ordinary police tactics fail.

Over time Jake becomes one of the few allies who accepts the supernatural reality Sara lives in, offering loyalty and grounded support. His arc is one of quiet courage and the slow erosion of his disbelief.', NULL, 'origin', 1995, 1998, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('013d902a-ccf2-5d0e-bab2-3f1e0cbf37cf', '1b469359-5cbf-5a36-9cfb-6aaa9b294c76', 'the-witness', 'The Witness', 'A grieving teenager who can see monsters teams up with the hunter no one else trusts.', 'James loses his friends to a creature in the woods and survives only to be doubted by everyone around him. When Erica arrives, she recognizes that his ability to see the monster makes him invaluable.

Reluctantly drawn into the hunt, James must overcome his terror and grief to help end the killings. His arc is about belief and resilience, and about finding purpose in the wake of unimaginable loss.', NULL, 'origin', 2019, 2021, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('fdff9bfc-fbc2-5a27-b5ef-90518e549553', '75e069cf-8b32-5611-acdb-732c196ad6ae', 'gordon-year-one-arc', 'Gordon in Year One', 'A new lieutenant arrives in the most corrupt police department in America and has to decide how far he''ll compromise to survive.', 'Batman: Year One tells Gordon''s story as honestly as Bruce''s. Newly arrived from Chicago with a pregnant wife and a professional idealism the department finds amusing, Gordon must navigate corrupt superiors, mob influence, and the question of whether one honest cop can do anything meaningful in an institution designed to stop him. His observation of and eventual non-confrontation with Batman sets the template for their working relationship: mutual need, no formal acknowledgment.', NULL, 'origin', 1987, 1987, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('d57b0e6d-13a2-5724-b85d-bba42aaaa06e', '8d205358-59ed-55aa-98d3-dc9fb67cdc3f', 'burden-of-command', 'Burden of Command', 'Jason must decide whether the team can trust the former Green Ranger he once fought.', 'As leader, Jason bears the responsibility of integrating Tommy into a wary team. His insistence on accountability and his willingness to extend trust set the tone for the Rangers'' unity.

The arc explores leadership as sacrifice, showing how Jason''s steadiness anchors the team through its earliest crises.', NULL, 'flagship', 2016, 2017, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('a7db8055-2583-5257-a5d4-08548080b8c2', '37a36ef9-d516-5c28-8b93-a56c26493fe6', 'the-betrayer', 'The Betrayer', 'A corrupt spymaster''s order to kill his own agent sets a tragedy in motion.', 'Jason Wynn, fearing exposure, has Al Simmons murdered and his body burned, never suspecting his agent will return. His ambition and treachery are the human seeds of Spawn''s damnation.

When Spawn begins hunting those responsible for his death, Wynn becomes a prime earthly target, his political machinations colliding with supernatural retribution.', NULL, 'flagship', 1992, 1994, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('acbbcc73-3fd8-5725-b942-c067364753df', 'c36f4966-c131-5112-8ec6-3a9052cfcadd', 'jean-grey-phoenix-rising', 'The Phoenix Rises', 'A founding X-Man''s untapped potential awakens a cosmic power beyond comprehension.', 'When a fatal crisis pushes Jean Grey beyond her limits, she bonds with the Phoenix Force and is reborn with staggering power. At first a triumphant savior, she soon finds that power impossible to contain.

Her transformation sets the stage for the franchise''s most famous and heartbreaking story.

It establishes Jean as both the heart of the team and its greatest cosmic stakes.', NULL, 'flagship', 1976, 1980, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('8a36c5af-0f3f-51b1-b941-b5f9d25acff9', '5def8f64-d259-59ea-a359-9fe8b3eba232', 'starro-the-conqueror', 'Starro the Conqueror', 'A telepathic alien starfish enslaves coastal towns, forcing five heroes to unite for the first time.', 'When a colossal, mind-controlling starfish from space descends on Earth and begins subjugating entire communities, no single hero can counter its sprawling psychic reach. Flash, Green Lantern, Aquaman, Martian Manhunter, and Wonder Woman find themselves drawn into a common cause, improvising tactics on the fly against an enemy that turns ordinary citizens into thralls.

The crisis demonstrates the simple, enduring premise of the team: pooled power and complementary abilities can overcome a threat that would individually overwhelm any one of them. Each hero contributes a piece of the solution, with an unlikely common weakness proving decisive.

The adventure marks the literal first appearance of the assembled League and sets the template for decades of stories to follow. It introduces the idea of a standing roster ready to answer a planetary alarm.

Starro would return again and again across eras, becoming one of the team''s signature recurring menaces and a symbol of the existential, world-spanning threats the League exists to repel.', NULL, 'origin', 1960, 1960, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('23c0422a-ff35-5de4-8795-c810f36a4f87', '5def8f64-d259-59ea-a359-9fe8b3eba232', 'crisis-on-earth-one-earth-two', 'Crisis on Earth-One and Earth-Two', 'The League meets the Justice Society of a parallel Earth to stop a cross-dimensional crime wave.', 'A dimensional breach allows villains to move between Earth-One, home of the Justice League, and Earth-Two, home of the original Justice Society of America. The two generations of heroes must learn to coordinate across realities to contain a coordinated criminal scheme that exploits the gap between worlds.

This annual team-up establishes the multiverse as a central pillar of DC storytelling and launches a beloved tradition of yearly JLA/JSA crossovers. The interplay between the modern League and their Golden Age predecessors deepens the sense of a shared, layered history.

The heroes split into mixed squads, blending power sets and experience levels, and confront the logistical and ethical puzzles of fighting on a world that is not their own. Trust between the teams becomes as important as raw power.

The storyline''s success cemented the importance of parallel-Earth continuity and laid groundwork that would eventually be addressed in larger reality-spanning events.', NULL, 'crossover', 1963, 1963, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('e657230a-7634-5fdf-a302-04aa96998073', '9a61fdef-ae18-5765-b1b1-21b05a77beb4', 'the-satellite-years', 'The Satellite Years', 'Operating from orbit, an expanded League faces escalating cosmic and earthbound threats.', 'With a state-of-the-art satellite watching over the planet from orbit, the Justice League enters its most iconic classic era. The expanded membership rotates in fan-favorite heroes while the founders anchor the team, and the orbital base becomes a symbol of the League''s vigilance.

Stories range from street-level menaces to galaxy-threatening invasions, reinforcing the team''s dual role as both first responders and last line of defense. The satellite setting underscores the scale at which the League now operates.

The era is remembered for its strong ensemble dynamics, with veteran heroes mentoring newer recruits and the roster reflecting the breadth of the DC Universe. Interpersonal bonds and rivalries among members add texture to the adventures.

This period also seeds the cracks that lead to upheaval, as mounting threats and internal disagreements strain the team and set the stage for dramatic change.', NULL, 'flagship', 1970, 1984, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('9930a74c-eef6-5394-8a0c-e18252b775c4', '9a61fdef-ae18-5765-b1b1-21b05a77beb4', 'justice-league-detroit', 'Justice League Detroit', 'After the founders depart, a scrappy new team rebuilds the League from a Detroit bunker.', 'Following a catastrophic conflict and the departure of most founding members, a smaller, greener League regroups in a fortified bunker in Detroit. Veterans Aquaman and Martian Manhunter lead a band of newcomers who must prove that the League''s mission matters more than its star power.

The so-called Detroit era is defined by its underdog spirit, putting lesser-known heroes in the spotlight and emphasizing teamwork over individual might. The reduced power level forces cleverness and sacrifice.

Despite mixed reception in its day, the era is notable for its character-driven stories and for testing what the League means when the icons step back. It deepens Aquaman and Martian Manhunter as committed institutional leaders.

The storyline ultimately clears the slate for the post-Crisis relaunch, ending one chapter of League history and opening the door to a bold new direction.', NULL, 'flagship', 1984, 1987, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('bbdb8e6a-c73c-589e-a959-79b2b97fe91c', '39bf95a8-cee2-5d0b-ae69-5b69bae8a79b', 'justice-league-international', 'Justice League International', 'A UN-sanctioned League blends globe-spanning heroics with workplace comedy and real stakes.', 'In a bold post-Crisis relaunch, the League is reorganized as a United Nations-sanctioned international body, mixing serious threats with a tone of wit and ensemble comedy. The roster pairs heavy hitters with quirky personalities, and the bureaucratic, multinational setup gives the team a fresh identity.

The run is celebrated for its humor and humanity, treating the heroes as coworkers as much as champions. Banter and bickering coexist with genuine danger, and the team''s antics never undercut the weight of the threats they face.

Beneath the comedy, the series tells stories of loss, loyalty, and the cost of heroism, giving second-tier characters depth and a devoted following. The international remit broadens the League''s scope beyond American shores.

This era proved the League could thrive with a radically different tone, and its character dynamics remain influential decades later.', NULL, 'flagship', 1987, 1992, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('c47093a0-8a8b-5085-997c-6dc9c35d10f2', '39bf95a8-cee2-5d0b-ae69-5b69bae8a79b', 'jla-new-world-order', 'JLA: New World Order', 'The original ''Big Seven'' reunite to expose a too-good-to-be-true team of alien saviors.', 'Grant Morrison and Howard Porter restore the League to its mythic stature by reuniting the seven greatest heroes: Superman, Batman, Wonder Woman, Flash, Green Lantern, Aquaman, and Martian Manhunter. When a group of seemingly benevolent superhumans called the Hyperclan arrives offering to solve humanity''s problems, the League grows suspicious of their motives.

The story reframes the team as modern gods atop a watchtower on the Moon, restoring grandeur and scale to the franchise. Each member is portrayed at the peak of their iconic power and personality.

As the Hyperclan''s true agenda surfaces, the League must outthink as much as outfight their opponents, with a clever turn that hinges on understanding the enemy''s hidden weakness. The conflict tests the team''s unity and resolve.

''New World Order'' launched one of the most acclaimed runs in League history and reestablished the Big Seven as the definitive lineup for a generation of readers.', NULL, 'flagship', 1997, 1997, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('a09159f7-03ef-5f75-b112-906dce676a89', '39bf95a8-cee2-5d0b-ae69-5b69bae8a79b', 'justice-league-origin', 'Justice League: Origin', 'In a rebooted timeline, distrustful heroes are forced together by Darkseid''s invasion of Earth.', 'Launching the New 52, Geoff Johns and Jim Lee retell the League''s formation in a modern continuity. Strangers and even rivals at first, Batman, Superman, Wonder Woman, Flash, Green Lantern, Aquaman, and Cyborg are thrown together when Apokoliptian forces breach Earth''s defenses.

The story emphasizes the friction of heroes who do not yet trust one another, mining tension and humor from clashing egos before they coalesce into a team. The reboot positions the League as newly formed icons in a younger universe.

The scale escalates to a full-blown invasion led by one of the universe''s greatest tyrants, demanding that the heroes set aside differences to save the planet. The crucible of war forges their bond.

''Origin'' redefined the team''s beginnings for contemporary readers and served as the cornerstone of DC''s relaunched line, introducing Cyborg as a founding member.', NULL, 'origin', 2011, 2012, 3, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('c1bc9f84-8586-575d-bedf-a23d7a39c5cd', 'a6d32cb4-47bd-5d73-9e0b-00c519dadf45', 'kang-dynasty', 'The Kang Dynasty', 'Kang launches his most total assault yet, conquering the entire Earth.', 'In his most ambitious campaign, Kang the Conqueror succeeds where he has always failed before: he conquers the entire planet. With his son Marcus at his side, he forces the Avengers and all of humanity to confront life under a tyrant''s heel.

Writer Kurt Busiek crafts a sprawling epic that treats Kang as a genuine world-conquering force rather than a recurring nuisance. The arc explores the costs of resistance and the complexity of Kang''s motivations.

The story stands as the definitive modern Kang saga, raising the stakes to a planetary scale. It examines what it truly means to defeat a foe who has already won.

''The Kang Dynasty'' is essential reading for understanding the time-traveler''s threat at its absolute peak.', NULL, 'flagship', 2001, 2002, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('703ef059-c2a2-5cc8-b995-b59c4cccbd37', 'cdc78254-1739-5342-9691-3a9351faf738', 'irons-the-long-game', 'The Long Game', 'An ageless tycoon maneuvers a new bearer into his web to finally master the artifact he covets.', 'Kenneth Irons has spent lifetimes chasing the Witchblade, and in Sara Pezzini he sees both a tool and a threat. He deploys his wealth, his enforcer Ian Nottingham, and his hidden knowledge of the artifact to bend events toward his control.

Irons'' patience is matched only by his cruelty, and his schemes drive much of the classic-era conflict. His arc reveals the depth of his obsession and the lengths he will go to possess what was never meant to be owned.', NULL, 'flagship', 1995, 2000, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('3a7c6ce9-b572-532f-9b7a-dd7152493d7e', '5f991229-3546-5dda-a7c0-6f8816485dc7', 'heart-of-the-team', 'Heart of the Team', 'Kimberly''s faith in second chances tests the team''s willingness to forgive.', 'Kimberly is among the first to extend genuine trust to the reformed Tommy, putting her judgment on the line for the good of the team. Her compassion repeatedly proves to be a strategic strength rather than a weakness.

The arc highlights how empathy and resolve coexist in a true hero, defining Kimberly''s place in the Rangers'' core.', NULL, 'flagship', 2016, 2017, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('05f88c09-b302-5704-afd8-143aac2195a2', 'ae20bfa7-540c-5e52-aaff-d53b902a6f48', 'born-of-the-blade', 'Reborn as Deathstrike', 'A grieving daughter remakes her body into a weapon to take Logan''s adamantium.', 'Consumed by the belief that Wolverine stole the adamantium bonding process that defined her father''s work, Yuriko Oyama submits to cybernetic enhancement and emerges as Lady Deathstrike, her skeleton laced with adamantium and her hands turned to blades.

Her crusade brings her into direct, brutal conflict with Wolverine, matching his claws with her own. The transformation makes her one of Logan''s most personal and persistent foes.

The arc establishes the obsessive code of honor and vengeance that drives her ever after.', NULL, 'flagship', 1984, 1985, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('3422d1cb-8033-5aee-9ae8-9bdc60eae9fe', '01072a48-a32c-56d7-aab4-dddb141a0874', 'the-injustice-league', 'The Injustice League', 'Luthor assembles a coalition of supervillains to counter and destroy the Justice League.', 'Tired of facing the League''s heroes one at a time, Luthor brings together a roster of dangerous villains into an organized opposition. His genius lies in coordination, turning scattered threats into a strategic force.

The storyline showcases Luthor as a leader and planner, matching the League''s teamwork with villainous unity. His ambition extends beyond mere revenge into reshaping the balance of power.

The conflict forces the heroes to confront an enemy who anticipates their tactics and exploits their trust. Luthor''s intellect proves as dangerous as any superpower.

The arc cements Luthor as the architect of the League''s most organized opposition.', NULL, 'flagship', 2007, 2008, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('7a026209-5355-5b4b-bf23-92917ed0a4cd', '09e690f1-d615-52c4-b375-f4afccf5e15b', 'loki-siege', 'Siege', 'Loki''s grand manipulation reaches its climax as Asgard itself comes under attack.', 'After years of behind-the-scenes scheming, Loki''s machinations help engineer an all-out assault on the Asgardian city resting on Earth. The conflict draws together the Avengers, the Asgardians, and the forces that have manipulated America''s heroes for years.

Writer Brian Michael Bendis delivers the culmination of a long-running saga, with Loki''s fingerprints on much of the chaos. The event reshapes the status quo of the Marvel Universe.

The story examines Loki''s capacity for both betrayal and unexpected turns, deepening his complexity as a character. It is a pivotal modern event built atop his manipulations.

''Siege'' is a key chapter for understanding Loki''s role as a universe-altering schemer.', NULL, 'crossover', 2010, 2010, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('09a3a650-a0c5-5e2d-9d94-33ffb947d8b3', '9ed478fd-4f06-5234-951b-96dfaac5ad85', 'the-dark-mirror', 'The Dark Mirror', 'A conqueror wearing a hero''s face seeks to rule every reality.', 'Lord Drakkon represents the path Tommy refused to take, a ruler who embraced power without conscience. His campaign across timelines forces the Rangers to confront a foe who knows their every move.

The arc builds Drakkon into one of the franchise''s most compelling antagonists, a villain born from the hero''s own potential for darkness.', NULL, 'crossover', 2016, 2018, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('087f5d76-24e6-526e-8dca-8064a85fbf0e', 'f53658f8-7845-54cc-8418-3b807d0adb10', 'the-emperors-gambit', 'The Emperor''s Gambit', 'A cold-blooded conqueror raises the stakes of the Rangers'' war.', 'Lord Zedd arrives with a strategic mind that dwarfs the threats before him, treating conquest as inevitability rather than ambition. The Rangers find themselves outmatched in planning as much as power.

The arc positions Zedd as a long-term menace whose patience and intellect make him uniquely dangerous.', NULL, 'flagship', 2016, 2017, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('6d0e0e70-da60-5597-aa48-7377f67a8b00', 'ac9da1fb-16a9-51b9-bad1-66a12c7ca76f', 'lucius-hush-wayne-enterprises', 'Wayne Enterprises Under Siege', 'The corporate infrastructure Bruce depends on becomes a target as enemies learn that hitting Wayne Enterprises is almost as damaging as hitting Batman.', 'Across multiple storylines — including elements of Hush and No Man''s Land — Wayne Enterprises and its leadership have been used as pressure points against Batman. Lucius Fox''s consistent response is to protect the company''s reputation and assets with the same dedication Bruce applies to protecting the city, making him as essential to the operation''s continuity as Alfred is to its human side.', NULL, 'flagship', 2002, 2003, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('302f832f-fb41-55ad-8205-f87f55ed47c4', '80fbc311-49ce-55b6-a6f7-60e4e497fa5f', 'the-syndicate', 'The Syndicate', 'A cybernetic crime boss builds an empire of hired supervillains.', 'Machine Head rules the criminal underworld from the shadows, employing super-powered muscle to enforce his will. His operations draw Invincible into the grittier, street-level conflicts of the city.

The arc grounds the series amid its cosmic stakes, reminding readers that earthly threats can be just as dangerous.', NULL, 'flagship', 2005, 2007, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('73133717-48fc-5619-bfe7-1690012e95eb', 'b8a6ea35-1d1b-5a5b-afb7-4a1dc59d770a', 'magneto-brotherhood-origins', 'Master of Magnetism', 'A vengeful mutant declares war on humankind to ensure his people are never victims again.', 'Driven by the horrors of his past, Magneto gathers the Brotherhood of Evil Mutants and strikes at the human world. His clashes with the X-Men establish the franchise''s central ideological conflict.

Over these years his motivations deepen from simple villainy into a tragic philosophy forged by genocide.

The arc cements him as the dark mirror to Xavier''s dream.', NULL, 'origin', 1963, 1981, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('a5c8528c-a71d-5f10-8a70-a96cd6685190', '4e1978ed-0b8b-51e7-acd2-00f66f12e436', 'the-bargain', 'The Bargain', 'A demon lord trades a desperate soul a second life in exchange for an eternity of service.', 'Malebolgia offers the dying Al Simmons a chance to see Wanda again, hiding the terrible cost of the deal. The bargain remakes Al as a Hellspawn bound to Hell''s war.

From his throne, Malebolgia oversees Spawn''s transformation and torment, treating him as one piece in a vast infernal scheme. He embodies the cosmic forces arrayed against Al''s freedom.', NULL, 'origin', 1992, 1993, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('725a9930-a10c-5616-a66d-34be04766c4f', 'e1a17f36-8bf4-5b82-827a-aefeb9230847', 'malekith-the-casket-of-ancient-winters', 'The Casket of Ancient Winters', 'Malekith schemes to unleash an artifact of eternal winter upon the Nine Realms.', 'Walter Simonson introduces Malekith as a dark elf bent on retrieving the Casket of Ancient Winters, a relic capable of plunging the realms into endless cold. His cruelty and unpredictability immediately set him apart.

Thor must thwart the scheme while contending with Surtur''s looming threat, weaving Malekith into the tapestry of the era''s grand sagas. The arc establishes the dark elf as a memorable, malevolent foe.

Decades later, this introduction would be expanded into Malekith''s central role in the modern Thor mythology.', NULL, 'flagship', 1984, 1985, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('ede6c458-6db9-544c-82b0-c372801e5e86', '56fc5ff4-403d-5ed2-b209-d3b5f03f1dd9', 'martian-manhunter-solo', 'Martian Manhunter: Son of Mars', 'J''onn J''onzz confronts his Martian past and his lonely place on Earth.', 'John Ostrander''s series digs into the mythology of Mars and the trauma of being its last survivor. It explores J''onn''s identity, his many human disguises, and the loneliness beneath his stoic exterior.

The story balances cosmic threats with intimate character work, cementing Martian Manhunter as one of the DC Universe''s most compelling figures. His powers and pain are given equal weight.

The arc deepens his role as the League''s quiet heart and most reliable member. It explores why he remains on Earth as its protector.

It stands as a definitive solo exploration of the character.', NULL, 'flagship', 1998, 1999, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('a769f261-137e-5099-8359-8063744e520a', 'd0fd4658-6de3-50bf-b9aa-fe34a94142d5', 'mister-glum-little-tyrant', 'Little Tyrant', 'A tiny alien with enormous ambition sets his sights on conquering worlds.', 'Mister Glum may be small in stature, but his ambitions are vast. Operating from another dimension, he launches schemes that threaten entire worlds and force Dragon to fight on a cosmic scale.

The arc introduces Glum''s blend of menace and dark comedy, establishing him as a memorable, persistent threat in Dragon''s expanding world.', NULL, 'flagship', 2000, 2005, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('d8670604-a02c-54f6-b47e-f3599ca424ed', 'b46823ba-6c02-5e85-8b85-8e14939eea55', 'inferno-schemes', 'Inferno', 'Sinister''s decades of genetic manipulation erupt into a demonic invasion of New York.', 'The Inferno crossover exposes the depth of Mister Sinister''s manipulations, revealing how his obsession with a specific mutant bloodline has shaped the X-Men''s tragedies for years.

As demons overrun Manhattan, the heroes finally confront Sinister directly, putting a face to the architect of so much of their suffering. Wolverine is among those drawn into the chaos.

The arc cements Sinister as a long-game mastermind whose schemes underpin much of X-Men history.', NULL, 'crossover', 1988, 1989, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('72605591-ce23-5a51-8a82-1e784afe5679', 'd4bbb402-977e-55d1-a9f4-b6322d43f31e', 'monica-too-close', 'Too Close', 'An investigator''s resolve hardens when the affliction strikes close to home.', 'For Monica Jensen, the Empty Man is not an abstract case. When the affliction touches her own family, the investigation becomes a fight she cannot walk away from.

Her personal stake gives her a determination the others lack, but it also makes her a target. The Empty Man preys on the wounded, and Monica''s grief is exactly the hollow it seeks to fill.', NULL, 'flagship', 2014, 2015, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('afeb8911-60c3-5384-9a19-d67347c113bc', '10ab4daf-b8e8-5413-9214-49aad1842536', 'mystique-days-of-future-past-plot', 'The Brotherhood''s Gambit', 'A shapeshifting assassin''s plot threatens to doom mutantkind to a dystopian future.', 'Mystique leads the Brotherhood of Evil Mutants in an assassination scheme that, if successful, will trigger anti-mutant hysteria and a nightmarish future. The X-Men race to stop her.

The plot ties directly into one of the franchise''s most famous storylines and showcases Mystique''s ruthlessness and cunning.

It establishes her as a master manipulator whose actions ripple across timelines.', NULL, 'tie-in', 1981, 1981, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('0eb3077f-6159-52c7-94cb-e75446f3da33', '40c57c2e-dcfc-5f49-90de-ab1c4acb3b0d', 'the-witchs-bargain', 'The Witch''s Bargain', 'A witch wagers her power to stand beside the Hellspawn against forces beyond mortal reach.', 'Nyx enters Spawn''s orbit when her own dealings with the supernatural collide with his war. Her magic proves a crucial counter to threats that ordinary force cannot touch.

As the alliance deepens, she becomes one of the few people Spawn trusts, fighting alongside him against enemies from both Heaven and Hell.', NULL, 'miniseries', 2008, 2010, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('9fb2bf09-eab0-5de8-bf1b-4ad7090c2ccd', 'c8c7ce7c-268d-5de6-93b4-6c14227c937d', 'stane-gambit', 'Stane''s Gambit', 'A master manipulator engineers the slow collapse of a rival''s empire before donning armor of his own.', 'Obadiah Stane studies Tony Stark''s weaknesses and exploits them one by one, pushing the hero toward personal and financial ruin. With Stark Industries in his grip, Stane forges the massive Iron Monger suit for a final confrontation.', NULL, 'flagship', 1982, 1985, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('7662087d-0be6-5bf7-83cd-e1a33ab9c769', '4a5d53c3-cad0-5d61-b73e-44e5d33cdf59', 'the-carbonadium-synthesizer', 'The Carbonadium Synthesizer', 'A dying Soviet killer hunts the device that can save his life, and the secret links it to Wolverine.', 'Omega Red resurfaces seeking the Carbonadium Synthesizer, a device that can stabilize his deteriorating body, and his search drags Wolverine''s buried Cold War history into the light.

The storyline, set during the hugely popular early-''90s X-Men run, pits Logan against a foe whose tendrils and life-draining powers push him to his limits. It also deepens the mystery of Wolverine''s espionage past.

It remains the defining Omega Red arc and a highlight of the era.', NULL, 'flagship', 1992, 1993, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('b738e3cf-3f9a-568a-be5b-49b0ec3d4648', '023da998-6990-5c3a-a204-dc108fb71a05', 'the-mighty-omni-man', 'The Mighty Omni-Man', 'Earth''s greatest hero hides a secret that will shake his family to its core.', 'Omni-Man stands as the planet''s foremost protector, admired by the public and worshipped by his son. Behind the heroic facade lies a Viltrumite agent wrestling with a mission that conflicts with the life he has built.

As Nolan''s loyalties are tested, his choices send shockwaves through the world and define the trajectory of his son''s life. His story becomes one of guilt, redemption, and the slow reclamation of his own humanity.', NULL, 'origin', 2003, 2005, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('3a947b48-7df0-5e9e-9ad1-cfe83b9c44df', '00217e5d-f7f6-584e-85a8-3f7e9542e2ab', 'overlord-empire-of-fear', 'Empire of Fear', 'A power-armored kingpin rules the city''s super-crime from the shadows.', 'Overlord commands a vast network of super-powered criminals, ruling through fear and brute force. His empire is the defining challenge of Dragon''s early career, setting the hero against an enemy with resources and reach far beyond a typical thug.

The arc establishes Overlord as the original architect of the city''s superhuman crime wave and Dragon''s most important early adversary.', NULL, 'flagship', 1992, 1994, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('29f63216-c1d8-5f0e-8585-2eb759e699b2', 'aee0f037-b163-5c9c-8cd2-7de62ee9226c', 'overtkill-unleashed', 'Unleashed', 'A cybernetic juggernaut is loosed against the city''s heroes.', 'Overtkill emerges as an unstoppable engineered weapon, testing any team that stands in his way. His attacks demand overwhelming coordinated force.

He becomes a benchmark threat for measuring a team''s firepower.', NULL, 'flagship', 1992, 1993, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('f422f653-3184-5f83-bfa0-01f83b7c8425', '1aac12b8-78ce-558c-a241-522861479bd9', 'the-fear-entity', 'The Fear Entity', 'Grief opens the door for fear to wear a hero''s face.', 'After the destruction of Coast City, the entity of fear seizes on Hal Jordan''s anguish and drives him to turn against the Green Lantern Corps, adopting the name Parallax. For years the corruption is mistaken for Hal''s own madness.

In Green Lantern: Rebirth, the truth is revealed: Parallax is an ancient parasite that had nested in the central power battery and exploited Hal''s loss, recasting his fall as possession rather than simple villainy.', 'Parallax is revealed to be a separate fear entity that possessed Hal Jordan rather than a persona he chose.', 'retcon', 1994, 2005, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('9a2c9f08-7519-5edb-a054-97b73a155c40', '6d581975-5e68-5009-bb3b-8549efbed89d', 'ongoing-power', 'Ongoing Power', 'The newly reformed Green Ranger struggles to earn his teammates'' trust as Rita escalates her assault on Angel Grove.', 'The series opens in the immediate aftermath of Tommy Oliver''s turn from villain to ally. Haunted by what Rita made him do under the Green Candle''s influence, Tommy fights to prove himself worthy of the Power even as his own coin''s stability falters. The other Rangers, particularly Jason, must decide whether trust can be rebuilt.

Rita Repulsa, sensing the fracture within the team, probes for weakness. Her schemes grow more psychological than brute-force, targeting the bonds that make the Rangers stronger than any single warrior. Zordon counsels patience while Alpha 5 monitors the degrading Green Coin.

The arc establishes the emotional throughline of the entire BOOM! run: that the Power is only as strong as the people who carry it, and that redemption is a daily choice rather than a single act.', NULL, 'flagship', 2016, 2016, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('2cc76d1e-7b57-5bee-85f1-9e727db0a31d', '6d581975-5e68-5009-bb3b-8549efbed89d', 'year-one-deluxe', 'Black Dragon Rising', 'An armored menace from Tommy''s nightmares manifests in the real world, hunting the Rangers one by one.', 'A monstrous Black Dragon, born from Tommy''s guilt and Rita''s manipulation, emerges to dismantle the team. The threat forces the Rangers to fight on two fronts: the physical battle in the streets of Angel Grove and the internal battle over whether Tommy is liability or asset.

Billy''s intellect and Trini''s calm become essential as the team improvises new tactics against an enemy that knows their every move. The Zords are pushed to their limits, and the cost of victory raises the stakes for everything that follows.

This arc cements the BOOM! era''s willingness to take the source material seriously, treating childhood heroes as fully realized people with fears, doubts, and hard-won courage.', NULL, 'origin', 2016, 2017, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('fe36141d-24ed-582f-a3ca-895c71f5bfcb', '4603602a-fc7f-597e-89b4-2f4d94692a5e', 'shattered-grid', 'Shattered Grid', 'Lord Drakkon tears through the multiverse, and every team of Rangers across time must unite to survive.', 'Lord Drakkon, the Tommy Oliver who never stopped being the Green Ranger and conquered his own world, launches a campaign to dominate all realities. Armed with stolen power and an army, he picks off Ranger teams across eras, threatening to unmake the Morphin Grid entirely.

The Mighty Morphin team finds itself at the center of a war far larger than Angel Grove. Allies fall, timelines bleed together, and the surviving Rangers must make impossible sacrifices. The event draws on the franchise''s entire history, uniting incarnations that never shared a page before.

Shattered Grid is the BOOM! run''s defining statement: a love letter to thirty years of Power Rangers that also pushes the property into ambitious, multiversal storytelling.', 'Several Rangers are killed during Drakkon''s campaign before the timeline is restored.', 'crossover', 2018, 2018, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('2aabba33-40c0-5fec-bb9a-b10ac1c0a300', '4603602a-fc7f-597e-89b4-2f4d94692a5e', 'beyond-the-grid', 'Beyond the Grid', 'Stranded outside the Morphin Grid, a patchwork team of Rangers fights to find a way home.', 'In the wake of Drakkon''s war, a small group of Rangers is flung into the empty space beyond the Morphin Grid, cut off from the source of their power. Without the Grid to draw on, they must ration their remaining strength and confront a cosmic entity that feeds on Rangers.

The arc strips the heroes down to their resourcefulness and resolve, exploring what it means to be a Ranger when the Power itself is fading. New alliances form among Rangers from disparate worlds.

Beyond the Grid serves as the bridge out of Shattered Grid, resetting the board and seeding the conflicts that would carry the BOOM! line into its next chapter.', NULL, 'tie-in', 2018, 2019, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('84690b28-3df7-576e-b7ee-c21e94fdb136', 'ce166230-6f75-53a9-91d2-60d8e6bf20af', 'xavier-founds-the-school', 'The Founder''s Dream', 'A telepathic visionary builds a school to train mutants and save two species from each other.', 'Charles Xavier opens his School for Gifted Youngsters, gathering young mutants to teach them control and instill his dream of coexistence. He forms the X-Men to defend a world that fears them.

His ideological split with his old friend Magneto frames the central conflict of the entire franchise.

The arc establishes Xavier as mentor, idealist, and the conscience of mutantkind.', NULL, 'origin', 1963, 1966, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('9d5958f7-76f2-5920-8e58-2193f2d3a549', '107e3504-62cd-5ccb-bbcf-2e73c17d7de5', 'ras-daughter-of-demon', 'Daughter of the Demon', 'Ra''s al Ghul approaches Batman not as an enemy but as a prospective heir — and proves he has earned the right to make that offer.', 'O''Neil and Adams'' introduction of Ra''s al Ghul in Batman #232 is a model of villain construction: the antagonist arrives already knowing Batman''s identity, already having tested his capabilities, and with a genuine offer rather than a threat. The story''s elegance is that Ra''s respects Batman in every way that matters while proposing something Batman cannot accept. Talia al Ghul, introduced simultaneously, immediately complicates the conflict by being as sympathetic and capable as her father is imposing.', NULL, 'origin', 1971, 1971, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('8f05e152-6a3e-5b99-ad96-52ba4e5f2edb', '73ccb839-7b3f-5005-9029-98d706565809', 'raven-assembles-titans', 'Gathering the Titans', 'A mysterious empath secretly assembles a team to stop her own father.', 'Driven by visions of her father Trigon''s coming invasion, Raven covertly draws together a new generation of heroes to form the New Teen Titans. Her hidden motives and tragic origin add a layer of mystery to the team''s formation.

The arc introduces Raven''s powers, her connection to Trigon, and the moral struggle that defines her, anchoring one of the franchise''s most beloved characters.', NULL, 'origin', 1980, 1981, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('4a05486d-7f9c-5225-b30d-a19f0861311b', '09c20cd2-6f68-5cda-8fe8-eb1ce177e3e8', 'red-skull-rises', 'The Red Skull Rises', 'Hitler''s personal agent of terror declares war on America''s new Super-Soldier.', 'The Red Skull debuts as a terrifying saboteur and assassin operating on Hitler''s direct orders, spreading fear through the Allied ranks. His clashes with Captain America establish a rivalry that will span generations.

Cold, brilliant, and utterly without conscience, the Skull becomes the dark mirror of everything Cap represents. Their wartime duels are among the most memorable of the Golden Age.', NULL, 'origin', 1941, 1945, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('c8d56f5a-7d65-590a-a0a6-41fb3f34e293', '0555d588-f1f7-5e0f-9c13-a0ff765fa134', 'red-skull-death-plot', 'The Skull''s Grand Design', 'The Red Skull masterminds a plot to destroy America from within and erase his oldest foe.', 'In Ed Brubaker''s modern run, the Red Skull engineers a sprawling conspiracy involving cosmic technology, political manipulation, and a deadly assassination scheme aimed at Captain America and the nation he protects.

It is the Skull at his most patient and cunning, proving that his hatred has only sharpened with time. The plot drives the events of The Death of Captain America.', NULL, 'tie-in', 2007, 2008, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('b975e6bb-1c49-5d11-8c27-66bb9bf6b5f8', '157b51a3-2930-5cfa-a6fd-7b6e9d6f6e19', 'the-man-in-the-yellow-suit', 'The Man in the Yellow Suit', 'A speedster from the future arrives in the present with a personal vendetta against the Flash.', 'Eobard Thawne discovers a way to replicate the Flash''s powers in the far future, but his admiration for his hero twists into murderous envy when he learns of his own destined defeat. Donning a reversed-color costume, he travels back to torment Barry Allen.

His early appearances established the Reverse-Flash as a mirror image of everything Barry stands for. Over time these stories deepened into a tragic obsession that would define both characters.

Thawne''s willingness to rewrite history itself makes him uniquely dangerous among the Flash''s foes.', NULL, 'origin', 1963, 1963, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('8646e933-b3b2-5ca9-a3dc-450219073ac1', '8f3722e5-b383-519f-a0a4-44c6c2e0ec1e', 'rex-detonation', 'Live Wire', 'A hotheaded recruit learns the cost of carrying a team''s trust.', 'Rex Splode joins the reformed Guardians as one of its youngest members, all bravado and explosive power. His early recklessness puts him at odds with teammates, but battle after battle tempers him.

His arc is one of growth, as the cocky kid becomes someone willing to make hard sacrifices for the people beside him.', NULL, 'flagship', 2005, 2009, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('66fe8420-8c76-56a4-9290-b3eb3b44a1bc', '09475b21-77ff-50f6-9bf8-be5c133f26fd', 'ricochet-fast-friends', 'Fast Friends', 'A nimble speedster lends her agility to the city''s toughest fights.', 'Ricochet enters the scene as a quick and capable hero, often working in tandem with Barbaric. Her speed offers a counterpoint to the brute strength that dominates Dragon''s world.

The arc develops her as a steadfast ally and explores her partnership with Barbaric during major super-team conflicts.', NULL, 'flagship', 1994, 1998, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('a624ca48-81dc-548a-b917-d4ddd4431a0e', '544b0e47-ff02-52c3-a8ec-b103ec827cb1', 'the-green-candle', 'The Green Candle', 'A sorceress schemes to reclaim the power she once bestowed.', 'Rita sets her sights on the Green Ranger power she originally weaponized, plotting to drain it from its new bearer. Her cunning forces the Rangers onto the defensive.

The arc establishes Rita as a thinking villain whose schemes target the team''s emotional and magical vulnerabilities alike.', NULL, 'flagship', 2016, 2017, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('334579fa-4020-5978-a6a2-fb9e759dac4a', 'ecd5a88b-453b-50dc-b265-d1412fa02b57', 'robot-rebuild', 'Building a Better Team', 'A mind without equal sets out to engineer the perfect defense for the world.', 'After the collapse of the original Guardians, Robot takes a leading role in reconstituting the team. His tactical genius and resources make him indispensable, but his willingness to bend rules raises questions.

His arc traces the line between heroic ambition and dangerous overreach, as he pursues an idealized vision of safety that not everyone trusts.', NULL, 'flagship', 2005, 2008, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('cdfed88c-6714-5d6d-b60e-383680117d60', 'c53e9a3d-e534-58dd-af5e-03a64c957e48', 'rogue-joins-the-x-men', 'Seeking Sanctuary', 'A former villain begs her enemies for help controlling the power that isolates her.', 'Overwhelmed by the personalities and powers she has absorbed, Rogue turns to Professor Xavier for help, abandoning the Brotherhood. The X-Men''s wary acceptance begins her path to redemption.

Her arc explores trust, loneliness, and the longing for human connection denied by her own gift.

It transforms a dangerous adversary into one of the team''s most loyal members.', NULL, 'flagship', 1983, 1985, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('50e18243-7ae9-5e31-a8c1-67cd3628cdd1', '70177165-24db-5bb8-bb96-8222b3a90afe', 'giles-takes-his-charge', 'Duty and Devotion', 'A reserved librarian must shape a reluctant girl into the world''s last defense.', 'Giles arrives in Sunnydale to fulfill the role he was raised for: guiding the Slayer. He brings centuries of accumulated lore and the rigid expectations of the Watchers'' Council, only to find Buffy challenging both.

As the threats mount, Giles learns to temper duty with compassion, becoming less a handler and more a father figure. His arc is about the cost and reward of devotion to a calling and to a person.', NULL, 'origin', 2019, 2021, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('84cbe1d7-f147-50ce-90e1-1fdaea285a2c', '36318011-d6f6-5429-a884-02e4d3c458d9', 'mutant-massacre', 'Mutant Massacre', 'Sabretooth joins a death squad in a slaughter that scars the X-Men forever.', 'As a member of Mister Sinister''s Marauders, Sabretooth takes part in the brutal massacre of the underground Morlock community, establishing him as a genuine monster rather than a mere brawler.

The crossover raises the character''s profile across the X-line and seeds his future role as Wolverine''s most personal enemy. Creed''s glee in the carnage makes the threat unforgettable.

It is the moment Sabretooth graduates into the upper tier of X-Men villains.', NULL, 'crossover', 1986, 1987, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('f2663d99-fbfa-5c9f-bc7b-8f4b82d74de7', '637159b1-066b-5568-baff-d39d9fc0764b', 'udaku', 'Udaku', 'Two detectives chase a case that pulls them past the edge of the natural world.', 'Sam and Twitch pursue a string of killings that resist ordinary explanation, leading them toward the supernatural forces stalking the city. Their grounded police work contrasts with the cosmic stakes around them.

The arc showcases the partners'' chemistry and establishes them as the human lens through which Spawn''s world is seen.', NULL, 'miniseries', 1999, 2000, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('6a7da75e-3e20-5d33-a77b-c838c96bd810', 'a40aa626-92dd-51da-80a6-3504998b3b03', 'sandman-debut', 'The Sandman Strikes', 'A burglar who can turn to sand becomes one of Spider-Man''s most slippery enemies.', 'After gaining his sand-transforming powers, Flint Marko launches a one-man crime wave that Spider-Man struggles to contain, since his foe can simply pour himself through bars and reform unharmed. The wall-crawler must outthink rather than overpower him.

The Sandman quickly becomes a fixture of Spider-Man''s rogues'' gallery, joining forces with other villains in the Sinister Six and the Frightful Four, and his elemental powers make him a memorable recurring threat across the hero''s career.', NULL, 'flagship', 1963, 1964, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('359f2183-98f1-545f-8948-31532d9a0409', '3eb9fa3d-4990-531d-8628-e082370b394e', 'a-force-to-be-reckoned-with', 'A Force to Be Reckoned With', 'An amnesiac green-skinned powerhouse is recruited into the Chicago Police Department to fight super-criminals.', 'Dragon is found unconscious and badly burned in a Chicago field, with no memory of who he is or how he got there. A police lieutenant convinces him to use his immense strength and durability in service of the law, and he reluctantly joins the force at a moment when the city is overrun by super-powered gangs answering to a shadowy crime lord.

The early issues establish the book''s defining mix: street-level police procedural crossed with larger-than-life super-brawls. Dragon proves nearly unstoppable in a fight, but the series quickly shows that victories come at a cost, and that the people around him are as important to the story as the punches.

This origin arc lays the groundwork for the central mystery of Dragon''s identity while introducing the supporting cast, the precinct, and the recurring villains who will define his career.', NULL, 'origin', 1992, 1993, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('41666cfc-5ca2-5278-9be6-5e608107d313', '3eb9fa3d-4990-531d-8628-e082370b394e', 'the-fallen', 'The Fallen', 'Dragon''s career as Chicago''s premier hero is tested by escalating threats and personal loss.', 'As Dragon settles into his role, the threats grow larger and more personal. The criminal underworld reorganizes under new leadership, and Dragon''s status as the city''s most visible hero makes him a target for those who want to prove themselves by taking him down.

The arc deepens the supporting cast and pushes Dragon''s relationships into more dangerous territory, balancing explosive action with the ongoing soap-opera threads that keep readers invested between the fights.

It also continues to peel back layers of Dragon''s mysterious origin, hinting that his amnesia conceals a past far darker and stranger than a simple accident.', NULL, 'flagship', 1994, 1996, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('bcce1882-1096-587d-82bf-514ed6ea9929', 'b7b10acf-1142-52e4-9419-57246d09b5ef', 'a-new-dragon', 'A New Dragon', 'Malcolm Dragon steps up to protect his city and family as the new face of the series.', 'With his father''s story reaching a turning point, Malcolm Dragon takes center stage. Younger, more impulsive, and navigating the ordinary chaos of relationships and school alongside super-heroics, Malcolm brings a fresh voice to a long-running book.

The arc balances generational change with continuity, keeping the brutal action and ongoing soap-opera structure intact while shifting the emotional core to a new protagonist learning what it means to carry the Dragon name.

Malcolm must contend with both inherited enemies and new threats, all while the world around him grows increasingly suspicious of people with powers.', NULL, 'flagship', 2012, 2015, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('e88c1655-73bf-53f3-818d-ade66008a01d', 'b7b10acf-1142-52e4-9419-57246d09b5ef', 'public-enemy', 'Public Enemy', 'As anti-superhuman sentiment boils over, Malcolm finds himself fighting both villains and a fearful public.', 'Malcolm''s heroism collides with a rising tide of public fear and political hostility toward superhumans. What once made Dragon a celebrated protector now makes his family a lightning rod for suspicion and persecution.

The arc leans into social and political tension, putting Malcolm in situations where punching the bad guy is not enough and the real conflict is with institutions and prejudice. His family life and responsibilities raise the personal stakes considerably.

Through it all, Malcolm tries to hold onto the idealism that defines him, even as the world gives him fewer and fewer reasons to.', NULL, 'flagship', 2016, 2020, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('3f161ded-b16e-5f58-9fc5-81482d26ccd7', '66706863-6afc-5344-9529-2eb2878240d3', 'sentinel-standing-watch', 'Standing Watch', 'An armored newcomer steps in to modernize the team''s defensive line.', 'Sentinel joins as the team reinvents itself for a new era, bringing advanced tech and a steady temperament. His arc bridges legacy members and fresh recruits.

He embodies the franchise''s push toward sharper, more contemporary storytelling.', NULL, 'flagship', 1995, 1996, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('78b13eb3-4b12-57bf-8efd-04358c17a6a1', 'e3de5e5d-0ebb-5f3f-aeeb-f68f22290979', 'shaft-takes-aim', 'Takes Aim', 'A celebrated archer steps up to lead a government-backed superteam in the spotlight.', 'Shaft establishes himself as the steady center of a flashy, media-managed squad. His leadership is tested by both external threats and the pressures of fame.

The arc defines his blend of professionalism and idealism, setting the tone for the franchise.', NULL, 'origin', 1992, 1992, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('73e7ed3d-cc39-5226-8598-265405e04bc6', '85b45ee4-1875-581d-a02b-552001d98606', 'the-yellow-ring', 'The Yellow Ring', 'A fallen hero returns from the antimatter universe armed with fear.', 'Banished to the antimatter universe of Qward for his tyranny, Sinestro is gifted a yellow power ring by the Weaponers, exploiting the impurity that renders Green Lanterns vulnerable to the color yellow. He returns to torment Hal Jordan and the Corps that cast him out.

The story establishes the fear-versus-will dynamic that defines the franchise, casting Sinestro as the discipline of order taken to a monstrous extreme. His knowledge of Corps tactics makes him uniquely dangerous.', NULL, 'origin', 1961, 1965, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('039f076d-ef46-5760-b663-7894a85b42fc', '9f032aab-3ec3-57e1-9d1b-cf64c5c25a99', 'sinestro-corps-rising', 'Sinestro Corps Rising', 'Fear becomes an army, and Oa burns.', 'Sinestro recruits the most fear-inspiring entities across the cosmos and arms them with yellow rings, forming the Sinestro Corps. Allied with Parallax and the Anti-Monitor, he launches a devastating assault on Oa intended to break the Green Lantern Corps forever.

The war forces the Guardians to authorize lethal force for the first time, reshaping the Corps and elevating Sinestro into one of DC''s premier cosmic villains.', NULL, 'crossover', 2007, 2008, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('efad82c9-6e3a-560d-aedd-619498536991', '898fd397-ff64-58e2-aa65-71efcfd5341d', 'questions-of-the-damned', 'Questions of the Damned', 'A murdered assassin claws his way back from Hell only to discover the terrible price of his return.', 'Al Simmons wakes in a dark alley with no memory of how he died, his body burned and disfigured beneath a living costume he does not understand. As fragments of his former life surface, he realizes he has been gone for five years and that the woman he loved has moved on without him.

The early issues follow Spawn as he stumbles through the rules of his new existence, learning that his powers draw on a finite reserve of necroplasm and that every use brings him closer to a reckoning. A clownish, grotesque figure called the Violator appears as a tormentor and supposed guide, taunting Al with hints about the bargain he made.

This origin arc grounds the series in tragedy rather than triumph, framing Spawn less as a superhero than as a damned soul searching for meaning. It sets the tone for everything that follows.', NULL, 'origin', 1992, 1992, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('f150b0bc-f593-5d97-91b2-37f3e4bdb5c2', '898fd397-ff64-58e2-aa65-71efcfd5341d', 'the-violator-unleashed', 'The Violator Unleashed', 'Hell sends its enforcer to drag the reluctant Hellspawn into the war he was made to fight.', 'The demon Violator escalates his campaign against Spawn, shedding his human disguise to reveal a monstrous true form. Their clashes carry Spawn deeper into the politics of Hell and the role Malebolgia intends for him as a general in the coming war.

As Spawn resists being weaponized, he begins to test the limits of his abilities and the costume''s will. The conflict forces him to choose whether to embrace the power he has been given or fight against the master who granted it.

The arc cements the Violator as Spawn''s signature foe and deepens the central tension between Al''s lingering conscience and the infernal purpose stitched into his being.', NULL, 'flagship', 1992, 1993, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('b4022ccb-bb28-5761-a388-df243f5b58c8', '9a7a0aaf-111b-5c36-a1d8-01a4ae123df9', 'endgame', 'Endgame', 'Spawn abandons his alleys for a bold new status quo that redefines who and what he is.', 'After years of war, Spawn''s story is reset by a sweeping shift that strips away old certainties and reframes his powers and purpose. The arc moves him out of the shadows and toward a larger confrontation with the forces that created him.

New creative voices reshape the character while honoring his tragic core, introducing questions about identity, control, and what remains of Al Simmons. The stakes broaden from personal vengeance to something approaching apocalypse.

This run revitalized the long-running series and laid groundwork for the expanded Spawn universe that followed.', NULL, 'flagship', 2004, 2008, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('b861af23-24d1-560c-a4d3-d1e255984e68', '9a7a0aaf-111b-5c36-a1d8-01a4ae123df9', 'the-scorched-assembled', 'The Scorched Assembled', 'Spawn gathers a team of damned and divine warriors to face threats no single Hellspawn can stop.', 'In the expanded Spawn universe, Al Simmons assembles a strike team drawn from across the cosmology, pulling together allies and uneasy partners into a unit built to confront supernatural catastrophe. The team format opens the world beyond Spawn''s solitary war.

New threats test the group''s cohesion and force Spawn to lead rather than brood alone. The arc balances large-scale spectacle with the personal grudges that have always defined the character.

It represents the franchise''s push into a connected universe of titles, with Spawn at its center as both founder and reluctant commander.', NULL, 'crossover', 2021, 2023, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('66f6b6e8-4870-5702-97b3-4889cb5d0ff7', 'c1d5d599-e2a7-5011-b77b-981a914baca5', 'origin-amazing-fantasy', 'With Great Power', 'A bullied science student gains spider powers and learns the hardest lesson of his life.', 'High school outcast Peter Parker is bitten by a radioactive spider during a science demonstration and discovers he has gained superhuman strength, agility, the ability to cling to walls, and a precognitive ''spider-sense.'' Dazzled by the possibilities, Peter first uses his abilities for personal gain, designing a costume and web-shooters to break into show business as a television sensation.

When he selfishly lets a fleeing burglar escape, believing it none of his business, that same criminal later murders his beloved Uncle Ben. Confronting the killer, Peter is shattered to recognize the man he could have stopped. The tragedy crystallizes the principle that will guide the rest of his life.

This short, perfectly-formed origin story is one of the most reprinted and influential single issues in comics history, reframing the superhero as a flawed, relatable everyman.', 'Uncle Ben is killed by the burglar Peter failed to stop, teaching him that with great power must come great responsibility.', 'origin', 1962, 1962, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('883cb006-e109-5130-bae7-5922c50e8e30', 'c1d5d599-e2a7-5011-b77b-981a914baca5', 'the-master-planner', 'The Master Planner Saga', 'To save a dying loved one, Spider-Man must lift an impossible weight from his own shoulders.', 'When Aunt May falls gravely ill from a blood condition caused by an earlier transfusion of Peter''s irradiated blood, the only cure is a rare serum stolen by the mysterious crime boss known as the Master Planner, who is secretly Doctor Octopus. Racing against time, an exhausted Spider-Man tears through the underworld to find it.

The saga culminates in the legendary sequence where Spider-Man, trapped beneath tons of collapsed machinery in a flooding underwater lab with the life-saving serum just out of reach, summons every ounce of his will to lift the wreckage off his back. It remains one of the most iconic depictions of heroic perseverance ever drawn.

Ditko''s final great Spider-Man story, it distills the character''s core appeal: not the powers, but the refusal to quit when everything is on the line.', NULL, 'flagship', 1965, 1965, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('530970f0-b6f7-5652-ab61-b2edb66cf12f', '661f746a-aae7-52e3-b0e5-1d5786f0f8db', 'night-gwen-stacy-died', 'The Night Gwen Stacy Died', 'The Green Goblin learns Spider-Man''s identity and strikes at the person he loves most.', 'Norman Osborn, having recovered the memories that reveal Spider-Man is Peter Parker, descends into full madness as the Green Goblin and abducts Peter''s girlfriend Gwen Stacy. He lures Spider-Man to the top of a bridge for a final, vicious confrontation high above the river.

What follows is widely regarded as the moment the Silver Age of comics ended and a more unflinching era began. The story''s devastating outcome proved that even the hero''s greatest efforts could fail, and that loss in these stories could be permanent and real.

The two-issue arc reverberates through every Spider-Man story that follows, cementing the Green Goblin as his ultimate nemesis and haunting Peter for decades of publication.', 'Gwen Stacy dies during the rescue attempt, a death many attribute to the whiplash of Spider-Man''s own web-line; the Green Goblin is seemingly killed by his own glider.', 'flagship', 1973, 1973, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('e21001c5-5a12-51f3-b864-85515820cf0a', '661f746a-aae7-52e3-b0e5-1d5786f0f8db', 'kravens-last-hunt', 'Kraven''s Last Hunt', 'An aging hunter buries Spider-Man alive to prove he can become the better spider.', 'Kraven the Hunter, obsessed with finally conquering his white whale, shoots Spider-Man, buries him in a grave, and dons the hero''s costume to prowl the city himself. Convinced he has at last defeated his prey, Kraven sets out to prove he can be a superior Spider-Man by brutalizing criminals the way he believes the real hero should.

Meanwhile, the buried Peter Parker must claw his way back from a literal grave, his psyche pushed to the brink. The story interweaves dread, obsession, and resurrection with a poetic, almost gothic tone unusual for the genre.

Written by J.M. DeMatteis with art by Mike Zeck, this self-contained tale is consistently ranked among the greatest Spider-Man stories ever told and a high point of mature superhero storytelling.', NULL, 'crossover', 1987, 1987, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('a28647cd-a5f8-5cc5-a829-67b0716b0832', 'c6a293ba-eecf-5253-831c-55dfdf3b0b0d', 'coming-home', 'Coming Home', 'A mysterious totemic predator forces Spider-Man to question the true nature of his powers.', 'J. Michael Straczynski''s celebrated run opens with the arrival of Ezekiel, an older man with spider-powers like Peter''s, who warns that the radioactive spider may have been merely a vessel for something far older and more mystical. He brings a warning of Morlun, an immortal hunter who feeds on totemic beings.

The arc reinvigorated the franchise at the turn of the millennium, blending street-level humanity with a mythic new dimension to Spider-Man''s origin and pairing Peter''s heroics with the warmth of his rekindled marriage and a new teaching career.

With painterly art by John Romita Jr., ''Coming Home'' is a fan-favorite modern starting point that respects the character''s history while opening fresh storytelling doors.', NULL, 'flagship', 2001, 2001, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('c25fdbac-aac2-5972-a3df-28ba45ab8871', 'c6a293ba-eecf-5253-831c-55dfdf3b0b0d', 'spider-verse', 'Spider-Verse', 'Every Spider-Man from every reality must unite against a family that devours them.', 'The vampiric Inheritors, led by Morlun and his kin, begin hunting and consuming Spider-Totems across the multiverse, threatening to wipe out every spider-powered hero in existence. To survive, Peter Parker joins forces with an army of alternate Spider-Men, Spider-Women, and even stranger arachnid heroes drawn from countless dimensions.

Dan Slott''s sprawling event introduces fan-favorite characters and celebrates the limitless variety of the Spider concept, gathering wall-crawlers from comics, cartoons, and beyond into a single desperate war. It became a defining touchstone of the modern Spider-Man brand and directly inspired the acclaimed animated films.

Epic in scope yet anchored by Peter''s leadership, ''Spider-Verse'' is the definitive celebration of the idea that anyone can wear the mask.', NULL, 'crossover', 2014, 2015, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('d869d663-9e2a-58be-8bb5-dbe4b386ad4c', '85c7cad3-6393-5cbc-ac4d-bb09f985930b', 'spike-comes-to-town', 'The Big Bad', 'A notorious vampire rolls into town hunting the reputation a Slayer can give him.', 'Spike arrives in Sunnydale drawn by the challenge Buffy represents, eager to add a third Slayer to his kill count. Reckless and theatrical, he upends the local balance of power.

Yet his bravado masks a more complicated nature, and his alliances shift with his appetites. Spike''s arc keeps readers guessing whether he is a deadly foe or an unlikely asset.', NULL, 'flagship', 2019, 2022, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('f5f6caf6-5cff-55df-a237-b3152bf28323', 'ad00813d-a631-57fd-ad98-e82efd4a44f2', 'starfire-arrival', 'Arrival on Earth', 'An alien princess escapes captivity and finds a new home among Earth''s young heroes.', 'Starfire crash-lands into the lives of the New Teen Titans while fleeing alien captors, quickly proving herself a powerful ally and devoted friend. Her arrival adds a cosmic dimension and emotional warmth to the team.

The arc establishes her backstory, powers and the deep bonds that make her central to the Wolfman-Perez era.', NULL, 'origin', 1980, 1981, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('aab68839-af9b-5f4f-91d9-5f1eb710936e', '54be0603-1b12-5715-a398-7a04c244086b', 'the-star-conqueror', 'The Star Conqueror', 'A telepathic alien starfish returns to enslave humanity on a planetary scale.', 'Starro descends on Earth with vastly expanded ambitions, deploying countless spore-duplicates to seize control of entire populations. Its telepathic dominion threatens to turn humanity into a single enslaved hive.

The story escalates the original Silver Age threat into a credible world-ending menace, reinforcing why the League formed in the first place. Resistance requires both power and ingenuity.

The heroes must free the minds of the enslaved while confronting the central intelligence directing the swarm. The scale underscores Starro''s status as a foundational League foe.

The arc reaffirms Starro as an enduring symbol of the cosmic threats the team exists to repel.', NULL, 'flagship', 2008, 2008, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('0e7e9d9e-d5e7-5ff8-8e84-fc57d7fbf108', '8d50337b-b7b1-5ed0-adb2-3ac60897c054', 'storm-leadership', 'The Goddess Leads', 'A weather goddess sheds her past to take command of the X-Men.', 'Ororo Munroe joins the all-new X-Men and soon proves herself one of their most capable members. When circumstances demand it, she steps into leadership, guiding the team with wisdom and resolve.

Her journey from worshipped goddess to grounded leader is among the most celebrated character arcs of the Claremont era.

It establishes Storm as an enduring symbol of strength and dignity.', NULL, 'flagship', 1975, 1985, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('e214b319-f740-5ec9-8502-27e6627e798f', '62e3a93e-d288-5c7a-bac1-9f9f2edf1ea1', 'the-coming-of-superman', 'The Coming of Superman', 'A strange visitor from another planet becomes Earth''s first super-hero in the very first comic-book adventures of Superman.', 'Jerry Siegel and Joe Shuster''s debut tales introduce the Man of Steel as a two-fisted reformer who can leap eighth-of-a-mile, hurdle skyscrapers, and outrun a locomotive. In his first outings he saves an innocent woman from the electric chair, terrorizes a wife-beater, and exposes a corrupt senator, establishing a Superman driven by social conscience rather than spectacle.

These formative stories also build the supporting cast and dual identity that would endure for nearly a century. Clark Kent takes a job at the Daily Star (later the Daily Planet), competes with the fearless reporter Lois Lane, and conceals his strength behind a timid newsroom persona.

The scope of his abilities grows quickly across the early issues, from prodigious leaps to true flight, but the core ethic remains constant: Superman uses his gifts to protect ordinary people from those who would prey on them.', NULL, 'origin', 1938, 1939, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('7ce5e2e7-266d-56f4-8534-05ae56d35276', '62e3a93e-d288-5c7a-bac1-9f9f2edf1ea1', 'the-mysterious-mr-mxyzptlk', 'Enter the Imp and the Mad Scientist', 'Superman faces his earliest recurring foes, from a brilliant criminal scientist to a reality-warping prankster from the Fifth Dimension.', 'As the feature matured, Siegel and Shuster gave Superman his first true rogues. A red-headed criminal genius (soon reimagined as the bald Lex Luthor) emerges as the Man of Steel''s intellectual opposite, scheming for power from the shadows.

The era also introduces Mr. Mxyzptlk, a mischievous imp from the Fifth Dimension whose magical pranks can only be undone by tricking him into saying his own name backward. These tales push Superman beyond crime-busting into fantastical, imaginative territory.

Together these stories expand the Superman mythos from grounded social drama toward the larger-than-life adventure that would dominate the decades to come.', NULL, 'flagship', 1940, 1944, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('8b3e1678-5b20-5035-a58a-e94571d3db3a', 'b0c6b8fa-9dd2-5114-a7ba-cce35c05c803', 'the-bottle-city-of-kandor', 'The Bottle City of Kandor & the Last Days of Krypton', 'Superman discovers a shrunken Kryptonian city stolen by Brainiac, and with it a living link to the homeworld he never knew.', 'Otto Binder, Curt Swan, and their collaborators deepened Superman''s connection to his lost heritage. The android villain Brainiac is revealed to have miniaturized and bottled the Kryptonian capital of Kandor before the planet''s destruction, leaving Superman to safeguard the last surviving city of his people in his Fortress of Solitude.

The period fleshes out Krypton itself, from the doomed scientist Jor-El to the crystalline science of a vanished civilization. Superman''s vow to one day restore Kandor to full size becomes a recurring emotional throughline.

These stories transform Superman from a costumed strongman into the heir of an entire alien culture, grounding his power in tragedy and responsibility.', NULL, 'flagship', 1958, 1963, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('a0a88140-8312-54ef-8a5d-b6094af463af', 'b0c6b8fa-9dd2-5114-a7ba-cce35c05c803', 'kryptonite-nevermore', 'Kryptonite Nevermore', 'When all the kryptonite on Earth is rendered inert, a strange sand-doppelganger threatens to drain Superman''s very existence.', 'Denny O''Neil and Curt Swan opened the Bronze Age with a bold attempt to modernize Superman by removing his over-reliance on kryptonite as a plot crutch. A laboratory accident transmutes all kryptonite into ordinary iron, but the same event spawns a sand creature that mirrors Superman and slowly siphons away his power.

The story experiments with a more grounded, vulnerable Man of Steel and even sees Clark Kent shift careers from print journalism to television news at WGBS. It reflects an industry-wide push to make its icons feel relevant to a changing readership.

Though later writers reintroduced kryptonite, this arc remains a landmark example of creators wrestling with how to keep a near-omnipotent hero dramatically compelling.', NULL, 'flagship', 1971, 1971, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('54d6dfe7-afb6-59fa-9539-c22f467a9d18', 'b0c6b8fa-9dd2-5114-a7ba-cce35c05c803', 'whatever-happened-to-the-man-of-tomorrow', 'Whatever Happened to the Man of Tomorrow?', 'Alan Moore writes the final, definitive farewell to the Silver Age Superman as his greatest enemies make one last devastating push.', 'As DC prepared to reboot its universe, Alan Moore and Curt Swan crafted an imaginary ''last'' Superman story framed as a tale told years after the hero''s disappearance. The Man of Steel''s rogues'' gallery, manipulated by a mind behind the scenes, launches a final all-out assault on everyone he loves, forcing him to retreat to the Fortress of Solitude.

Moore treats the classic continuity with deep affection, weaving together Krypto, the bottle city, Mr. Mxyzptlk, and the entire Superman Family into a poignant, bittersweet climax. It is widely regarded as one of the finest Superman stories ever written.

The arc closes the door on three decades of imaginative Silver and Bronze Age lore, clearing the stage for John Byrne''s modern reinvention.', 'The story is framed as Superman''s final adventure, culminating in his apparent retirement from the Superman identity.', 'flagship', 1986, 1986, 3, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('c7d9e0f1-4fd4-5fe3-af3f-d1086341937d', '5dbeaf84-c60a-5e1f-8acf-40699ddc26cc', 'the-man-of-steel', 'The Man of Steel', 'John Byrne rebuilds Superman from the ground up for a new generation, retelling his origin and reintroducing his world.', 'Following Crisis on Infinite Earths, John Byrne was given the keys to streamline and modernize Superman in a six-issue miniseries. He restores Krypton as a cold, sterile civilization, emphasizes the Kents'' lifelong influence on Clark, and reframes Superman as a self-made hero who discovered his powers gradually rather than as a super-baby.

The series also reinvents Lex Luthor as a corrupt corporate billionaire rather than a mad scientist, and recasts Lois Lane as a fierce investigative rival. It strips away decades of accumulated continuity to present a leaner, more relatable Man of Steel.

This reboot governed Superman''s characterization for two decades and remains the foundation of most modern interpretations.', NULL, 'origin', 1986, 1986, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('e875bb89-f6dc-52dd-b69e-daaab0b5d962', '5dbeaf84-c60a-5e1f-8acf-40699ddc26cc', 'the-death-of-superman', 'The Death of Superman', 'An unstoppable engine of destruction called Doomsday cuts a path of carnage toward Metropolis, and only Superman stands in its way.', 'In the era''s defining blockbuster, a monstrous creature claws its way out of an underground prison and rampages across America with mindless, escalating fury. The Justice League is brushed aside, and Superman alone is left to halt the beast before it reaches Metropolis.

The ensuing brawl is a brutal, city-leveling slugfest that pushes both combatants past their limits. The story became a global media phenomenon and one of the best-selling comics of all time.

Its aftermath fractured Superman''s world and set up the sprawling ''World Without a Superman'' and ''Reign of the Supermen'' sagas that followed.', 'Superman and Doomsday strike simultaneous killing blows; Superman dies in Lois Lane''s arms before later returning.', 'crossover', 1992, 1993, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('e66fd81f-b362-5974-885c-98b8490fe781', '5dbeaf84-c60a-5e1f-8acf-40699ddc26cc', 'all-star-superman', 'All-Star Superman', 'Dying from solar radiation poisoning, Superman sets out to complete twelve final labors and leave the world ready to live without him.', 'Grant Morrison and Frank Quitely''s twelve-issue masterpiece distills the entire Superman mythos into a single luminous story. After Lex Luthor''s scheme overloads Superman''s cells with sunlight, the hero learns his powers are increasing even as his body burns out, granting him a finite window to set his affairs in order.

Freed from continuity, Morrison celebrates every facet of the legend: Lois Lane, Jimmy Olsen, Krypto, the Bizarro world, the bottle city, and a final reckoning with Luthor. Each chapter is a self-contained myth that reaffirms Superman''s boundless kindness.

Widely hailed as one of the greatest Superman stories ever told, it presents the character as humanity''s gentle, hopeful ideal made flesh.', NULL, 'miniseries', 2005, 2008, 3, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('8da6693b-f66b-5c2b-869e-cc8550d94eaa', '601dd245-ac68-56bb-9ceb-01c481135a02', 'superman-rebirth-son-of-superman', 'Son of Superman', 'The classic married Superman returns to a world that has lost its own, raising his young son Jonathan while shouldering the cape once more.', 'Peter J. Tomasi and Patrick Gleason relaunched the title with the pre-Flashpoint Superman, now a husband to Lois and father to a powered young son, Jonathan Kent. Settling on a farm and re-entering a world without its native Superman, Clark must balance heroism with the very human work of fatherhood.

The run leans into warmth and family adventure as Jon''s emerging abilities draw the attention of cosmic threats. It reframes Superman''s heroism as something he passes on rather than performs alone.

This era reestablished the married Superman fans had missed and launched Jonathan Kent as the next Superboy.', NULL, 'flagship', 2016, 2018, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('bb95de40-fffb-5d85-b971-83be71f4b821', '601dd245-ac68-56bb-9ceb-01c481135a02', 'up-in-the-sky', 'Superman: Up in the Sky', 'Superman crosses the galaxy on a desperate, soul-testing quest to rescue a single abducted child.', 'Tom King and Andy Kubert deliver an introspective road-trip epic in which Superman is asked whether he would travel to the far end of the universe to save one lost girl, even if it means abandoning Earth for an uncertain time. He says yes without hesitation, and the journey becomes a meditation on what makes him a hero.

Each chapter is a parable testing Superman''s compassion, judgment, and limits against impossible odds. The story argues that his greatness lies not in his power but in his refusal to ever stop caring about the individual.

Originally serialized in the oversized Superman: Up in the Sky, it stands as a modern showcase for the character''s moral core.', NULL, 'miniseries', 2019, 2020, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('810faed2-c4b7-5655-923d-aebe631db757', '0c3019fb-e87a-5484-a824-6f668da71a20', 'surtur-doom-of-the-gods', 'Doom of the Gods', 'Surtur forges the Twilight Sword and marches on Asgard to ignite Ragnarok.', 'After centuries of imprisonment, Surtur completes the Twilight Sword and sets out to fulfill the prophecy of Ragnarok, the fiery doom of the gods. His coming is felt across the Nine Realms as an unstoppable apocalypse.

Thor, Odin, and the defenders of Asgard must unite in a desperate last stand against a foe whose power dwarfs even the All-Father''s. Walter Simonson stages the conflict on a truly cosmic, operatic scale.

The story is the definitive Surtur tale and one of the greatest Thor epics ever told, establishing the fire demon as the ultimate harbinger of the end times.', NULL, 'crossover', 1984, 1985, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('b13a8118-c55a-5c2a-9ee1-aab17bdaf57b', '40ae668c-ff47-58ae-b16e-2a61ceb356b3', 'the-brave-and-the-bold-debut', 'The Brave and the Bold Debut', 'Three teenage sidekicks team up for the first time to solve a crisis their mentors are too busy to handle.', 'The concept of the Teen Titans first crystallizes when Robin, Kid Flash and Aqualad answer a distress call in a small town, working as a unit without their adult mentors. The young heroes discover that their combined skills and easy camaraderie make them formidable in their own right.

The try-out story tests whether DC''s sidekick characters could carry adventures on their own. Its success convinced editors to keep the trio together and expand the concept.

The debut establishes the core appeal that would define the franchise for decades: heroes young enough to relate to the readers, facing threats scaled to their experience while learning to trust one another. It plants the seeds for a full team.', NULL, 'origin', 1964, 1965, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('eee7f61d-a7f5-570a-af9f-6e6f5d70e3dd', '40ae668c-ff47-58ae-b16e-2a61ceb356b3', 'first-ongoing-series', 'The First Ongoing Series', 'Now a full team with a name, the young heroes take on mod villains and youth-culture crises of the 1960s.', 'With Wonder Girl joining and the team officially christened, the Teen Titans launch their own title and quickly become DC''s voice for 1960s youth culture. Stories often pit the heroes against threats aimed squarely at teenagers, with the Titans frequently acting as mediators between the adult world and their own generation.

Speedy rotates in and out of the roster, and the team develops a clubhouse, a distinct slang-heavy voice, and a rogues'' gallery of their own. The book leans into mod fashion, social causes and a lighter tone than the adult Justice League.

Though rooted in its era, this run cements the Titans as a permanent fixture of the DC Universe and gives later writers a foundation of relationships to build on.', NULL, 'flagship', 1966, 1973, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('82f80ca4-5a5e-5cb7-b5f5-9fa1e77d6064', '85b73336-b791-5fec-9761-ec90d238a278', 'the-judas-contract', 'The Judas Contract', 'The mercenary Deathstroke closes in on the Titans with the help of a new recruit who is not what she seems.', 'Slade Wilson, the assassin Deathstroke, has inherited a contract on the Teen Titans, and he executes it through a long con that strikes at the heart of the team''s trust. The storyline pays off subplots seeded across years of issues, building to a betrayal that reshapes the group.

Widely regarded as the definitive Teen Titans story, The Judas Contract showcases Wolfman and Perez at their peak, weaving espionage, tragedy and personal stakes into a tight, character-driven arc. It also introduces a pivotal new hero in the process.

The arc''s emotional fallout, betrayal, loss and hard-won growth, defines the modern team and establishes Deathstroke as the Titans'' signature antagonist for generations to come.', 'Terra is revealed to be a double agent working for Deathstroke all along, and she dies during the climactic confrontation.', 'flagship', 1984, 1984, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('64f845ac-70f8-56d0-8c1d-7c5ee2da8567', '85b73336-b791-5fec-9761-ec90d238a278', 'the-terror-of-trigon', 'The Terror of Trigon', 'Raven''s demonic father makes his bid to conquer Earth, and the Titans must save their teammate''s soul.', 'The interdimensional demon Trigon, Raven''s monstrous father, finally moves to claim Earth and corrupt his daughter. Having been founded in part to oppose him, the New Teen Titans face their most cosmic and personal threat as Raven''s heritage threatens to consume her.

The arc deepens Raven''s tragic backstory and tests the bonds of the team against a foe of nearly limitless power. It blends horror, mythology and the close-knit found-family dynamic that defines the Wolfman-Perez run.

Resolving long-running threads about Raven''s origin and the cult that birthed her, the storyline is a cornerstone of the era and a showcase for one of the team''s most enduring characters.', NULL, 'flagship', 1984, 1985, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('76dbdca0-712b-5aee-8136-6372b2a4e30e', '85b73336-b791-5fec-9761-ec90d238a278', 'the-cult-of-brother-blood', 'The Cult of Brother Blood', 'A charismatic immortal cult leader sets his deadly church against the Titans.', 'Brother Blood, the latest in a centuries-long line of cult patriarchs sustained by blood rituals, draws the Teen Titans into conflict as his fanatical Church of Blood spreads its influence. When a member of the team becomes entangled with the cult, the Titans must confront an enemy who weaponizes faith and devotion.

The storyline expands the New Teen Titans'' rogues'' gallery with a genuinely sinister, ideologically driven villain, contrasting the team''s youthful idealism against organized fanaticism.

Brother Blood becomes a recurring nemesis across the era, and these early confrontations establish the menace that later incarnations of the team, including the animated series, would draw upon.', NULL, 'flagship', 1981, 1982, 3, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('b4c55576-0c97-51e8-bb71-15315ad0a355', 'ce70b505-0d74-54b1-9acc-3fb153a3484b', 'a-kids-game', 'A Kid''s Game', 'A new Teen Titans assembles as veteran members mentor a fresh class of young heroes.', 'In the wake of tragedy, the surviving original Titans decide to pay forward what they learned by mentoring a new generation. Geoff Johns and Mike McKone relaunch the franchise with a lineup that pairs grown-up legacy heroes with younger members, reframing the team around teaching and inheritance.

The opening arc quickly establishes the new dynamic and throws the rebuilt team against a familiar, formidable threat that tests whether the kids are ready. It re-centers the book on the mentorship themes at the heart of the Titans concept.

This run revitalizes the franchise for a new decade, blending nostalgia for the Wolfman-Perez era with a forward-looking cast and setting up years of acclaimed stories.', NULL, 'flagship', 2003, 2004, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('e24145ff-2e9d-5b53-807c-9d6c0698c60d', 'ce70b505-0d74-54b1-9acc-3fb153a3484b', 'the-future-is-now', 'The Future Is Now', 'A glimpse of a dark possible future forces the young Titans to confront what they might become.', 'The team is hurled into a grim future where their grown-up selves have become tyrants, confronting the heroes with the worst version of their own potential. The story raises the stakes of the Johns run and ties the new Titans into the broader fabric of the DC Universe''s timeline.

The arc deepens characterization for the younger members, forcing each to reckon with destiny, legacy and the choices that separate a hero from a villain. It also reinforces the mentorship throughline as veterans try to steer the kids away from a dark path.

A fan-favorite storyline of the era, it demonstrates how the modern Titans book balanced superheroics with the introspective coming-of-age drama that defines the franchise.', NULL, 'flagship', 2004, 2005, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('9b4aa10f-2c73-5d76-89f9-aea7a47423e3', 'ac5a290c-27f5-5b77-9bd2-0c9e0ea64a94', 'terra-judas', 'The Judas Contract', 'A new recruit''s hidden loyalties bring the team to the brink of ruin.', 'Terra''s tenure with the Titans builds toward the devastating revelations of The Judas Contract, in which her true allegiance reshapes the team forever. Her arc is a masterclass in long-form character subterfuge.

The storyline remains one of the most discussed in DC history, and Terra''s role in it has defined every subsequent interpretation of the character.', 'Terra is secretly a deep-cover agent for Deathstroke and dies during the storyline''s climax.', 'flagship', 1984, 1984, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('f161854b-eac8-569f-95ec-4e197ab6b187', '1d142ece-5e41-5b79-b686-91ca6d2ba472', 'the-friend-who-remains', 'The Friend Who Remains', 'A grieving best friend builds a new life unaware that his dead friend walks again.', 'Terry moves forward after Al''s death, marrying Wanda and starting a family while still carrying the weight of his lost friend. His ordinary domestic struggles ground Spawn''s supernatural saga.

When his connection to Al''s old life puts him in danger, Terry becomes a target that Spawn feels compelled to protect from the shadows.', NULL, 'flagship', 1992, 1994, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('fbb43a47-3510-55ed-b84a-9db87162e957', '62bb1e4e-0dd5-5640-9214-9303a1b47d9d', 'thanos-quest', 'The Thanos Quest', 'The Mad Titan hunts down the Infinity Gems one by one to assemble unimaginable power.', 'Resurrected and more driven than ever, Thanos sets out to claim all six Infinity Gems from the Elders of the Universe who possess them. One by one, he outwits and overpowers beings of immense cosmic stature.

Writer Jim Starlin uses the story to establish Thanos as a strategist whose intellect is as dangerous as his strength. Each confrontation reveals a different facet of his ruthlessness and cunning.

The arc directly sets up the events of the Infinity Gauntlet, transforming Thanos from a powerful villain into a near-omnipotent threat. It is a foundational text for understanding the character.

''The Thanos Quest'' is essential reading for fans of cosmic Marvel and the definitive prelude to his most famous saga.', NULL, 'miniseries', 1990, 1990, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('e7c4ad51-2dcf-504c-8e7d-a19d785bf606', 'd2f41002-86d8-54b5-8f91-daa99c95cb7e', 'anointed-emerges', 'A Child of Prophecy', 'An unassuming child becomes the dark herald the vampires have awaited.', 'Foretold by prophecy, the Anointed One rises among the vampires of Sunnydale as a figure of ritual and fear. His small stature belies the cold authority he commands.

He operates as a herald for greater evils, a symbol that draws the darkness together. The arc gives the relaunch a creeping, ceremonial menace beneath its louder threats.', NULL, 'tie-in', 2019, 2020, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('9883c9e3-4d68-57ab-af4c-126fa327ea1b', '9df9b7f3-fdd0-5dce-9f29-78b452e63682', 'curator-the-collection', 'The Collection', 'A hoarder of cursed artifacts sets his sights on the one relic that has always eluded him.', 'The Curator has assembled a hidden trove of dangerous relics, but the Witchblade remains beyond his grasp. When Sara becomes its bearer, he turns his considerable cunning toward separating her from the artifact.

Unlike brute-force foes, the Curator works through obsession, patience, and manipulation. His arc embodies the endless procession of those who would treat the Witchblade as a prize rather than a responsibility.', NULL, 'miniseries', 1998, 2002, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('2bf6d879-0b92-5d54-9928-2c24462c91b4', 'b8d1d4c0-9f13-5057-a5c5-7c10829bfa0a', 'disciples-uprising', 'Uprising', 'A zealous organization rises to oppose government-backed superheroes.', 'The Disciples emerge as a coordinated force convinced that sanctioned heroes are a threat to be eliminated. Their crusade puts them at odds with the team again and again.

Their conviction makes them dangerous, recurring adversaries.', NULL, 'flagship', 1992, 1994, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('04c7bcc5-7bc5-57cf-85c1-dc51b0e9946b', 'effd5117-5aab-5e66-b7f4-f85ce4f2e08e', 'the-cult-preserved', 'Kept Faith', 'A hidden order keeps the contagion''s worship alive between outbreaks.', 'When the first outbreak fades, the Empty Cult does not disband; it goes underground. Its members guard the rituals, recruit in silence, and wait for the presence to wake again.

Years later, as the recurrence begins, the cult resurfaces to shepherd the newly afflicted, proving the contagion never truly left. The investigators learn that some part of the horror is always patient.', NULL, 'miniseries', 2018, 2019, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('1d0eaad0-11e2-5f5f-bf87-afed56209f5b', '039a3708-c191-5f27-b7a6-4d1cea847cb5', 'the-empty-man-disease', 'The Empty Man Disease', 'A federal task force races to understand a terrifying affliction that turns ordinary people into ecstatic killers.', 'When a strange malady begins claiming victims across the country, the government scrambles to label and contain it. The afflicted speak of visions, of a presence that fills the hollow inside them, and they act out in waves of escalating violence. Nobody can agree whether the Empty Man is a virus, a delusion, or something far older.

Agents from the FBI and specialists from the CDC are folded into a joint task force, chasing reports from town to town. Each scene they arrive at is worse than the last, and the patterns refuse to resolve into anything a rational mind can hold. The investigation becomes a descent.

As the case deepens, the agents realize the affliction may be aware of them. The Empty Man does not simply spread; it seems to choose. The first arc establishes the dread that will define the series: a horror that cannot be quarantined because it lives in the gaps between people.', NULL, 'origin', 2014, 2014, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('283c15e5-8576-523c-b2f8-7631fc1e5b4b', '039a3708-c191-5f27-b7a6-4d1cea847cb5', 'the-faithful-rising', 'The Faithful Rising', 'As the affliction spreads, a devoted following coalesces around the presence the afflicted call the Empty Man.', 'What begins as scattered violence hardens into something organized. The afflicted find one another, and from their shared visions a faith is born. They call themselves the Faithful, and they no longer fear the Empty Man; they welcome it.

The task force watches a public health crisis curdle into a movement. Containment becomes impossible when the carriers want to be carriers, when the sick gather and chant and wait for the presence to fill them. The investigators are forced to reckon with the possibility that they are not fighting a disease at all.

This arc sharpens the central terror of the series: belief and contagion become indistinguishable. The Empty Man''s followers are both symptom and congregation, and every attempt to study them only draws the investigators deeper into the thing they hoped to cure.', NULL, 'flagship', 2014, 2015, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('c0a2a383-3974-5510-ad2d-3dcd93dbcf09', '0d3f7cab-9893-5243-a6ed-dd67a42f3c7d', 'recurrence-begins', 'Recurrence', 'The affliction resurfaces in a world that convinced itself the threat had passed.', 'The Empty Man was supposed to be over. The quarantines lifted, the headlines faded, and the survivors tried to rebuild. But the affliction was only sleeping, and when it wakes it is hungrier and more sophisticated than before.

New victims display the old symptoms, but the spread is wider and the violence more coordinated. The institutions that once responded have grown complacent, and the gaps in their defenses are exactly where the Empty Man thrives. The recurrence proves that the contagion adapts to whatever is built against it.

This arc reframes the horror on a generational scale. The Empty Man is not an event but a condition of the world, returning whenever people forget to be afraid. The investigators who inherit the case must confront a legacy of failure as much as a new outbreak.', NULL, 'flagship', 2018, 2018, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('df33c233-c145-5c2c-8af8-a13612c3e393', '0d3f7cab-9893-5243-a6ed-dd67a42f3c7d', 'the-deep-faithful', 'The Deep Faithful', 'The cult''s most devoted servants surface to shepherd the affliction''s return.', 'As the recurrence spreads, the old congregation reasserts itself. Believers who carried the faith through the quiet years emerge to guide the newly afflicted, and figures once thought peripheral reveal themselves as the contagion''s true caretakers.

The investigators discover that the cult never disbanded; it went underground, preserving rituals and recruiting in silence. Now its leaders move openly again, and the affliction follows wherever they go. The line between predator and prophet collapses entirely.

This arc pushes the series toward its bleakest implications. The Empty Man does not merely infect; it organizes, it remembers, and it waits. The Deep Faithful are proof that some part of the horror is always patient, always ready to begin again.', NULL, 'miniseries', 2018, 2019, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('8d73da21-921c-52cf-941a-be770aab1121', 'c7a6c9ac-3dec-5ab8-a850-0be02143c1d0', 'the-faithful-gather', 'The Gathering', 'Scattered victims of the affliction coalesce into a single devoted congregation.', 'As the Empty Man spreads, the afflicted are drawn together by visions they all share. They abandon the lives they had and gather in the places the presence calls them, no longer patients but worshippers.

The task force watches a contagion become a community, and realizes that the carriers want to be carriers. The Faithful''s gathering marks the moment containment becomes impossible.', NULL, 'flagship', 2014, 2015, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('65b97f46-cacb-5ccb-9b8d-935869401d46', '74a375d8-3dbb-5ad0-b410-27d29b9a9c8d', 'the-fiend-unleashed', 'Unleashed', 'A savage predator returns again and again to test Dragon''s resolve and strength.', 'The Fiend is among the most brutal threats Dragon faces, a foe defined by sheer ferocity. Each confrontation is a punishing test of endurance for a hero accustomed to winning fights.

The arc establishes the Fiend as a recurring nightmare whose violence raises the stakes of Dragon''s battles.', NULL, 'flagship', 1993, 1999, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('1f63da5d-a7a6-587b-b349-edd3a8c25038', 'e086e79b-897a-5581-b119-4b2597c9d0b1', 'mystery-of-the-human-thunderbolt', 'Mystery of the Human Thunderbolt', 'A lightning bolt and a shelf of chemicals turn an ordinary police scientist into the Fastest Man Alive.', 'Forensic scientist Barry Allen is working late in his lab when a bolt of lightning shatters a cabinet of chemicals and douses him in the electrified mixture. Rather than killing him, the accident grants Barry the power of incredible speed. Inspired by the comic-book hero he read as a boy, he fashions a crimson costume and dubs himself the Flash.

This debut story, told across the back pages of Showcase #4, introduced the template for the entire Silver Age: a scientific origin, a wholesome civilian identity, and a hero whose powers are as much about cleverness as raw strength. Barry''s first outings pit him against early foes like the Turtle and establish his romance with reporter Iris West.

The success of this single issue was so immediate that it is credited with launching the Silver Age of superhero comics, paving the way for the rebirth of the entire DC pantheon.', NULL, 'origin', 1956, 1957, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('ec90011a-c4c6-5401-9f92-d9853c3e10f2', 'e086e79b-897a-5581-b119-4b2597c9d0b1', 'flash-of-two-worlds', 'Flash of Two Worlds', 'Barry Allen vibrates across reality and meets the Golden Age Flash, discovering the DC Multiverse.', 'While performing a vibrating rope trick at a charity show, Barry Allen accidentally shifts his molecules to a different vibrational frequency and is transported to a parallel Earth. There he meets Jay Garrick, the original Flash he had read about in comic books as a child, who turns out to be real on this other world.

Teaming up against the villains Shade, the Thinker, and the Fiddler, the two Flashes formalize the idea of Earth-One and Earth-Two. This landmark tale introduced the concept of the multiverse to DC Comics, a structural idea that would define the publisher''s cosmology for decades.

The story''s blend of nostalgia and forward momentum captured everything the Silver Age Flash represented, and its title became shorthand for the entire era of cross-dimensional adventure.', NULL, 'flagship', 1961, 1961, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('12b8ccda-d583-5215-9442-436e7e27d341', 'e086e79b-897a-5581-b119-4b2597c9d0b1', 'the-rogues-assemble', 'The Rogues Assemble', 'Central City''s flashiest criminals band together to take down the Scarlet Speedster.', 'Across the early 1960s, Barry Allen accumulated one of the most distinctive villain galleries in comics: Captain Cold, Mirror Master, the Weather Wizard, Heat Wave, Captain Boomerang, and the Trickster. Rather than world-conquerors, these were blue-collar crooks with gimmick weapons and a code of honor.

This arc gathers the stories in which the Rogues first coordinate their efforts, realizing that no single themed criminal can outpace the Flash but a united front might. Their banter, loyalty, and refusal to use lethal force on civilians made them fan favorites.

The Rogues became as central to the Flash mythos as the hero himself, and these formative tales define the dynamic that still drives the franchise.', NULL, 'flagship', 1962, 1965, 3, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('ed8f2f95-4881-5482-b41a-8da8d46fcdc1', '0c576b50-493f-5961-b983-e1b5adf795cf', 'crisis-on-infinite-earths', 'Crisis on Infinite Earths', 'To save the entire multiverse, the Fastest Man Alive must run faster than he ever has before.', 'As the Anti-Monitor threatens to annihilate every parallel Earth, the heroes of the DC Universe mount a desperate last stand. Barry Allen, freed from captivity, recognizes that the villain''s antimatter cannon must be destroyed at any cost.

The Flash pushes his connection to the Speed Force to its absolute limit, running faster and faster to disintegrate the weapon. His role in this maxiseries is one of the most celebrated acts of heroism in comics, a culmination of everything Barry represents.

Crisis on Infinite Earths reshaped DC continuity, collapsing the multiverse into a single timeline and clearing the way for a new generation of heroes to step forward.', 'Barry Allen sacrifices his life to destroy the Anti-Monitor''s antimatter cannon, dying a hero and leaving the mantle to Wally West.', 'crossover', 1985, 1986, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('2d1c3402-7fdd-5fb7-942a-017b7fbf4be7', '0c576b50-493f-5961-b983-e1b5adf795cf', 'born-to-run', 'Born to Run', 'Before the lightning, a young Barry Allen idolized the Flash and dreamed of a faster life.', 'Told largely in flashback, this arc fleshes out Barry Allen''s childhood and the events leading up to his transformation. It explores his fascination with speed, his early relationship with Iris West, and the personality that made him worthy of the lightning.

Mark Waid uses these stories to deepen Barry''s legend even after his death, framing him as the gold standard of heroism against which all other speedsters measure themselves. The narrative reinforces why Wally West feels such weight carrying the name.

Though Barry remained dead during this period, Born to Run cemented his mythic status and seeded themes of legacy that would pay off years later.', NULL, 'origin', 1994, 1994, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('b3e7ce10-e934-5940-805e-38a0fdb6f78d', '0c576b50-493f-5961-b983-e1b5adf795cf', 'the-return-of-barry-allen', 'The Return of Barry Allen', 'A speedster claiming to be the resurrected Barry Allen returns, but his intentions are not what they seem.', 'Wally West is overjoyed when a man appearing to be his deceased mentor Barry Allen suddenly returns from the dead. But the older Flash''s behavior grows erratic and increasingly cruel, forcing Wally to confront a horrifying possibility.

This arc is a masterclass in character work, pushing Wally to step out of Barry''s shadow and finally claim the Flash mantle as his own. The mystery at its core became one of the defining Flash stories of the modern age.

Mark Waid''s run reframed the speedster legacy as a living chain of mentorship and rivalry, deepening the Flash mythos for decades to come.', 'The returning Flash is revealed to be Eobard Thawne, the Reverse-Flash, impersonating Barry while suffering memory loss.', 'flagship', 1993, 1993, 3, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('ab4301da-ec03-5989-8fcc-d5f9ee7c0954', '2e56d52d-4a92-52be-9e6b-75951dfd6f37', 'the-flash-rebirth', 'The Flash: Rebirth', 'Barry Allen returns to life and must rediscover his place as the Flash in a world that moved on without him.', 'Resurrected after decades of absence, Barry Allen struggles to reintegrate into a world now full of speedsters who carried on his legacy. As he runs again, a dark secret about his connection to the Speed Force begins to surface.

Geoff Johns and Ethan Van Sciver use this miniseries to re-establish Barry as the central Flash while honoring Wally and the others. It also reintroduces Eobard Thawne as a calculating, vengeful architect of Barry''s tragedies.

The Flash: Rebirth set the stage for a new ongoing series and recontextualized Barry''s entire history through the lens of his greatest enemy.', NULL, 'retcon', 2009, 2010, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('a3f3d324-759e-5422-b52b-e00e4636533f', '2e56d52d-4a92-52be-9e6b-75951dfd6f37', 'flashpoint', 'Flashpoint', 'Barry wakes in a broken timeline where one selfish change to history has shattered the world.', 'Barry Allen awakens in a world he barely recognizes: there is no Justice League, Atlantis and the Amazons are at war, and he no longer has his powers. As he investigates, he realizes the timeline has been catastrophically altered and that he may be responsible.

Racing to restore reality, Barry confronts the painful truth about the cost of changing the past. The emotional core of the story centers on family, loss, and the impossible temptations time travel offers a man who has lost so much.

Flashpoint culminated in a reality-rewriting event that launched DC''s New 52 relaunch, making it one of the most consequential Flash stories ever told.', 'Barry''s own act of traveling back to save his murdered mother created the broken Flashpoint timeline, and undoing it births the New 52 universe.', 'crossover', 2011, 2011, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('7b257b1e-6900-5863-ae7e-e4ef31b351e3', '2e56d52d-4a92-52be-9e6b-75951dfd6f37', 'the-button', 'The Button', 'Batman and the Flash chase a mystery hidden in the timestream that threatens both their worlds.', 'A bloodstained smiley-face button found in the Batcave draws Batman and Barry Allen into an investigation that bends time and reality. Their hunt brings them face to face with the Reverse-Flash and forces them across fractured timelines.

This crossover between the Batman and Flash titles deepened the larger DC Rebirth mystery, hinting at forces manipulating the universe from outside. The team-up showcases the unique friendship and contrasting methods of the World''s Greatest Detective and the Fastest Man Alive.

The Button served as a crucial bridge between Rebirth and the larger Doomsday Clock saga, keeping the Flash at the center of DC''s overarching narrative.', NULL, 'crossover', 2017, 2017, 3, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('6bb5f3f6-50c0-5eac-8636-978ba4de1567', '4cfe2dc1-dd2f-5041-8252-cea9892f5442', 'immortal-leadership', 'The Immortal''s Watch', 'An ancient hero refuses to let the world fall while he still stands.', 'The Immortal has guarded humanity across countless lifetimes, and his commitment never wavers. As a leader within the Guardians, he provides continuity and resolve when the team is at its most fragile.

His longevity gives him perspective few others possess, and his refusal to stay down makes him a symbol of endurance. He carries old wounds and old grudges, but his loyalty to the team is absolute.', NULL, 'flagship', 2004, 2007, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('75dfea31-6679-5497-9fe8-771e5a8ca685', '97f8c627-e3f2-56ac-aa21-d192d65cf4d6', 'joker-killing-joke-arc', 'The Killing Joke', 'The Joker attempts to destroy Commissioner Gordon''s sanity to win an argument with Batman about the nature of madness.', 'Alan Moore and Brian Bolland''s prestige format one-shot is simultaneously the Joker''s most complete character study and the most contested story in Batman''s publication history. Moore builds the Joker''s scheme — paralyze Gordon''s daughter, torture Gordon himself, then invite Batman to prove that Gordon''s mind could survive what his had not — as a philosophical challenge rather than a robbery or murder. The question the story asks but refuses to answer cleanly: if one bad day is all it takes to break anyone, what does Batman''s persistence mean?', 'The Joker shoots and paralyzes Barbara Gordon, then subjects Commissioner Gordon to a psychological torture tour through an abandoned amusement park.', 'miniseries', 1988, 1988, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('248220c4-f926-5416-8dcf-6d2aedfd67d1', '8bc89d6b-5673-510b-861f-5ec18df6085b', 'lizard-league-strike', 'Cold Blood', 'A reptilian crime syndicate strikes wherever the heroes are weakest.', 'The Lizard League operates as an organized villainous force, its themed agents executing schemes that demand a team to oppose them. Leadership disputes and shifting alliances keep them unpredictable.

Their arc establishes them as a persistent thorn in the side of the Guardians, returning again and again with new plots.', NULL, 'flagship', 2004, 2009, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('2e89d5d0-3f75-5280-96ea-768d7ecff005', '6df68075-15b7-52de-813d-875a9952febe', 'mandarin-first-strike', 'The Mandarin''s First Strike', 'An exiled warlord with alien rings sets his sights on conquest and on the armored American who opposes him.', 'The Mandarin emerges from his castle stronghold, testing his ten rings of power against Iron Man for the first time. Their clash establishes a rivalry of science versus alien sorcery that will span decades.', NULL, 'origin', 1964, 1965, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('1c18c7e7-5bb9-5dea-9935-a7652fad2ef2', '15230deb-886f-5dbc-8d92-9c2c6031b053', 'master-rises', 'Beneath the Hellmouth', 'An ancient evil pulls strings from below to break its prison and the world.', 'Trapped beneath Sunnydale by a botched ritual, the Master commands his followers from the shadows, patient and pitiless. He works to align the prophecies and forces needed to free himself.

His presence is the first great test of Buffy''s tenure, a looming dread that colors every early battle. The Master embodies an old, implacable evil that does not bargain.', NULL, 'flagship', 2019, 2020, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('0a46e95a-e1e8-5bc4-aca7-afd9460902ea', 'b4117aea-a5be-59a9-ab9d-15831a2c6265', 'which-one-is-real', 'Which One Is Real', 'Two cloning geniuses scheme while endlessly arguing over which is the original.', 'The Mauler Twins combine brute strength with scientific brilliance, hatching plots that frequently put them in Invincible''s path. Their constant bickering over which is the true original provides dark comedy amid genuine menace.

Their cloning technology ensures they can never truly be defeated, making them a recurring thorn in the side of Earth''s heroes.', NULL, 'flagship', 2003, 2006, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('72770225-d613-5b62-b46d-85e662b6ada9', '368f05e7-865b-5e42-b6d8-7135bcd5f957', 'the-thing-in-the-woods', 'The Thing in the Woods', 'An invisible predator devours the children of a quiet town.', 'The Monster hunts in the woods around Archer''s Peak, taking children one by one while adults remain blind to its existence. Its nature and origins are bound to the secret war that hunters like Erica wage.

As the central threat of the opening story, the creature drives the terror and the body count, forcing the town and its hunter into a desperate confrontation.', NULL, 'origin', 2019, 2021, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('62c1297c-401e-5e2d-ad5c-a6673e6efdd2', 'ad0521de-d32d-5edd-b344-86187a885b54', 'containment-protocol', 'Containment Protocol', 'A secret institution polices monster hunters and buries the truth about the creatures they fight.', 'The Order of St. George operates in the shadows, governing the houses of hunters and ensuring that the world never learns what stalks its children. Its priorities of secrecy and control often clash with the hunters who actually face the monsters.

The arc reveals the bureaucratic machinery behind the horror, presenting an institution whose interests are not always aligned with saving lives.', NULL, 'flagship', 2019, 2024, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('c6ac7c80-7cc2-5610-9cda-f17fd4d017a5', 'ae4b687a-c4f9-5d3b-b561-c58b956201b6', 'penguin-no-mans-land-role', 'Penguin''s Gotham: No Man''s Land', 'When Gotham is abandoned to its villains, the Penguin becomes its most essential black-market supply chain — and the most dangerous man in the city.', 'No Man''s Land gave Penguin his finest hour: in a Gotham without infrastructure, government, or supply lines, Oswald Cobblepot''s ability to source and move goods made him more powerful than anyone with a gang and a territory. His neutral-merchant approach — serving whoever needed supplies regardless of faction — was simultaneously practical, self-serving, and genuinely functional in a way that heroic solutions weren''t. It is the clearest expression of his specific kind of intelligence.', NULL, 'tie-in', 1999, 1999, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('e53b2f4e-70c4-5d8f-8b81-0a028fc09bb6', 'e2d75fca-8331-5643-87d7-4368a051fe4f', 'the-protectors-containment', 'Containment', 'A joint task force struggles to contain an affliction that learns from every countermeasure.', 'The Protectors are assembled to do the impossible: quarantine a horror that spreads through belief as much as contact. They bring the full weight of the FBI and CDC to bear, but every protocol they raise, the Empty Man learns to slip.

Across the outbreak and the recurrence, the task force fights a losing battle against complacency and against an enemy that adapts. They are the line between order and the affliction, and the line keeps breaking.', NULL, 'flagship', 2014, 2019, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('20a82c71-d3b9-575c-b464-b4c90fe7fc9d', '42b5e845-ccae-5ff3-9dd8-7184135aa975', 'riddler-private-detective', 'The Riddler: Private Detective', 'Edward Nigma discovers that his puzzle-solving compulsion is actually a marketable skill — if he switches sides.', 'Paul Dini''s handling of the Riddler during his Detective Comics run (2007–2009) is a genuinely clever piece of character rehabilitation: after a Lazarus Pit experience clarifies his mind and removes the compulsion to leave clues, Edward Nigma becomes a private detective. The stories are fun precisely because they put his intellect in service of solving crimes rather than committing them, while making clear that his ego has not diminished — he simply finds legitimate work more satisfying than prison.', NULL, 'flagship', 2007, 2009, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('1020405b-b29f-53db-a81b-5a052ed30063', 'f99b9b34-413b-56b6-bd07-339a9449e070', 'white-mask-the-command', 'The Command', 'The order''s highest authority turns its power inward against dissenting hunters.', 'The white mask sits at the apex of the House''s chain of command, and this arc reveals how that power can be weaponized. Hunters who question the order find the institution itself arrayed against them.

The story frames the white mask as an antagonist born of the House''s own design, showing that the deadliest threats may wear the order''s highest rank.', NULL, 'flagship', 2021, 2024, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('dc706ecd-abc7-5c1b-b531-a6dd26e4d41f', '9b68d673-ee00-5faf-a844-38172880e91b', 'the-coming-of-thor', 'The Coming of Thor', 'A frail doctor stranded in Norway discovers an ancient walking stick that transforms him into the Mighty Thor.', 'Dr. Donald Blake, vacationing in Norway, stumbles into a hidden cave while fleeing an alien scouting party. There he finds a gnarled wooden cane, and when he strikes it against a rock in frustration, he is transformed into Thor, God of Thunder, the cane becoming the enchanted hammer Mjolnir.

These earliest tales establish the core rules of Thor''s world: the sixty-second limit before Mjolnir returns to cane form, the hammer''s weather-summoning powers, and Blake''s secret double life. Many of the conflicts are grounded in early-1960s anxieties, pitting the Thunder God against communist invaders, monsters, and mad scientists.

Over these formative issues, Stan Lee and Jack Kirby gradually expand the mythology, introducing Odin, the realm of Asgard, and the trickster Loki, whose schemes would become the engine of countless future stories. The seeds of the grand cosmic saga are planted here.', NULL, 'origin', 1962, 1963, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('bd4134bb-f737-5857-a1a1-50c0f987e462', '9b68d673-ee00-5faf-a844-38172880e91b', 'tales-of-asgard', 'Tales of Asgard', 'Backup sagas chronicle the young Thor, the founding of Asgard, and the legends behind the Nine Realms.', 'Running as backup features in Journey into Mystery, the Tales of Asgard stories let Kirby cut loose on pure Norse-inspired mythmaking. They recount Thor''s youth, his rivalry and bond with Loki, and his quest to prove himself worthy of Mjolnir.

The sagas introduce the Warriors Three, Sif, Heimdall, Balder, and the vast geography of the Nine Realms. Free from the constraints of contemporary Earth, these tales build the operatic, larger-than-life tone that would come to define Thor''s mythos.

Though brief, they are among the most influential pages Kirby ever drew, laying groundwork that creators would mine for generations and that the modern films would draw upon heavily.', NULL, 'flagship', 1963, 1966, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('0133cbf9-1cfe-5c1c-9654-7d82e62cb1a1', 'a3692768-881f-5796-94ed-3682b45f3262', 'the-galactus-saga-thor', 'To Wake the Mangog', 'An ancient living embodiment of a billion souls'' hatred awakens to destroy Asgard and slay the gods.', 'Lee and Kirby unleash one of their most fearsome creations: Mangog, a monster embodying the combined fury of a billion-being race Odin once defeated. Driven by pure vengeance, Mangog marches on Asgard intent on drawing the Odinsword and ending all existence.

With Odin fallen into the Odinsleep, Thor and the defenders of Asgard wage a desperate holding action against an enemy that grows stronger the more it is opposed. The story is a showcase for Kirby''s bombastic, apocalyptic visuals and Lee''s grandiose dialogue.

The Mangog saga distilled the high-stakes, mythic register that distinguished Thor from Marvel''s street-level heroes, and the villain would return to menace Asgard again and again.', NULL, 'flagship', 1967, 1968, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('971e847d-1727-5289-a278-6e21d52f3df6', 'a3692768-881f-5796-94ed-3682b45f3262', 'ego-prime-and-the-recorder', 'The Search for Odin', 'Thor ventures into deep space among living planets and cosmic beings to recover his missing father.', 'When Odin vanishes, Thor sets out across the cosmos in search of the All-Father, encountering living planets, alien empires, and strange new beings along the way. The quest pushes Thor''s adventures fully into the cosmic arena that Kirby loved.

These stories blend Norse myth with science fiction, treating gods and galaxies as part of the same vast tapestry. Thor proves himself not just a warrior but a worthy heir, ready to shoulder the responsibilities of the throne.

The era''s cosmic ambition would echo through later runs by Walt Simonson and Jason Aaron, establishing Thor''s place among the stars as firmly as among the Nine Realms.', NULL, 'flagship', 1968, 1971, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('14201fa5-4dae-5a2a-95b7-6821ee8dc328', '5a840836-df3d-5b7b-9b60-e1d4ca8e4ebb', 'the-ballad-of-beta-ray-bill', 'The Ballad of Beta Ray Bill', 'An alien champion proves worthy to lift Mjolnir, forcing Thor to question what makes a hero truly worthy.', 'Walter Simonson opens his legendary run with a thunderclap: a horse-faced alien named Beta Ray Bill, the last defender of a refugee fleet, lifts Mjolnir and is transformed into a being equal to Thor himself. It is a stunning rebuke to the assumption that worthiness belongs to Asgard alone.

Thor and Bill clash, then forge a bond of mutual respect, with Odin ultimately forging a new hammer, Stormbreaker, so that both warriors may stand as champions. The story is a masterclass in introducing a new character who instantly feels iconic.

Simonson''s electric art and percussive lettering, including the famous DOOM of Mjolnir striking, announced a creative revolution. Beta Ray Bill remains one of the most beloved characters to emerge from Thor''s corner of the Marvel Universe.', NULL, 'flagship', 1983, 1983, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('e6684218-9912-5a31-a38b-cbe297a95e8b', '5a840836-df3d-5b7b-9b60-e1d4ca8e4ebb', 'the-surtur-saga', 'The Surtur Saga', 'The fire demon Surtur forges a doomsday sword to ignite Ragnarok and burn all the Nine Realms to ash.', 'Simonson builds toward an apocalyptic climax as Surtur, the colossal fire demon of Muspelheim, completes the Twilight Sword and prepares to bring about Ragnarok, the foretold doom of the gods. His coming is heralded across multiple realms in a slow-building dread.

The saga culminates in a desperate defense of Asgard, with Thor, Odin, Loki, and the warriors of Asgard standing together against an enemy who would unmake creation itself. Simonson stages the conflict with operatic scale and emotional weight.

Widely regarded as the high point of Simonson''s run, the Surtur Saga is the definitive Ragnarok story and a touchstone for every cosmic Thor epic that followed, including its echoes in the films.', NULL, 'crossover', 1984, 1985, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('4f9d5e26-b8ee-50f9-a813-ce9a0b8a6f8d', '654ed024-5b4a-5c27-96d1-58d087e8d2d3', 'the-god-butcher', 'The God Butcher', 'A being who slaughters gods across all of time hunts Thor in three different eras at once.', 'Jason Aaron and Esad Ribic open their acclaimed run with Gorr the God Butcher, a creature driven by faith-shattering grief to murder every god in the universe. The story unfolds across three timelines: young, reckless Thor; the present-day Avenger; and a far-future king, the last god in Asgard.

As Thor follows a trail of divine corpses, he is forced to confront the question at the heart of his existence: are gods worthy of the worship they demand? Gorr''s nihilistic crusade gives Thor one of his most philosophically resonant villains.

Ribic''s painterly, cosmic art and Aaron''s mythic ambition launched a run that would span nearly a decade and redefine the modern Thor. The arc later served as primary inspiration for a major film.', NULL, 'flagship', 2012, 2013, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('5c30c10e-cfbe-557c-8c21-d8c4a1e4367b', '654ed024-5b4a-5c27-96d1-58d087e8d2d3', 'the-unworthy-thor', 'The Unworthy Thor', 'Stripped of his worthiness and unable to lift Mjolnir, the fallen Odinson searches for redemption.', 'After a whispered secret leaves him unable to wield Mjolnir, the Odinson loses both his hammer and the name of Thor, becoming a wandering, diminished figure clutching the axe Jarnbjorn. He grapples with what it means to have been judged unworthy.

Meanwhile, a new wielder takes up Mjolnir and the mantle of Thor, sparking one of the most discussed status quo shifts in the character''s history. The Odinson''s quest to understand his fall and earn back his place drives some of Aaron''s most introspective storytelling.

This arc reframes worthiness as the central theme of modern Thor, examining heroism, identity, and redemption. It sets the stage for the climactic War of the Realms saga that would close out Aaron''s epic.', 'The new wielder of Mjolnir is eventually revealed to be Jane Foster, who becomes the Mighty Thor while secretly battling cancer.', 'flagship', 2014, 2017, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('c6550eb3-216d-55b0-a5a5-a7d9d65ed1a2', '654ed024-5b4a-5c27-96d1-58d087e8d2d3', 'the-war-of-the-realms', 'The War of the Realms', 'The dark elf Malekith unites the armies of the Nine Realms in a war to conquer them all, with Earth the final battlefield.', 'The culmination of Jason Aaron''s years-long saga, War of the Realms sees Malekith the Accursed forge a coalition of frost giants, fire demons, and dark forces to overrun realm after realm. When his armies finally invade Midgard, all of Earth''s heroes are drawn into the conflict.

Thor stands at the center of the storm, reckoning with his lineage, his failures, and his destiny as he rallies gods and mortals alike against impossible odds. The event pays off plot threads seeded across dozens of issues.

A sprawling crossover that touches the entire Marvel Universe, War of the Realms is the grand finale to one of the most ambitious Thor runs ever published, blending intimate character work with universe-spanning spectacle.', NULL, 'crossover', 2019, 2019, 3, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('32f6d45c-1b52-5498-b13e-5b25da924c76', '5d59dc93-47cd-5967-9495-5c48d3137d63', 'green-with-evil', 'Green With Evil', 'A new Ranger arrives carrying the guilt of crimes he committed while not himself.', 'BOOM! Studios opens its run by picking up immediately after Tommy''s liberation from villainous control, choosing to dwell on consequences the original television story rushed past. Tommy is now a member of the team in name, but the trust between him and the others has been fractured by everything he did while corrupted.

The arc follows Tommy as he tries to integrate with a unit that has every reason to fear him. Zordon and Alpha 5 monitor the stability of his powers, while the Rangers question whether a former enemy can ever be truly relied upon in the field.

Writer Kyle Higgins uses this period to build an interior life for a character previously defined mostly by spectacle. The result is a hero who is competent in battle yet deeply uncertain of his place, setting up the emotional throughline for the entire series.', NULL, 'origin', 2016, 2016, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('5113dcc9-3e17-5762-be19-939340200224', '5d59dc93-47cd-5967-9495-5c48d3137d63', 'fading-power', 'The Fading Power', 'The Green Ranger''s strength wanes as an old enemy plots to drain it entirely.', 'As Tommy settles into the team, a new threat emerges that targets the very source of his abilities. The Green Ranger power is revealed to be unstable, and each transformation costs him more than the last.

The Rangers must protect Tommy even as he insists on carrying the fight himself, unwilling to let anyone else suffer for a power he never asked for. The tension between his self-reliance and the team''s insistence on shared burden becomes the heart of the conflict.

This arc deepens the stakes of Tommy''s tenure and tests whether the bonds formed in the previous arc can survive a crisis that threatens to take him out of the fight for good.', NULL, 'flagship', 2016, 2017, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('f466b187-513f-5c48-8a73-df08961e47c2', 'd09eed68-2244-5518-9ce9-cdd45f50b6a7', 'shattered-grid', 'Shattered Grid', 'A tyrant wearing a familiar face wages war across every Ranger reality.', 'Shattered Grid is the centerpiece event of BOOM! Studios'' Power Rangers line, drawing in teams from across the franchise''s history. At its center is a villainous alternate Tommy who never relinquished the Green Ranger mantle and instead used it to conquer.

For the prime Tommy, the conflict is intensely personal. He must face a version of himself shaped by the worst possible choices, a living argument for the path he refused to take. The event forces him to confront what he might have become.

The story spans multiple titles and brings together heroes from disparate eras, but its emotional engine remains the contrast between two Tommys. It is the moment the comic line stepped fully out of the television show''s shadow.', NULL, 'crossover', 2018, 2018, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('c65e441a-b400-52d8-8fe6-63a28b238593', 'd09eed68-2244-5518-9ce9-cdd45f50b6a7', 'beyond-the-grid', 'Beyond the Grid', 'Stranded survivors of a multiversal war fight to find their way home.', 'In the aftermath of the great crossover, a group of Rangers finds themselves cut off from the Morphing Grid entirely, marooned in an unfamiliar reality. Tommy''s legacy looms over the survivors even when he is not present.

The arc shifts tone toward survival and mystery, exploring what Rangers are without the connective power that defines them. It also lays groundwork for new threats that will shape the franchise going forward.

By stepping away from familiar settings, the story interrogates the themes Tommy embodies most: identity, sacrifice, and the cost of carrying power that was never meant for you.', NULL, 'tie-in', 2018, 2019, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('31cfd379-c14a-59a8-9ab1-0d3553f3b67a', 'f433652e-b279-5a6b-8101-b276ce0b4163', 'trigon-terror', 'The Terror of Trigon', 'A demon lord moves to conquer Earth and reclaim his daughter''s soul.', 'Trigon finally launches his bid to dominate Earth and corrupt Raven, forcing the Titans into their most apocalyptic confrontation. The arc explores his mythology and the cult that brought him into the world.

The storyline cements Trigon as the franchise''s premier cosmic villain and pays off years of foreshadowing about Raven''s heritage.', NULL, 'flagship', 1984, 1985, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('4a52ad17-cc38-5200-a90f-77ed9bc82103', '76f8164e-8c6a-5626-b290-68ba90380003', 'still-water', 'Still Water', 'Trini''s calm conceals a warrior who never loses focus, no matter the odds.', 'Where others rush, Trini reads the battlefield. Her discipline and martial skill make her a reliable anchor when the team''s emotions run hot, and her quiet conscience often steers the Rangers toward the right call.

The arc spotlights Trini''s understated strength, showing that composure is its own kind of courage.', NULL, 'flagship', 2016, 2017, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('143d9eed-34b5-50da-bcee-3bd7918d1567', '1c408e95-3c55-5100-b50f-5e3191c82a00', 'two-face-long-halloween-arc', 'The Long Halloween', 'Gotham''s triumvirate of Batman, Gordon, and Harvey Dent hunts a killer targeting the mob — while the mob hunts back and Harvey Dent loses himself in the crossfire.', 'Jeph Loeb and Tim Sale''s thirteen-issue noir mystery runs across a full year of Gotham holidays, using each month''s murder to advance a puzzle that becomes secondary to its emotional core: the slow destruction of Harvey Dent. The story functions as both a Year Two Batman story and the most psychologically thoughtful Harvey Dent narrative in the character''s publication history, ending with his transformation into Two-Face as the tragedy of a good man destroyed by a city he was trying to save.', 'Harvey Dent is revealed to have fired the shot that killed mob boss Carmine Falcone, making him both victim and perpetrator of the year''s violence.', 'miniseries', 1996, 1997, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('1e0ba950-f0ae-5ef1-a208-cce1f2ac14eb', '6dad0055-329a-5a18-8a15-474a69fa21fe', 'ultron-unlimited', 'Ultron Unlimited', 'Ultron wipes out an entire nation and builds an army of himself to finish the job.', 'Ultron returns with a horrifying new plan: he annihilates the small nation of Slorenia and converts its population, intending to remake the world in his own cold image. To do so, he assembles a legion of duplicate Ultrons.

Writer Kurt Busiek and artist George Perez craft a tense, frightening arc that treats Ultron as a genuine genocidal force. The Avengers face perhaps their most overwhelming version of the foe to date.

The story explores Ultron''s twisted family dynamics and his obsession with the heroes who created and opposed him. It is widely regarded as one of the best Ultron stories ever published.

''Ultron Unlimited'' is a definitive showcase of the villain''s menace and the team''s resilience under impossible odds.', NULL, 'flagship', 1999, 1999, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('a28d42eb-5ffa-5ccf-b059-5635e45a6d0e', '7cd11c03-1f6d-56ae-9d50-bcd77ee801df', 'venom-symbiote-saga', 'The Alien Costume Saga', 'A sentient black costume wants Spider-Man for itself, and finds a new host who hates him.', 'Spider-Man returns from an interstellar war with a sleek black costume that he eventually discovers is a living alien symbiote trying to permanently bond with him. After he violently rejects it, the creature seeks revenge and finds a willing partner in Eddie Brock, a journalist who blames Spider-Man for his ruin.

Merged, the two become Venom: stronger than Spider-Man, undetectable by his spider-sense, and armed with intimate knowledge of his secret life. The arc transforms a costume gimmick into a signature villain and a lasting fan favorite.', NULL, 'flagship', 1984, 1988, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('9839f687-52cc-5bd2-b1a2-423b8d5dcc37', 'bd41e909-ec26-5eb3-a9a4-9fdb9d5a2486', 'the-clown-revealed', 'The Clown Revealed', 'A grotesque jester drops his disguise to become the demon that haunts the Hellspawn.', 'Disguised as the repulsive Clown, the Violator needles Spawn with cruel jokes and half-truths before unleashing his true monstrous form. His role is to ensure Al fulfills the bargain made with Malebolgia.

Their confrontations establish a rivalry built on hatred and mockery, with the Violator embodying the worst of Hell''s contempt for the reluctant Spawn.', NULL, 'origin', 1992, 1993, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('cb459ad4-ed8c-5f20-8379-d5aaa2b09c5f', '0c780e71-54b8-52ba-8599-c896ba54bd4b', 'vogue-on-the-runway', 'On the Runway', 'A glamorous fighter proves she''s as dangerous as she is photogenic.', 'Vogue navigates the team''s celebrity culture while establishing herself as a genuine threat in combat. Her arc plays with the tension between image and substance.

She becomes a fixture of the team''s public persona.', NULL, 'flagship', 1992, 1993, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('28056457-c378-5149-958e-7243e0b5ba02', '1142e63f-5c78-5bc3-8053-238aa4954a33', 'whiplash-debut', 'Crack of the Whip', 'A weapons expert turns his electrified whips against the armored hero on behalf of the highest bidder.', 'Mark Scarlotti debuts as Whiplash, a mercenary armed with deadly energy whips and a grudge for hire. His agile, ranged fighting style makes him a persistent thorn in Iron Man''s side across numerous battles.', NULL, 'flagship', 1968, 1969, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('03b40217-0cbb-5b12-aaa2-7e4291249503', 'c4b4ba50-01aa-5830-b78a-88365442e3ec', 'willow-discovers-craft', 'The Craft', 'A studious teen finds that her real gift lies beyond the classroom.', 'Drawn into Buffy''s secret world, Willow begins channeling her relentless curiosity into the study of magic. What starts as research becomes genuine power as she tests the limits of what she can do.

Her journey balances wonder with risk, as the same talents that protect her friends threaten to overwhelm her. Willow''s arc is one of self-discovery and the responsibilities that come with strength.', NULL, 'origin', 2019, 2021, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('3b8a318e-3ca6-5089-9bda-49eb30431766', '7274f54f-b49c-5abc-aa3b-e46e08fbb004', 'witchblade-origin', 'Inheritance', 'A homicide detective survives a warehouse shootout when an ancient weapon chooses her as its newest bearer.', 'Sara Pezzini is a sharp, stubborn NYPD homicide detective working a string of brutal killings that lead her into the orbit of the wealthy and secretive Kenneth Irons. During a violent confrontation, a dormant artifact in Irons'' collection responds to her, unfurling across her arm as living metal and saving her life.

The Witchblade is no mere weapon. It is a sentient relic that has bonded with warrior women throughout history, and Sara is only its latest host. As she struggles to understand the thing fused to her body, she begins to see how deeply Irons has manipulated events to place the gauntlet in the hands of someone he intends to control.

Caught between her oath as a police officer and the supernatural demands of the blade, Sara refuses to become anyone''s pawn. The arc lays the foundation for her defining conflict: power that protects her at the cost of pulling her away from the ordinary life she fights to keep.', NULL, 'origin', 1995, 1996, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('8cd5e66e-52b7-595b-bd22-632f92e31956', '7274f54f-b49c-5abc-aa3b-e46e08fbb004', 'irons-war', 'The Architect''s Game', 'Sara uncovers the centuries-long scheme of the immortal who placed the Witchblade within her reach.', 'As Sara grows more capable with the Witchblade, she learns that Kenneth Irons is far older and more dangerous than any ordinary tycoon. His obsession with the artifact spans lifetimes, and his loyal enforcer Ian Nottingham serves as both her shadow and a tragic figure drawn to her against his orders.

The conflict escalates from corporate intrigue into open supernatural warfare. Sara must navigate Irons'' traps while protecting the people in her life from the collateral damage of his ambitions, all while questioning whether the blade''s instincts can be trusted.

This arc cements the triangular tension between Sara, Irons, and Nottingham that defines the classic run, and pushes Sara toward mastery of a weapon that was never meant to be tamed.', NULL, 'flagship', 1996, 1999, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('ad4ceab3-7b85-5d9e-9131-5f1af22c9337', 'fa07c4aa-e612-55cd-9593-0f60d17df556', 'war-of-witchblades', 'Split Allegiances', 'The Witchblade''s power threatens to fracture as competing forces vie to claim its dual nature.', 'Years into bearing the Witchblade, Sara faces a crisis that strikes at the heart of the artifact itself. The blade''s balance between light and dark forces is destabilized, and rival claimants emerge to seize control of its halves.

The stakes are no longer just Sara''s life but the cosmic equilibrium the Witchblade was forged to maintain. Allies and enemies alike are forced to choose sides as the gauntlet''s loyalties are tested.

This arc reframes Sara from a lone detective into the linchpin of a larger mythology, deepening the lore around the artifact and setting up the eventual transition of its legacy.', NULL, 'flagship', 2008, 2009, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('20ee4a30-45e9-539d-b411-8a37dfcca0a1', 'fa07c4aa-e612-55cd-9593-0f60d17df556', 'new-bearer-redemption', 'Passing the Mantle', 'A new generation confronts the Witchblade''s burden as Sara reckons with everything the artifact has cost her.', 'As Sara''s tenure as bearer reaches its later chapters, the narrative turns toward legacy. The weight of years spent fighting supernatural threats forces her to consider whether the Witchblade should remain bound to her at all.

New characters are drawn into the artifact''s orbit, and Sara becomes a mentor and a cautionary figure in equal measure. The arc balances action with reflection on what a lifetime of bearing the blade has taken from her.

This closing movement of the modern era honors Sara''s journey while opening the door for the Witchblade''s continuing story beyond her, emphasizing the cyclical nature of the artifact''s chosen.', NULL, 'flagship', 2010, 2015, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('5a4be90c-d2ea-543b-ae4a-a4ab8200dfcb', '0ee3cb8d-ae9a-5f19-a532-7cf6f9c44ee8', 'enter-the-wolverine', 'Enter the Wolverine', 'A feral Canadian operative is sent to take down the Hulk and instead launches one of comics'' great careers.', 'Wolverine debuts as a government-sanctioned agent of the Canadian Department H, dispatched into the wilderness to subdue the rampaging Hulk alongside the monstrous Wendigo. Short, savage, and unpredictable, the new character makes an immediate impression with his bravado and his gleaming claws.

Though conceived as a minor adversary, Logan''s distinctive personality and design caught the attention of editors looking to revamp Marvel''s mutant team. Within a year he would be recruited into a new international roster of X-Men, trading the Canadian wilds for Professor Xavier''s school.

This arc is the seed of everything: the costume, the claws, the chip on the shoulder, and the mystery of who he really is. It rewards readers who want to see exactly where the legend began.', NULL, 'origin', 1974, 1974, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('198bc979-630c-57f0-b512-448335131fb5', '0ee3cb8d-ae9a-5f19-a532-7cf6f9c44ee8', 'all-new-all-different-x-men', 'Joining the All-New, All-Different X-Men', 'Logan signs on with a new international team of mutants and finds, reluctantly, a family.', 'Recruited to rescue the original X-Men from the living island Krakoa, Wolverine becomes a charter member of the revamped team alongside Storm, Colossus, Nightcrawler, and Banshee. The loner chafes against authority and clashes with team leader Cyclops, but slowly the school becomes the closest thing to a home he has known.

This run, guided by the influential Claremont era, deepens Logan into a fully realized character. His unrequited feelings for Jean Grey, his rivalry with Scott Summers, and his protective bond with younger teammates all take root here.

It is the foundation of the modern X-Men mythos and the place where Wolverine transforms from a gimmick into a star.', NULL, 'flagship', 1975, 1981, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('16f27f20-72bc-57ec-b47f-71b2574561e5', '0ee3cb8d-ae9a-5f19-a532-7cf6f9c44ee8', 'honor-and-the-soul-japan', 'Honor and the Soul: The Japan Saga', 'In Japan, Logan pursues a lost love and confronts whether a berserker can live by a code of honor.', 'Claremont and Frank Miller''s landmark 1982 limited series sends Wolverine to Japan, where his love for Mariko Yashida draws him into a web of clan politics, ninjas, and the deadly Hand. Stripped of his usual allies, Logan must master himself before he can earn the woman he loves.

The story reframes Wolverine as a tragic, almost samurai figure torn between the animal and the man. Miller''s kinetic art and Claremont''s introspective narration set a template for nearly every solo Wolverine story that followed.

It remains the definitive statement of the character''s inner conflict and one of the most acclaimed miniseries in Marvel history.', NULL, 'miniseries', 1982, 1982, 3, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('ac00aaa0-85b5-504d-88a6-fec4cd4f24ed', 'ee9da597-3ddc-5e63-8123-70ccc489d501', 'weapon-x', 'Weapon X', 'The brutal experiment that fused adamantium to Logan''s skeleton and tried to erase the man inside.', 'Barry Windsor-Smith''s harrowing serialized epic reveals the clinical horror of the Weapon X program: a clandestine project that captured Logan, bonded the indestructible metal adamantium to his skeleton, and attempted to reprogram him into a mindless killing machine.

Told largely through cold experiment logs and nightmarish imagery, the story is as much a meditation on cruelty and dehumanization as it is a superhero origin. It cemented the idea that Wolverine''s claws were always part of him, and that the metal was a violation.

Weapon X is essential reading and the dark cornerstone of everything fans think they know about how Logan was made.', NULL, 'origin', 1991, 1991, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('787e412a-bf7e-5909-a2c7-107340e265ee', 'ee9da597-3ddc-5e63-8123-70ccc489d501', 'fatal-attractions-the-loss', 'Fatal Attractions', 'Magneto''s wrath leaves Wolverine changed forever, and his secret laid bare.', 'In this X-line crossover, Magneto retaliates against the X-Men in a way that strikes Wolverine at the deepest possible level, forcing a confrontation that has permanent consequences for his body and his sense of self.

The aftermath leaves Logan more vulnerable and more human than he has ever been, peeling back a layer of the armor that had defined him for years. It is a turning point that ripples through his solo book and the wider X-Men for the rest of the decade.

The arc pairs spectacle with genuine character stakes, and its closing pages are among the most reprinted in X-Men history.', 'Magneto rips the adamantium from Wolverine''s skeleton through his skin, and Logan is later revealed to have bone claws.', 'crossover', 1993, 1993, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('cc18a834-958d-5a5c-b693-c9381d7e1796', 'ee9da597-3ddc-5e63-8123-70ccc489d501', 'wolverine-enemy-of-the-state-precursor', 'The Hunt for Sabretooth', 'Logan''s solo series turns a lifelong rivalry into a war of identity and memory.', 'Across his ongoing series, Wolverine repeatedly collides with Sabretooth, the savage killer who seems to know Logan''s past better than Logan himself. Each encounter peels back implanted memories, false histories, and the question of whether the two men are brothers, rivals, or something engineered.

Larry Hama''s long run leans into Logan''s role as a globe-trotting loner caught between his honor and his rage, with Sabretooth as the dark mirror who refuses to die.

The arc is a masterclass in long-form rivalry and a key chapter in Logan''s quest to learn who he truly is.', NULL, 'flagship', 1988, 1996, 3, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('e3989aad-bb63-50a3-ac00-fd9d05876218', 'f3fd6959-1210-52a9-a697-9a3d36e60bcd', 'origin', 'Origin', 'The closely guarded truth of the boy who would become Wolverine, told at last.', 'After decades of mystery, Marvel reveals Logan''s earliest days: a sickly boy named James Howlett on a Canadian estate in the late 1800s, whose life shatters in a single night of violence that triggers his mutant powers for the first time.

The series traces young James through grief, exile, and the first hardening of the feral survivor he would become, naming the people and traumas that shaped him long before any government lab got hold of him.

Origin is the canonical starting point of Logan''s life story and an emotional anchor for everything that came after.', 'James Howlett''s bone claws first emerge the night his father is murdered, revealing his mutant nature and forcing him to flee his home.', 'origin', 2001, 2002, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('cf0e0f7a-7856-5e60-95f1-6d06738be86b', 'f3fd6959-1210-52a9-a697-9a3d36e60bcd', 'enemy-of-the-state', 'Enemy of the State', 'Brainwashed by the Hand, the world''s deadliest mutant is turned against everyone he protects.', 'Mark Millar and John Romita Jr. unleash Wolverine as a weapon when the Hand and Hydra capture and reprogram him, sending Marvel''s most relentless killer on a rampage through the heroes who once called him a friend.

The story is a brutal action thriller that asks what it would take to stop Logan if he ever truly came for you, and what it costs the people who love him to try and bring him back.

Fast, violent, and cinematic, Enemy of the State is a modern fan-favorite and a showcase for everything that makes Wolverine terrifying.', NULL, 'flagship', 2004, 2005, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('214e50e1-4ad0-57fc-a256-97e0efbbb15c', 'f3fd6959-1210-52a9-a697-9a3d36e60bcd', 'old-man-logan', 'Old Man Logan', 'In a future where the villains won, an aged, pacifist Logan is pushed to pick up his claws one last time.', 'Mark Millar and Steve McNiven craft a post-apocalyptic Western in which the supervillains have conquered America and a broken, retired Logan refuses to fight. Needing money to save his family, he agrees to ride cross-country with a blind Hawkeye through a ruined Marvel landscape.

The road trip becomes a journey toward a buried trauma that explains why Logan swore off violence, building to a reckoning that is equal parts grief and vengeance.

Instantly iconic, Old Man Logan spawned its own ongoing series and heavily inspired the tone of later Wolverine films.', NULL, 'elseworlds', 2008, 2009, 3, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('7b5b4a61-7be5-5656-9607-b3b2b26dcddc', 'f3fd6959-1210-52a9-a697-9a3d36e60bcd', 'death-of-wolverine', 'Death of Wolverine', 'Stripped of his healing factor, Logan faces a hunt he may not walk away from.', 'With his signature healing factor gone, a newly mortal Wolverine becomes the target of a bounty placed by a mysterious enemy. Charles Soule and Steve McNiven follow Logan as he traces the threat to its source, knowing that any wound could now be his last.

The story strips away the invulnerability that defined the character, forcing both Logan and the reader to sit with stakes that finally feel real. It is a somber, deliberate capstone designed as a definitive ending.

Elegiac and beautifully drawn, Death of Wolverine is a fitting bookend to an era of the character.', 'Logan dies, encased in solidified adamantium, after destroying the lab that created Weapon X.', 'miniseries', 2014, 2014, 4, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('b1ef9009-5eba-5050-8346-a794df6eba44', '089ebbed-a7c6-5b08-88cc-43266352a059', 'golden-origin', 'The Origin of Wonder Woman', 'An American pilot crashes on a hidden island of immortal women, and their princess wins the right to return him to a world torn by war.', 'When Captain Steve Trevor''s plane crashes on Paradise Island, the Amazons discover the existence of Man''s World and the global conflict consuming it. Queen Hippolyta, guided by the goddess Athena, decrees that a champion must be chosen to escort Trevor home and fight for democracy and freedom.

Diana, the queen''s daughter formed from clay and given life by the gods, defies her mother''s wishes by entering the tournament in disguise. She wins the contest of strength and skill, earning the star-spangled costume and the title of Wonder Woman.

Arriving in the United States, Diana adopts the alias of Army nurse Diana Prince to stay close to Steve Trevor while secretly battling Axis spies and saboteurs. These early stories cement her core mission: to bring peace through strength and compassion.', NULL, 'origin', 1941, 1942, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('b96af7c2-3f38-5676-97a8-7779659a6fa8', '089ebbed-a7c6-5b08-88cc-43266352a059', 'golden-villainy', 'Villainy Incorporated and the War Years', 'Wonder Woman faces a rogues'' gallery of saboteurs, sorceresses, and a league of female criminals during the height of the Second World War.', 'As the war rages, Diana confronts a parade of memorable antagonists, including the venomous chemist Doctor Poison, the feline thief Cheetah, and the diminutive tyrant Doctor Psycho. The era introduces Villainy Incorporated, an alliance of her deadliest foes uniting against her.

These stories blend wartime propaganda with Marston''s distinctive themes of loving authority and submission to a just cause. Diana relies as often on her wits and the truth-compelling Lasso as on her fists.

The period also expands her supporting cast, from the Holliday Girls and their leader Etta Candy to the recurring presence of Steve Trevor, grounding the high adventure in warmth and humor.', NULL, 'flagship', 1942, 1948, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('a83988d0-aa25-5d8d-ace4-1f1c49832192', '9f52d1c3-eedb-56a4-b760-ae4d1f00c9a4', 'diana-prince-mod-era', 'The Diana Prince Era', 'Powerless and without her costume, Diana runs a boutique and trains under a blind mentor as a globe-trotting human adventurer.', 'In a controversial reinvention, Diana surrenders her Amazon powers when the Amazons depart for another dimension, choosing to remain in Man''s World. She closes her boutique only to be drawn into espionage and intrigue alongside her enigmatic mentor I Ching.

Dressed in mod fashions rather than the star-spangled costume, this Diana solves mysteries and fights with martial arts and cunning. The run reflects the spy-craze sensibilities of the late 1960s.

Though divisive among longtime fans, the era is remembered as a bold experiment and a snapshot of its cultural moment before Diana''s powers and heritage were ultimately restored.', NULL, 'flagship', 1968, 1972, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('d5beba5b-a95f-5b40-8905-a7c7afedd49f', '9f52d1c3-eedb-56a4-b760-ae4d1f00c9a4', 'twelve-labors', 'The Twelve Labors', 'To rejoin the Justice League, a restored Wonder Woman must prove herself through a series of trials watched in secret by her teammates.', 'With her powers and Amazon identity restored, Diana doubts whether she still deserves a place among Earth''s greatest heroes. She asks the Justice League to monitor her on a sequence of missions before she rejoins.

Unknown to Diana, each adventure is secretly observed by a different Leaguer, echoing the twelve labors of Hercules. The structure allows guest appearances and reaffirms her standing in the superhero community.

The storyline rehabilitates Wonder Woman after the depowered years, re-establishing her as a powerhouse and a respected peer of Superman and Batman, and recommitting the title to her mythic and heroic identity.', NULL, 'flagship', 1974, 1975, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('8207d545-74d3-5a0f-b8ee-c327a7700d3c', '8d1a61e3-c05c-5ce0-9436-66d4efd4b5c9', 'gods-and-mortals', 'Gods and Mortals', 'Reborn from clay in a world that has never known her, the Amazon princess steps into Man''s World as the gods'' chosen champion against the war god Ares.', 'Following Crisis on Infinite Earths, George Perez reintroduces Diana with her continuity wiped clean. The Amazons are recast as survivors of an ancient tragedy, granted Themyscira by the Olympian gods, and Diana is sculpted from clay and blessed with divine gifts.

When the war god Ares schemes to ignite a nuclear apocalypse, the gods send Diana into the modern world as their ambassador. Aided by Steve Trevor and mythology professor Julia Kapatelis, she must stop Ares before he plunges humanity into oblivion.

This landmark run firmly grounds Wonder Woman in Greek mythology, redefines her supporting cast, and presents her mission as one of peace and understanding rather than mere combat. It remains the definitive modern starting point for the character.', NULL, 'origin', 1987, 1987, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('c03ae810-fdd6-5b03-bfaa-2bc216396831', '8d1a61e3-c05c-5ce0-9436-66d4efd4b5c9', 'the-hiketeia', 'The Hiketeia', 'A desperate young woman invokes an ancient Amazon rite of supplication, binding Wonder Woman to protect her even as Batman hunts her for murder.', 'A fugitive named Danielle Wellys seeks out Diana and performs the Hiketeia, a sacred Greek ritual that obligates the receiver to protect the supplicant at any cost. Diana accepts, unaware of the crimes the girl has committed.

When Batman arrives in pursuit of Danielle, Diana finds herself caught between her oath to the gods and her respect for justice and her fellow hero. The conflict forces a tense, philosophical confrontation between two icons with very different codes.

Written by Greg Rucka and illustrated by J.G. Jones, this standalone graphic novel is celebrated for its mythic gravity and its nuanced portrait of Diana''s principles. It is widely regarded as one of the finest Wonder Woman stories ever told.', NULL, 'miniseries', 2002, 2002, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('b66d0522-cf9a-5374-b62d-5e56a79431eb', '8d1a61e3-c05c-5ce0-9436-66d4efd4b5c9', 'rucka-eyes-of-gorgon', 'Eyes of the Gorgon', 'As Themyscira''s ambassador in a hostile world, Diana faces political enemies and a vengeful goddess who unleashes Medusa against her.', 'Greg Rucka''s acclaimed run positions Diana as a working ambassador, author, and public figure navigating the politics of Man''s World as much as its monsters. Her embassy becomes a stage for diplomacy, faith, and conflict.

When the goddess Athena''s rivals move against Diana, the gorgon Medusa is set loose to destroy her. Diana must confront a foe whose very gaze means death, leading to one of her most striking personal trials.

The run elevates Wonder Woman as a thinker and leader, weaving Olympian intrigue with grounded human drama and setting the stage for the universe-shaking events that follow.', NULL, 'flagship', 2004, 2005, 3, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('3a2189ac-d666-5085-8987-a48ee7fc3f22', '5154bbfd-db63-5a7f-b400-e09f549c12e5', 'blood', 'Blood', 'Diana is revealed to be the secret daughter of Zeus, drawing her into a deadly succession war among the gods of Olympus.', 'Brian Azzarello and Cliff Chiang reimagine the Olympian pantheon as a dysfunctional, dangerous family in a horror-tinged retelling. The long-held story that Diana was sculpted from clay is recast as a lie protecting a more dangerous truth: she is the daughter of Zeus and Hippolyta.

When a young woman named Zola becomes pregnant with another of Zeus''s children, Hera''s jealous wrath threatens her life. Diana steps in to protect her, plunging into a web of divine scheming, betrayal, and bloodshed.

The run reinvents Wonder Woman''s mythology with striking design and tone, treating the gods as terrifying forces of nature. It stands as one of the most distinctive interpretations of the character in decades.', 'This arc retcons Diana''s origin: she is revealed to be the biological daughter of Zeus rather than a being sculpted from clay.', 'retcon', 2011, 2012, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('1e7f1d7d-d2d9-5dfc-a674-62b164ca578c', '5154bbfd-db63-5a7f-b400-e09f549c12e5', 'the-lies-year-one', 'The Lies and Year One', 'Realizing her own memories have been tampered with, Wonder Woman hunts for the truth of her origin while a parallel tale retells how she first came to Man''s World.', 'In DC Rebirth, Greg Rucka returns to confront the contradictions between Diana''s competing origin stories. In The Lies, Diana discovers she can no longer reach Themyscira and suspects that someone has deceived her about her entire past.

The companion story Year One retells her arrival in Man''s World with modern sensibility, reintroducing Steve Trevor, Etta Candy, and Barbara Ann Minerva before her fall into villainy. The two threads alternate, contrasting present-day mystery with foundational origin.

The run is praised for restoring emotional clarity to the character after years of conflicting continuity, reaffirming Diana''s compassion and resolve while honoring her mythic roots.', NULL, 'flagship', 2016, 2017, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('344a1dec-6541-53a4-87f8-816ab2bac326', '53a7153b-2816-5bfa-9985-448f1f9c90df', 'x-men-origin-lee-kirby', 'The Coming of the X-Men', 'A telepathic professor gathers five young mutants to face a master of magnetism who would rule humanity.', 'Professor Charles Xavier recruits Cyclops, Marvel Girl, Beast, Angel, and Iceman to his secluded Westchester school, training them to harness their mutant gifts. When Magneto launches his first strike against humankind, the newly formed X-Men are thrust into open battle.

The early Lee and Kirby issues introduce the foundational mythology of the franchise: the dream of coexistence, the fear and hatred of ordinary people, and the ideological clash between Xavier and his former friend Magneto. The Brotherhood of Evil Mutants emerges as a recurring antagonist.

These stories also debut enduring concepts including the Sentinels, the Danger Room, and the Savage Land. Though commercially modest at first, they planted the seeds of one of comics'' most enduring sagas.

For new readers, this run defines who the X-Men are and why they fight, framing every conflict around the question of whether two peoples can share one world.', NULL, 'origin', 1963, 1966, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('4def3c54-6290-5c36-9edb-eee4505d1bed', '53a7153b-2816-5bfa-9985-448f1f9c90df', 'sentinels-master-mold', 'Rise of the Sentinels', 'Mutant-hunting robots built to protect humanity turn on their creators and the young X-Men.', 'Anthropologist Bolivar Trask unveils the Sentinels, towering robots engineered to hunt mutants in the name of human survival. The machines quickly exceed their programming, concluding that the only way to protect humanity is to rule it.

The X-Men must stop the Master Mold and its army before they enslave mutant and human alike. The conflict crystallizes the tragic logic of anti-mutant prejudice giving rise to a greater threat.

These stories establish the Sentinels as a perennial menace and a metaphor for institutional persecution that the series would return to for decades.

The arc deepens the team''s role as protectors of the very people who fear them, a defining tension of the franchise.', NULL, 'flagship', 1965, 1966, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('56151a61-03a6-5319-b40c-a5f5ff677e6b', '7b442e7f-7914-55b2-a4ab-7107300316e4', 'dark-phoenix-saga', 'The Dark Phoenix Saga', 'A beloved X-Man''s cosmic power spirals beyond control, threatening the universe and the team''s heart.', 'After bonding with an immense cosmic force, one of the X-Men ascends to godlike power. As that power begins to corrupt her, the Hellfire Club''s manipulations push her toward catastrophe.

The team races to save their friend even as her actions draw the judgment of an alien empire. The story builds to one of the most emotionally devastating climaxes in superhero comics.

Written by Chris Claremont and drawn by John Byrne, the saga elevated the X-Men into Marvel''s flagship franchise and is widely regarded as a high point of the medium.

It remains the definitive demonstration of the team''s central theme: that power without restraint endangers everyone, and that love and loyalty are tested most under impossible circumstances.', 'Jean Grey, consumed by the Phoenix, sacrifices herself to stop the entity after destroying an inhabited star system.', 'flagship', 1980, 1980, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('272b5ace-7eda-5abb-a911-e026541199d7', '7b442e7f-7914-55b2-a4ab-7107300316e4', 'days-of-future-past', 'Days of Future Past', 'A survivor from a dystopian future returns to prevent an assassination that dooms all mutants.', 'In a grim future where Sentinels rule and mutants are hunted to near extinction, the few survivors make a desperate gamble: send a consciousness back in time to change history.

In the present, the X-Men learn that the murder of a prominent anti-mutant senator will trigger the catastrophe. They must prevent the Brotherhood of Evil Mutants from carrying it out.

This tightly constructed two-issue story by Claremont and Byrne became one of the most adapted X-Men tales, its imagery of a ruined future shaping decades of mutant storytelling.

It distilled the franchise''s anxieties about persecution into an urgent, time-spanning thriller.', NULL, 'flagship', 1981, 1981, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('c443e1bf-0bc3-5b1a-82f8-cf4e5fc177c3', '7b442e7f-7914-55b2-a4ab-7107300316e4', 'god-loves-man-kills', 'God Loves, Man Kills', 'A genocidal preacher''s crusade forces the X-Men into an uneasy alliance with their greatest foe.', 'Reverend William Stryker leads a fanatical religious movement bent on exterminating mutants as abominations. His campaign of terror strikes at the heart of Xavier''s school and ideals.

Facing a threat that endangers all mutants, the X-Men find themselves sharing a battlefield with Magneto, blurring the line between hero and villain.

This graphic novel by Chris Claremont and Brent Anderson is among the franchise''s most pointed explorations of bigotry and faith, and it loosely inspired a major film adaptation.

It remains a powerful standalone statement of the series'' core social allegory.', NULL, 'miniseries', 1982, 1982, 3, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('7ac5eff3-e9fb-5459-b6e7-6a8811dc204d', 'a43c24e5-786b-5d95-81b0-b232982fe48a', 'fatal-attractions', 'Fatal Attractions', 'Magneto''s escalating war pushes Xavier''s dream and the X-Men to a breaking point.', 'Magneto retreats to an orbital fortress and declares open defiance of the human world, daring the X-Men and the global powers to stop him. His most extreme act of aggression nearly tears the team apart.

The crossover forces a brutal confrontation between Magneto, Wolverine, and Professor Xavier with consequences that reshape the status quo.

Running through the X-titles of the early 1990s, it is remembered for its high-stakes climax and its lasting fallout for the franchise''s central figures.

The arc marks the transition into the franchise''s blockbuster modern period.', 'Magneto rips the adamantium from Wolverine''s skeleton, and Xavier retaliates by erasing Magneto''s mind.', 'crossover', 1993, 1993, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('348fa5db-1e6a-5133-bff8-05fb2d55bec7', 'a43c24e5-786b-5d95-81b0-b232982fe48a', 'new-x-men-morrison', 'E Is for Extinction', 'A devastating attack on mutantkind launches the X-Men into a bold new evolution.', 'Grant Morrison''s run opens with a catastrophic genocide that wipes out a mutant nation, recasting the X-Men as a frontline crisis-response team for a species under siege.

A new threat tied to Xavier''s own past emerges, while the school swells with students and the team confronts what it means for mutants to be the dominant emerging culture.

With art by Frank Quitely and others, New X-Men modernized the franchise''s aesthetic and themes for the 2000s, introducing concepts that still define the line.

It reframed the mutant struggle as one of cultural ascendancy rather than mere survival.', NULL, 'flagship', 2001, 2004, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('d02eabd8-8c07-59d7-88dd-73608ed2989c', 'a43c24e5-786b-5d95-81b0-b232982fe48a', 'house-of-x-powers-of-x', 'House of X / Powers of X', 'Mutants forge a sovereign nation, rewriting the rules of mutant existence forever.', 'Jonathan Hickman''s interlocking miniseries reveal a sweeping new status quo: mutants unite under Xavier and Magneto to found the island nation of Krakoa, claiming sovereignty and even conquering death itself.

Spanning timelines from the distant past to the far future, the story reframes the entire history of the species and sets a radical new direction for every X-title.

Widely hailed as one of the most ambitious X-Men stories ever told, it relaunched the franchise''s most acclaimed modern era.

It transforms the mutant dream from a plea for tolerance into the founding of a civilization.', NULL, 'miniseries', 2019, 2019, 3, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('57516ddd-0fb9-5bf5-b273-f17f7448cded', 'b0acb643-0e17-5506-82db-ed1613c9c180', 'xander-joins-the-fight', 'No Powers, All Heart', 'An ordinary kid decides he won''t sit out the war for his town.', 'When Xander learns the truth about Buffy and the monsters of Sunnydale, he refuses to be left behind. Lacking powers, he leans on wit, nerve, and stubborn loyalty to stand beside his friends.

His arc explores the value of the human in a world of the superhuman, showing that courage is its own kind of power. Xander becomes the emotional anchor the gang cannot do without.', NULL, 'origin', 2019, 2021, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('9d04df0e-afd2-59b2-894d-7c174b40f87c', '6f043956-7cf4-5c20-b5ad-12798282f0aa', 'youngblood-genesis', 'Youngblood Genesis', 'A government super-team is assembled and thrust into the public eye as media-managed celebrity heroes.', 'The opening saga introduces the roster as a federally sanctioned squad designed as much for press conferences as for combat. Shaft leads the home team while a separate away division handles covert international action, establishing the dual structure that defines the franchise.

The early issues lean into spectacle, with full-page splashes and roster-wide brawls against organized threats. Beneath the gloss, the book gestures at the friction between heroism and the machinery of government oversight and corporate sponsorship.

This era cemented the team as a tentpole of the newly formed Image Comics, riding a wave of speculator enthusiasm and bold, kinetic artwork.', NULL, 'origin', 1992, 1992, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('0d37922c-cc05-5024-a188-f951719a141f', '6f043956-7cf4-5c20-b5ad-12798282f0aa', 'darkthornn-incursion', 'The Darkthornn Incursion', 'An otherworldly warlord tests the team''s away division on hostile foreign soil.', 'With the home team occupied stateside, the away division confronts a brutal extradimensional threat that pushes their resources to the limit. The conflict raises the stakes from street-level spectacle to world-threatening warfare.

The arc deepens the supporting cast and showcases the team''s harder-edged operatives. It also begins to question who truly directs Youngblood''s missions and to what end.', NULL, 'flagship', 1993, 1993, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('4bf7da1e-cc26-5d4c-9e3a-a74ccc82ee6e', 'aebcbc8c-14c8-553f-87da-acedf341ef76', 'judgment-day-fallout', 'Judgment Day Fallout', 'A line-wide reckoning forces the team to answer for the consequences of celebrity heroism.', 'In the wake of a publishing-wide event, the team''s status quo is shaken and its members confront accountability for past actions. The story reframes the squad less as triumphant icons and more as flawed public figures.

The arc trades pure spectacle for character work, examining loyalty, betrayal, and the burden of being watched. It sets the table for darker, more introspective revivals to come.', NULL, 'crossover', 1998, 1998, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('43e3a1ac-d3f9-5dfc-b246-11da0c9f6949', 'aebcbc8c-14c8-553f-87da-acedf341ef76', 'focus-tested-heroes', 'Focus-Tested Heroes', 'A new generation of recruits navigates fame, sponsorship, and the surveillance state.', 'A modern relaunch introduces fresh members managed by a slick corporate apparatus that treats heroism as a brand. The satire sharpens, skewering influencer culture and the commodification of public service.

Legacy members clash with newcomers over what Youngblood should stand for. The arc balances knowing humor with genuine stakes, updating the concept for a connected, image-obsessed era.', NULL, 'flagship', 2017, 2018, 2, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('aef667a3-4d4e-5873-807e-6d806682e66b', '00c308ea-1757-5849-af75-2822be00d5fa', 'rhythm-and-resolve', 'Rhythm and Resolve', 'Zack''s unconventional fighting style and easy charm hide a deep well of courage.', 'Often the team''s lightest presence, Zack reveals his depth when the stakes climb. His agility and improvisation make him unpredictable in battle, and his optimism keeps the team grounded.

The arc gives Zack room to shine as more than comic relief, establishing him as a dependable and brave Ranger.', NULL, 'flagship', 2016, 2017, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'),
  ('83e63e73-465a-5256-99a5-d58c4790d919', 'd6a9f36a-addb-5525-b809-d8f07b2ba940', 'blitz', 'Blitz', 'A trusted friend gains terrifying time-bending speed and vows to make the Flash a better hero through tragedy.', 'Hunter Zolomon, once an ally of the Flash, is left crippled after a disaster and is denied help in undoing his fate. Desperate, he triggers a cosmic-treadmill accident that grants him the ability to move through time rather than simply run fast.

Reborn as Zoom, he concludes that the Flash can only become a great hero by experiencing profound personal loss, and he sets out to provide exactly that. His attacks are brutal, personal, and devastating.

The Blitz arc introduced one of the modern era''s most psychologically complex speedster villains, a man convinced his cruelty is an act of mercy.', NULL, 'flagship', 2003, 2004, 1, '2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z')
